const QDATA={"reading": [{"id": "R115-1", "year": 115, "no": 1, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Look at the picture. All of the students who are exercising are wearing ___.", "options": {"A": "caps", "B": "glasses", "C": "jackets", "D": "pants"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "這題要看原卷的圖片才能確定「正在運動的學生都戴著什麼」，答案是 glasses（眼鏡）。因為答案完全取決於圖片內容，沒有圖片無法單靠句子判斷。", "keyPoint": "看圖選字彙", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R115-2", "year": 115, "no": 2, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Rita ___ her dogs many times a day. That's why they're too fat.", "options": {"A": "feeds", "B": "kisses", "C": "walks", "D": "washes"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後半句 That's why they're too fat（所以牠們太胖了）是關鍵線索：狗會胖通常是因為吃太多，所以是 feeds（餵食）她的狗很多次。walks（散步）、kisses（親吻）、washes（洗澡）都不會讓狗變胖，所以不選。", "keyPoint": "語意推理：因果關係", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-3", "year": 115, "no": 3, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "You can ask Sophia anything about butterflies and bees. She has great ___ of insects.", "options": {"A": "chances", "B": "knowledge", "C": "news", "D": "power"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "She has great ___ of insects，能回答任何關於蝴蝶和蜜蜂的問題，代表她對昆蟲有豐富的「知識」，所以選 knowledge。chances（機會）、news（消息）、power（力量）都跟「懂很多」的意思對不上。", "keyPoint": "have knowledge of 片語", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-4", "year": 115, "no": 4, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Adam slept ___ last night because he kept waking up from bad dreams.", "options": {"A": "deeply", "B": "early", "C": "terribly", "D": "quickly"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "because 後面說他一直做惡夢驚醒，可知他昨晚睡得「很糟」，所以選 terribly（糟糕地）。deeply（沉沉地）、quickly（快速地）、early（早）都和「一直驚醒」矛盾，不合邏輯。", "keyPoint": "語意推理：因果關係", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-5", "year": 115, "no": 5, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Tara enjoys being with all kinds of animals; she even ___ a snake as a pet.", "options": {"A": "drops", "B": "gives", "C": "keeps", "D": "makes"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "she even ___ a snake as pet，句意是她甚至「養」一條蛇當寵物，keep... as pet 是固定用法，選 keeps。drops（丟下）、gives（給）、makes（製作）都不符合「養寵物」的意思。", "keyPoint": "keep + 動物 + as pet", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-6", "year": 115, "no": 6, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Little Eric chose the doll ___ big brown eyes because it was the cutest in the store.", "options": {"A": "at", "B": "in", "C": "on", "D": "with"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "the doll ___ big brown eyes 表示「有一雙大棕色眼睛的娃娃」，with 表示「具有…特徵」，是固定用法（with + 身體特徵）。at/in/on 都不能表達「擁有某特徵」的意思。", "keyPoint": "with 表特徵", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-7", "year": 115, "no": 7, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "After four hours of mountain climbing, Rosa's legs got ___, so she took a rest on the top of the mountain.", "options": {"A": "dirty", "B": "sick", "C": "sore", "D": "strong"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "爬山四小時後腿部感覺，接著 took a rest（休息）表示腿在痛，所以選 sore（痠痛的）。dirty（髒）、sick（生病）、strong（強壯）都跟「爬山後需要休息」的情境不合。", "keyPoint": "語意推理：身體狀態形容詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-8", "year": 115, "no": 8, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Having three cups of coffee a day can't be bad for our health, ___?", "options": {"A": "can it", "B": "can they", "C": "is it", "D": "are they"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "這是附加問句(tag question)，前面主要子句是 Having three cups... can't be bad，主詞其實是動名詞片語（視為單數 it），且前面是 can't（否定），附加問句要用肯定＋原本助動詞 can，所以是 can it。", "keyPoint": "附加問句 tag question", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-9", "year": 115, "no": 9, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "You can't push that door open with only one hand. It's too heavy. You have to use ___!", "options": {"A": "all", "B": "another", "C": "both", "D": "one"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "只用一隻手推不開，要用「兩隻」手，both 表示「兩者都」剛好對應「一隻手（one hand）」對比「兩隻手」，所以選 both。all（全部，三個以上）、another（另一個）、one（一個）都不符合「兩隻手」的情境。", "keyPoint": "both 表兩者都", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-10", "year": 115, "no": 10, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Alan works hard in his new job, and he wants to know ___ his boss feels about him.", "options": {"A": "how", "B": "that", "C": "whether", "D": "why"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "he wants to know ___ his boss feels about him，問的是老闆對他「感覺如何」，how... feel 是固定問法（詢問感受程度/狀態），選 how。whether（是否）、why（為什麼）、that（引導名詞子句但不能配合 feels 表達方式）都不合句意。", "keyPoint": "How + 主詞 + feel 表達感受", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-11", "year": 115, "no": 11, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "I thought the girl ___ was Kate, but it was her sister, Candy. They sounded almost the same.", "options": {"A": "answered the phone", "B": "she answered the phone", "C": "who answered the phone", "D": "and answered the phone"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "I thought the girl ___ was Kate，這裡需要一個關係子句修飾 the girl（那個接電話的女孩），主詞是 girl，關代要用 who 代替人當主詞，選 who answered the phone。其餘選項不是完整關係子句結構，會讓句子文法錯誤。", "keyPoint": "who 引導的關係子句（形容詞子句）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-12", "year": 115, "no": 12, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Ken is going abroad with a woman he met online, though he doesn't know ___ well.", "options": {"A": "her", "B": "each other", "C": "any", "D": "another"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "he doesn't know ___ well，doesn't know 後面要接受詞，指的是「那位他在網路上認識的女性」，用受格代名詞 her 代替 a woman，選 her。each other（互相）、any（任何）、another（另一個）都無法自然代替 the woman 這個受詞。", "keyPoint": "受格代名詞 her 代替前面提到的人", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-13", "year": 115, "no": 13, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Joe is happy he is not at the ___ of the class now. His grades are better than half of his classmates' this school year.", "options": {"A": "side", "B": "front", "C": "center", "D": "bottom"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後句說 His grades are better than half of his classmates'，表示他成績進步、不再是班上最後面，所以是 not at the bottom（不在班級的「底部/最後」）。side、front、center 都跟「排名最後」無關。", "keyPoint": "at the bottom 表排名最後", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-14", "year": 115, "no": 14, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Look! There is not a cloud in the sky. I think the chances of getting some rain today are really ___.", "options": {"A": "far", "B": "good", "C": "possible", "D": "small"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "There is not a cloud in the sky（天空一朵雲都沒有）表示不太可能下雨，所以下雨機會是「很小 small」。good（好/大）、possible（可能）、far（遠）都與「晴朗無雲」的線索矛盾。", "keyPoint": "語意推理：天氣線索", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-15", "year": 115, "no": 15, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "On windy days, the flowers in my garden ___ like shy children with their heads down.", "options": {"A": "bow", "B": "fall", "C": "rise", "D": "smell"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "like shy children with their heads down（像害羞低著頭的孩子）形容花在風中「低垂彎腰」的樣子，所以是 bow（鞠躬/低垂）。fall（掉落）、rise（升起）、smell（聞）都不符合「低頭」的畫面。", "keyPoint": "語意推理：比喻描寫", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-16", "year": 115, "no": 16, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Mr. Olson went to the doctor when he found he ___ his hair. He hoped he would be able to keep his thick hair.", "options": {"A": "was losing", "B": "is losing", "C": "will lose", "D": "has lost"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "he found he ___ his hair 描述「發現自己頭髮正在掉」，是過去某時間點正在進行的狀態，用過去進行式 was losing，配合主要子句 went（過去式）語意一致。is/will/has 時態都跟整句過去式背景不搭。", "keyPoint": "過去進行式", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-17", "year": 115, "no": 17, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Do you know what Lindsey's first job was? Before becoming a movie star, she ___ the floors at the supermarket.", "options": {"A": "mops", "B": "is mopping", "C": "has mopped", "D": "mopped"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "Before becoming a movie star（成為明星之前）表示這是過去已完成、單純的過去動作，所以用簡單過去式 mopped。mops（現在式）、is mopping（現在進行）、has mopped（現在完成）都跟「過去、已成明星」的時間點不符。", "keyPoint": "過去簡單式表示過去單一動作", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-18", "year": 115, "no": 18, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Our dog Lassie hides under the bed every time the moon comes out. She has been ___ for years, but we don't know why.", "options": {"A": "it", "B": "like this", "C": "like us", "D": "that"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "She has been ___ for years，描述狗多年來「一直是這樣（躲床下）」的習慣行為，like this（像這樣）指代前面「每次月亮出來就躲床下」的行為模式。it、that是代名詞不能接 like us 之類自然銜接，like us（像我們）語意不合。", "keyPoint": "like this 指代前述行為", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-19", "year": 115, "no": 19, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Tom: Sam, could you help me in the kitchen now?\nSam: No, I ___ TV. It's the most important game of the season.", "options": {"A": "watch", "B": "watched", "C": "have watched", "D": "am watching"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "Sam 說 No，表示現在正在做某事沒空幫忙，It's the most important game（現在正播的比賽）表示動作正在進行，所以用現在進行式 am watching。watch/watched/have watched 都無法表達「此刻正在做」的意思。", "keyPoint": "現在進行式表示當下動作", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-20", "year": 115, "no": 20, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Amanda wants to make fruit tea by following The Best Fruit Tea You Can Make at Home. She has several kinds of fruit in the kitchen: apples, bananas, oranges, papayas, pears, and strawberries. Which are some of the fruits she can use to make the fruit tea?", "options": {"A": "Oranges, papayas and pears.", "B": "Apples, bananas and oranges.", "C": "Apples, oranges and strawberries.", "D": "Bananas, papayas and strawberries."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "115-P1", "explain": "文章說水果茶用 apples, bananas, oranges, papayas, pears, strawberries 加上檸檬汁製作，但食譜實際用的是文中提到的水果，對照選項只有 C「Apples, oranges and strawberries」是文中確實列出的水果組合。", "keyPoint": "細節題：對照文章列出的水果", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R115-21", "year": 115, "no": 21, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "According to the reading, which is correct when we make the fruit tea?", "options": {"A": "Boiling water with sugar in it.", "B": "Making sure to take out the fruit.", "C": "Putting in the fruit and the lemon juice at the same time.", "D": "Leaving the teabags in the pot of hot water for 2 to 3 minutes."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "115-P1", "explain": "文章步驟提到先煮水、放茶包，讓茶包泡在熱水中一段時間（2到3分鐘），再放水果和檸檬汁，最後要把水果取出。選項D「將茶包留在熱水中2-3分鐘」符合步驟順序，其他選項（加糖、水果檸檬汁同時加、不取出水果）都與流程不符。", "keyPoint": "細節題：步驟流程比對", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R115-22", "year": 115, "no": 22, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "According to the comics, what kind of person is Hawkins?", "options": {"A": "He sees good things in people.", "B": "He never goes to work on time.", "C": "He blindly follows other people.", "D": "He talks about things he can't do."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "115-P2", "explain": "漫畫裡 Hawkins 一直說大話（要縮短上課時間、要賣149台車），結果都做不到（bombed），這顯示他是「說自己做不到的事」的人，選D。他並沒有表現出看到別人優點(A)、盲從(C)或不準時(B)的行為。", "keyPoint": "推論題：人物性格判斷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-23", "year": 115, "no": 23, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does it mean when we say someone bombed something?", "options": {"A": "They gave it up.", "B": "They failed at it.", "C": "They were fine with it.", "D": "They were careful about it."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P2", "explain": "文中 Hawkins 說要賣149台車卻只賣1台，接著說 I bombed it again，之後就被公司開除(pack your things)，可知 bombed 表示「搞砸、失敗」，選B。並不是放棄(A)、沒關係(C)或小心(D)。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：bomb（搞砸）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-24", "year": 115, "no": 24, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Which question can the brochure answer?", "options": {"A": "Can I order tickets online?", "B": "How much are the tickets?", "C": "How can I get to the Marigolds' Home?", "D": "When can I visit the Marigolds' Home?"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "115-P3", "explain": "宣傳手冊列出了 Opening times（開放時間：3-10月、11-2月的時段及公休日），因此可以回答「何時能參觀」，選D。手冊沒提到線上訂票、票價或交通方式，所以A、B、C都無法從手冊得知。", "keyPoint": "細節題：找出手冊涵蓋的資訊", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-25", "year": 115, "no": 25, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What breaks the rules for visitors to the Marigolds' Home?", "options": {"A": "Eating burgers in the Rose Garden.", "B": "Taking pictures in the Main House.", "C": "Entering the Rabbit's Temple without shoes.", "D": "Taking pet dogs for a walk on the playground."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "115-P3", "explain": "規則第1條說 Pets are not allowed in any areas，所以帶寵物狗去操場散步違反規則，選D。吃東西只有在建築物內禁止，Rose Garden不算室內(A)可能不違規；拍照禁止的是Sir Archie's House不是Main House(B)；進入Rabbit's Temple要脫鞋，選項C說「不脫鞋進入」才違規，但選項描述並非違規行為的正確對應。", "keyPoint": "細節題：規則比對", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R115-26", "year": 115, "no": 26, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "After shopping at the gift shop of the Main House, Lizzy walks out and sees the Family Library in front of her. She wants to visit the Rose Garden. How can she get there?", "options": {"A": "Turn left and walk past the Main House, then go straight and turn right at the corner.", "B": "Turn left and walk past Sir Archie's House, then turn right and walk past the Main House.", "C": "Turn right and go straight to the Farmyard, then turn right and go straight, then turn left at the corner.", "D": "Turn right and walk through the Butterfly Garden, then walk past the Rabbit's Temple and the café."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "115-P3", "explain": "這題必須對照原卷提供的園區地圖，依照 Lizzy 目前所在位置（禮品店走出來看到Family Library）規劃走到 Rose Garden 的路線，答案是C的路線敘述符合地圖上的相對位置。", "keyPoint": "看地圖規劃路線", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R115-27", "year": 115, "no": 27, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why was Beatrice Harrison called the Nightingale Lady?", "options": {"A": "She wrote songs about nightingales.", "B": "She sang as beautifully as a nightingale did.", "C": "She taught nightingales to sing in a radio show.", "D": "She was famous for playing music with nightingales."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "115-P4", "explain": "文章說 Harrison 常和夜鶯一起在花園演奏大提琴，經BBC轉播後大受歡迎，持續12年，所以人們稱她「夜鶯女士」是因為她「因與夜鶯一起演奏音樂而出名」，選D。她沒有寫關於夜鶯的歌(A)、沒有像夜鶯一樣唱歌(B)、也沒有教夜鶯唱歌(C)。", "keyPoint": "細節題：稱號由來", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-28", "year": 115, "no": 28, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "Which is NOT used in the reading to mean the nightingale(s)?", "options": {"A": "Her visitor.", "B": "The little singers.", "C": "The artist.", "D": "Her garden friends."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "115-P4", "explain": "文中 her visitor、the little singers、her garden friends 都是用來指「夜鶯」，但 the artist（藝術家）指的是演奏大提琴的 Harrison 本人，不是夜鶯，所以選C。", "keyPoint": "指代題：找出不同指稱對象", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-29", "year": 115, "no": 29, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why does Alex Jackson write about Rose Lacey?", "options": {"A": "Because she died.", "B": "Because she is very sick.", "C": "Because she is moving away.", "D": "Because she is leaving for another job."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "115-P5", "explain": "文章開頭說 we are here to say goodbye to Rose Lacey，加上文末提到 In her short life of 40 years，這是一篇悼詞，表示 Rose 已經過世了，所以選A。文中沒提到她生病、搬家或換工作。", "keyPoint": "細節題：文章性質（悼詞）判斷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-30", "year": 115, "no": 30, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "How did Rose Lacey and Alex Jackson get to know each other?", "options": {"A": "They met at a party.", "B": "They were relatives.", "C": "They worked in the same office.", "D": "They took a course on movies together."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "115-P5", "explain": "文章說 I was at a party to pick up my wife when I heard Rose explaining... 表示他們是在一場派對上認識的，選A。文中沒提到親戚關係、同辦公室或一起上課。", "keyPoint": "細節題：如何相識", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-31", "year": 115, "no": 31, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What is special about Rose Lacey's articles?", "options": {"A": "They are important to movie makers.", "B": "They talk about movies from a fresh angle.", "C": "They give interesting information about actors.", "D": "They are good examples of how to write stories."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P5", "explain": "文章說 Rose could always bring out something new from movies that we thought we knew so well，讓讀者用全新角度重新體驗電影，這正是「從新的角度談論電影」，選B。文中沒特別強調對電影製作人的重要性(A)、演員資訊(C)或寫作範本(D)。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：文章特色歸納", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-32", "year": 115, "no": 32, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "Why does the title say \"Glass Bottles' Second Life\"?", "options": {"A": "People collect sea glass and use it to make new glass bottles.", "B": "People collect sea glass at the beach and use it to make wishes.", "C": "Glass bottles that are thrown into the sea become the homes of sea animals.", "D": "Glass bottles that are thrown into the sea become sea glass which is used in art pieces."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "115-P6", "explain": "文章說玻璃瓶被丟進海裡，經過海浪打磨多年後變成海玻璃，最後被藝術家拿去做藝術品，等於玻璃瓶有了「第二次生命」，選D。其餘選項提到做新瓶子、許願、海洋動物的家都不是文章內容。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：標題含義", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-33", "year": 115, "no": 33, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "According to the reading, how is sea glass made?", "options": {"A": "Sea glass becomes rounder after it is pushed up to the beach.", "B": "Colder sea water helps pieces of glass become sea glass faster.", "C": "Pieces of glass become white on the outside after many years in the sea.", "D": "Glass bottles break into pieces when they are dug out from the sea floor."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "115-P6", "explain": "文章步驟4提到 After tens or hundreds of years in the sea, the pieces of glass grow an ice-like white color on the outside，說明玻璃碎片在海裡多年後外表變白，選C。海玻璃是先變圓再被沖上岸，不是A的順序；沒有提到水溫影響速度(B)；玻璃瓶是被丟入海中而非從海底挖出(D)。", "keyPoint": "細節題：海玻璃形成步驟", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-34", "year": 115, "no": 34, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "According to the reading, why will less sea glass be found in the future?", "options": {"A": "People do not make as many glass items as before.", "B": "People have learned not to throw garbage into the sea.", "C": "Artists are using too much sea glass in their art pieces.", "D": "Waves are not big enough to push sea glass up to the beach."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "115-P6", "explain": "文末說 people now seldom use glass to make bottles and bowls—paper bowls and cups have become more popular，代表玻璃製品變少，海裡的玻璃瓶也變少，未來海玻璃會越來越少，選A。文章沒提到人們不再丟垃圾(B)、藝術家用太多(C)或海浪變小(D)。", "keyPoint": "推論題：因果推理", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-35", "year": 115, "no": 35, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does the prevalence of English mean?", "options": {"A": "That English is very common.", "B": "That English is not welcomed.", "C": "That English is easy and simple.", "D": "That English is not a national language."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "115-P7", "explain": "文章接著舉例說英文出現在手機、電視、機器人各處，可知 prevalence 表示英文「非常普遍/常見」，選A。並非「不受歡迎」(B)、「簡單」(C)或「非官方語言」(D)。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：prevalence（普遍）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-36", "year": 115, "no": 36, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "In the first reading, which is one of the ways that Anna Adams uses to make readers believe in her ideas?", "options": {"A": "Sharing her own life stories.", "B": "Borrowing from people's experience.", "C": "Using examples from another language.", "D": "Showing information from news reports."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P7", "explain": "Anna Adams 在文章中引用工程師 Helgi Atlason 和老師 Eirikur Wilson 說的話（別人的親身經驗）來支持自己的論點，屬於「借用他人經驗」，選B。她沒有分享自己的生活故事、比較其他語言或引用新聞報導數據。", "keyPoint": "推論題：論證方式判斷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-37", "year": 115, "no": 37, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "Which words in the second reading are NOT used to describe Icelandic?", "options": {"A": "A language in its sickbed.", "B": "A dying language.", "C": "Our first language.", "D": "This beautiful language."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P7", "explain": "第二篇文章開頭提到別人形容冰島語是 a language in its sickbed（病榻上的語言）且說 needs to be saved，但作者反駁說我們並沒有放棄冰島語，並沒有直接稱它是 a dying language（垂死的語言），這是第一篇/他人觀點的說法而非第二篇文章描述冰島語的用詞，選B。", "keyPoint": "指代題：找出文中未用的描述詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-38", "year": 115, "no": 38, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Are Anna Adams and Gunnar Eggertsson worried about the future of Icelandic?", "options": {"A": "No, they are not.", "B": "Yes, they both are.", "C": "Adams is, but Eggertsson is not.", "D": "Adams is not, but Eggertsson is."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "115-P7", "explain": "第一篇 Anna Adams 認為冰島語可能會消失，很擔心（Will Iceland one day give up Icelandic...?）；第二篇 Gunnar Eggertsson 則反駁說冰島語沒有真的那麼糟，語氣是安心、不擔心的，所以是「Adams擔心，但Eggertsson不擔心」，選C。", "keyPoint": "推論題：比較兩篇作者立場", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-39", "year": 115, "no": 39, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "Which idea do Anna Adams and Gunnar Eggertsson both talk about in the readings?", "options": {"A": "Whether Icelanders speak better English than Icelandic.", "B": "Whether the number of Icelandic speakers is big enough.", "C": "Whether school subjects should be taught only in Icelandic.", "D": "Whether Iceland should allow more foreigners to work in Iceland."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P7", "explain": "兩篇文章都提到冰島語使用人數（314,000人）這個數字，第一篇認為人數太少令人擔心，第二篇則引用學者說法認為35,000人以上就算安全，兩人都在討論「冰島語使用人數是否足夠」，選B。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：找出兩篇共同討論的議題", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-40", "year": 115, "no": 40, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Choose the best word(s) for blank 40 in the story.", "options": {"A": "give you a piece of good land", "B": "choose a person to be the next king", "C": "put the beautiful ones in my castle", "D": "decide who will work in my garden"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P8", "explain": "故事開頭說國王沒有孩子，擔心土地落入錯的人手中，於是決定挑一個孩子繼承王位，並發種子考驗大家，因此老國王說的「我將會___」應該是「選一個人成為下一任國王」，選B，與後文選出Wong當國王呼應。", "keyPoint": "推論題：文意銜接（故事開頭伏筆）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-41", "year": 115, "no": 41, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Choose the best sentence for blank 41 in the story.", "options": {"A": "But he lost his pot a few weeks later", "B": "Months passed but nothing grew from it", "C": "But soon the plant that grew from it died", "D": "The seed grew into a big tree in a short time"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P8", "explain": "後文說 Wong still didn't find anything in his，和最後揭曉「國王把種子煮過所以不會發芽」呼應，可知Wong的盆子裡好幾個月都沒長出東西，選B「Months passed but nothing grew from it」。其餘選項提到盆子弄丟、植物長出又死掉、長成大樹，都與後文矛盾。", "keyPoint": "推論題：故事情節銜接", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-42", "year": 115, "no": 42, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Choose the best word(s) for blank 42 in the story.", "options": {"A": "the last one to give up", "B": "the first one to share good news", "C": "the first one to bring his pot to the king", "D": "the only one to take good care of his plant"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "115-P8", "explain": "Sung 告訴大家他的種子長出小植物，別人才「excitedly said that he would be king」，可知Sung是第一個宣布好消息的人，選B「the first one to share good news」。他其實種子沒真的發芽（因為種子都被煮過），所以不是真的細心照顧(D)或最先送盆子去給國王(C)。", "keyPoint": "推論題：人物行為描述", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R115-43", "year": 115, "no": 43, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Choose the best word for blank 43 in the story.", "options": {"A": "wise", "B": "strong", "C": "honest", "D": "popular"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "115-P8", "explain": "國王把種子煮過讓它們不能發芽，目的是測試誰誠實，只有Wong誠實地帶著沒長出東西的空盆子來，沒有像其他孩子一樣假裝或找別的植物來冒充，所以國王稱讚的是「誠實(honest)」的孩子，選C。", "keyPoint": "推論題：故事寓意（誠實）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-1", "year": 114, "no": 1, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Look at the picture. A ___ is flying over the houses.", "options": {"A": "bird", "B": "butterfly", "C": "kite", "D": "plane"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "題目要看圖才能確定天上飛的是什麼。句意是「一台___正飛過房子上方」，圖裡畫的是飛機，所以選 plane。鳥（bird）、蝴蝶（butterfly）、風箏（kite）都是常見會「飛」的東西，用來混淆考生，但要以圖片內容為準。", "keyPoint": "看圖選字彙", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-2", "year": 114, "no": 2, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "When I was a teenager, I was very ___ . But now, it’s easier for me to talk to people.", "options": {"A": "happy", "B": "lazy", "C": "popular", "D": "shy"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "關鍵在 But now, it's easier for me to talk to people，表示「現在」和「以前（青少年時期）」形成對比，以前應該是「怕生、害羞」，長大後才變得敢跟人說話，所以選 shy。happy、lazy、popular 都跟「不敢跟人講話」這件事沒有直接因果關係。", "keyPoint": "前後對比推語意", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-3", "year": 114, "no": 3, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Lena doesn’t want to go ___ with John because she is afraid of water.", "options": {"A": "dancing", "B": "hiking", "C": "sailing", "D": "shopping"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "關鍵字是 afraid of water（怕水），四個選項中只有 sailing（駕船、坐船出海）跟水有關，所以 Lena 才會因為怕水而不想跟 John 去 sailing。hiking、shopping、dancing 都跟水無關。", "keyPoint": "因果線索字 afraid of water", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-4", "year": 114, "no": 4, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Cindy enjoys ___ her dad read stories to her before bed.", "options": {"A": "to listen to", "B": "listening to", "C": "listen to", "D": "listens to"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "enjoy 後面一定要接動名詞（V-ing）當受詞，這是固定的動詞用法，所以選 listening to。to listen to、listen to、listens to 都不符合 enjoy 的文法規則。", "keyPoint": "enjoy + V-ing", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-5", "year": 114, "no": 5, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Dad is busy cooking in the kitchen. Dinner will be ___ in ten minutes.", "options": {"A": "free", "B": "full", "C": "medium", "D": "ready"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "爸爸在廚房忙著煮飯，句意是「晚餐再十分鐘就會___好」，英文中「飯做好了」的固定講法是 dinner is ready，所以選 ready。free（空閒的）、full（飽的/滿的）、medium（中等的）都不符合這個情境。", "keyPoint": "固定搭配 dinner is ready", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-6", "year": 114, "no": 6, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "There are so many new ___ in the office. It’ll take me some time to remember who is who.", "options": {"A": "faces", "B": "ideas", "C": "rules", "D": "tools"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是辦公室裡有很多新來的人，要花時間記住「誰是誰」，英文用 new faces（新面孔）表示新同事，這是常見的說法。ideas、rules、tools 都跟「記住是誰」的情境不符。", "keyPoint": "new faces（新面孔）片語", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-7", "year": 114, "no": 7, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "I feel like a ___ . I was looking for my keys for hours but they have been in my pocket the whole time.", "options": {"A": "fool", "B": "ghost", "C": "king", "D": "stranger"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "情境是找鑰匙找了好幾個小時，結果鑰匙一直都在自己口袋裡，這種糗態最適合用 feel like a fool（覺得自己像個傻瓜）來形容。ghost（鬼）、king（國王）、stranger（陌生人）都跟「烏龍、糗」的感覺搭不起來。", "keyPoint": "feel like a fool 表達糗態", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-8", "year": 114, "no": 8, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Mr. and Mrs. Wu have three daughters. Two are in high school, and ___ is in elementary school.", "options": {"A": "each", "B": "the other", "C": "the one", "D": "the next"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句子提到三個女兒中「兩個」讀高中，剩下「一個」讀國小；當總數確定、講完前面剩最後一個時，英文要用 the other（單數，特定剩下的那個），所以選 B。each 是指每一個都、the one／the next 不符合這個「兩個＋剩下一個」的文法搭配。", "keyPoint": "two...the other（兩者中的另一個）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-9", "year": 114, "no": 9, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "It is hard for trees to ___ along this beach because of the strong winds from the sea.", "options": {"A": "blow", "B": "build", "C": "follow", "D": "grow"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是海邊風太大，樹很難「長」得起來，所以選 grow（生長）。blow（吹）、build（建造）、follow（跟隨）都不符合「樹」在這個情境下該做的動作。", "keyPoint": "情境選字：grow（生長）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-10", "year": 114, "no": 10, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Christmas ___ and I want to visit my aunt abroad. Do you have any plans yet?", "options": {"A": "came", "B": "comes", "C": "is coming", "D": "was coming"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "耶誕節「即將到來」用現在進行式表示不久後會發生的事，是常見用法，所以選 is coming。came、comes、was coming在時態上都不符合「未來即將發生」的語意。", "keyPoint": "現在進行式表未來", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-11", "year": 114, "no": 11, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Jo won’t be happy if you’re late for his party tonight, so ___ sure that you arrive on time.", "options": {"A": "make", "B": "makes", "C": "to make", "D": "is making"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "so 後面接的是祈使句（命令句），要用原形動詞開頭，所以選 make（make sure that...確定...）。makes、to make、is making都不是祈使句該用的形式。", "keyPoint": "祈使句用原形動詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-12", "year": 114, "no": 12, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "You may have a long drive because of the terrible ___ . There are usually a lot of cars and buses during this time.", "options": {"A": "experience", "B": "machine", "C": "service", "D": "traffic"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面一句 There are usually a lot of cars and buses during this time 就是在解釋為什麼開車要開很久，答案就是「交通（traffic）」不好、塞車。experience、machine、service都跟「很多車」沒有關聯。", "keyPoint": "上下文推字彙：traffic", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-13", "year": 114, "no": 13, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "In the future, there will ___ be greater basketball players than Stephen Curry, but now we believe he is the best!", "options": {"A": "again", "B": "already", "C": "never", "D": "perhaps"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "正解 perhaps（也許）。句子用「but now（但現在）」做轉折：也許未來會有更強的球員，「但現在」他最強——perhaps 保留了「未來或許有更強者」的可能，才和 but now 形成對比。若填 never，等於說未來絕不會有更強的，but 的轉折就不成立。", "keyPoint": "perhaps 也許（呼應 but now 的轉折）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-14", "year": 114, "no": 14, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "I guess the rainwater has come in from the kitchen. See? ___ of the windows are closed except the one in the kitchen.", "options": {"A": "All", "B": "Both", "C": "Most", "D": "Some"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句型是「___ of the windows are closed except the one in the kitchen」，意思是「除了廚房那扇，其他窗戶全部都關著」，用 All ... except 表示「全部...除了」，所以選 All。Both（兩者都）、Most（大部分）、Some（一些）都無法表達「除了一個之外全部」的完整語意。", "keyPoint": "All...except 全部除了", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-15", "year": 114, "no": 15, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "___ machines have been used to pick fruits for a long time, they were not used on strawberry farms until several years ago.", "options": {"A": "Although", "B": "Because", "C": "Before", "D": "If"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前半句說機器已經用來採水果很久了，後半句卻說直到幾年前才被用在草莓農場，前後語意是「轉折、對比」，要用 Although（雖然）連接讓步子句。Because（因為）、Before（在...之前）、If（如果）都無法表達這種「雖然...但是...」的對比關係。", "keyPoint": "雖然...但是 Although 表讓步", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-16", "year": 114, "no": 16, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "There are online videos that teach you exercises you can do at home. They’ll ___ you a trip to the gym, and some money too.", "options": {"A": "cost", "B": "give", "C": "keep", "D": "save"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是線上運動教學影片能幫你「省下」跑健身房的一趟路，也能省錢，save sb something是「幫某人省下...」的固定用法，所以選 D save。cost是花費（相反意思）、give、keep都不符合「省錢省時間」的語意。", "keyPoint": "save sb sth 省下...", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-17", "year": 114, "no": 17, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Jane’s parents are always happy to see their grandchildren, but mine ___ less so when I visit them with my kids.", "options": {"A": "is", "B": "are", "C": "do", "D": "does"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "mine在這裡代替的是「my parents（我的爸媽）」，是複數，所以動詞要用複數的 are。is、do、does在文法或主詞一致性上都不符合。", "keyPoint": "代名詞 mine 指代複數名詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-18", "year": 114, "no": 18, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Before she ___ about it, you should tell Daphne you broke her favorite cup.", "options": {"A": "asks", "B": "asked", "C": "was asking", "D": "will ask"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "Before引導的是表示未來的時間副詞子句，英文文法規則是「時間/條件子句用現在式代替未來式」，所以要用 asks（現在式）而不是 will ask。asked、was asking在時態上都不對。", "keyPoint": "時間子句用現在式代未來", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-19", "year": 114, "no": 19, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "It was very windy this morning. Some of the shirts on the balcony were blown away ___ in the pond.", "options": {"A": "fell", "B": "and fell", "C": "fallen", "D": "and fallen"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句子是「衣服被風吹走了，而且掉到池塘裡」，were blown away 和「掉落」這兩個動作要用對等連接詞 and 連接，且時態要一致用過去式 fell，所以選 and fell。單獨 fell缺少連接詞、fallen／and fallen是過去分詞，時態不對。", "keyPoint": "對等連接詞 and 連接相同時態動詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-20", "year": 114, "no": 20, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What happened to Rex?", "options": {"A": "He got lost.", "B": "He got hurt.", "C": "He bit people.", "D": "He ate too much."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "114-P1", "explain": "文中說 Rex was hit by a car last night（昨晚被車撞），所以牠是受傷了（got hurt）。文章沒有提到牠走失、咬人或吃太多，所以答案是 B。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：找出事件原因", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-21", "year": 114, "no": 21, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "How did the writer help Rex?", "options": {"A": "By calling the police.", "B": "By making him exercise.", "C": "By taking him to see a doctor.", "D": "By looking for a new home for him."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "114-P1", "explain": "文中提到大家「decided to take him for a walk every evening」，因為運動（exercise）讓Rex變得更健康強壯，所以作者一行人幫助Rex的方式是「讓牠運動」，答案是B。文章沒提到報警或找新家。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：因為運動而康復", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-22", "year": 114, "no": 22, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What do we know about Mark from the dialogue?", "options": {"A": "He made Linda unhappy.", "B": "He is looking for a new job.", "C": "He did not like Linda’s cake.", "D": "He is getting married to Jenny."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "114-P2", "explain": "本題原始對話框內容因掃描檔案關係遺失，但依官方公告的正解，答案是 Mark讓Linda不開心（He made Linda unhappy），代表對話中Mark做的某件事讓Linda感到不高興，需要搭配原始對話框圖片才能完整理解情境。", "keyPoint": "對話推論題（需配合原圖對話框）", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-23", "year": 114, "no": 23, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "Which is most likely an example of stealing someone's thunder?", "options": {"A": "Dennis never changes his mind except when his wife tells him to.", "B": "Melisa tells Tom she’ll go to the party but tells her mom she’ll stay home.", "C": "Jeff tells everyone he’ll move abroad when Ivy is still telling them about her baby.", "D": "Alisa says she doesn’t care what we have for lunch but also doesn’t like the restaurant we chose."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P2", "explain": "「steal someone's thunder」是英文慣用語，意思是「搶走別人本來該有的關注、風頭」。選項C中Ivy正在跟大家分享懷孕消息，這時候Jeff卻插話說自己要出國，等於搶走了Ivy原本該有的注意力，最符合這個片語的意思。其他選項都只是單純意見不合或改變心意，跟「搶風頭」無關。", "keyPoint": "片語 steal someone's thunder（搶風頭）", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-24", "year": 114, "no": 24, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What can you do with a White Lake City Card?", "options": {"A": "Save 20% on children’s train tickets.", "B": "Visit any public museum in the city for free.", "C": "Take a train to places out of the three zones.", "D": "Move around the city by metro as much as you want."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "114-P3", "explain": "文中明確寫 you can visit the city by metro, bus, or train as many times as you want，意思是持卡可以無限次搭乘地鐵、公車、火車，跟選項D「可以用地鐵盡量移動」相符。A、C都超出卡片能用的免費/範圍規定，B則是只有八折優惠而非免費。", "keyPoint": "圖表細節判讀：無限次搭乘", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-25", "year": 114, "no": 25, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Stacy is going to White Lake City and is staying at a hotel near the White Lake Main Station. She wants to visit the Museum of White Lake City History on Friday and see White Lake on Saturday. If she plans to buy (a) White Lake City Card(s), which of the four choices will be best for her and cost her the least?", "options": {"A": "A 3-day Card for Zone 1.", "B": "A Weekend Card for Zones 1-3.", "C": "A 1-day Card for Zone 1 and a Weekend Card for Zones 1-2.", "D": "A 1-day Card for Zones 1-2 and a Weekend Card for Zones 1-2."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P3", "explain": "Stacy住在White Lake Main Station附近（屬Zone 1），週五要去歷史博物館（也在Zone 1，屬平日行程用1-day/3-day/5-day卡），週六要去White Lake（在Zone 2，屬週末用Weekend卡）。所以只需要「Zone 1的1-day卡（$20）」加上「Zones 1-2的Weekend卡（$50）」，總共$70，是四個選項中最便宜又足夠涵蓋需求的組合，答案是C。其他選項不是買太貴的天數/範圍，就是買不到需要的區域。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀＋費用計算", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-26", "year": 114, "no": 26, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What is Rolling Acres?", "options": {"A": "A zoo.", "B": "A campground.", "C": "A vacation farm.", "D": "A family restaurant."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P4", "explain": "文中說 Rolling Acres...has become a popular place for families to go on vacation，加上有水果、蔬菜園、餵動物等活動，是個「度假農場」，答案是C。不是zoo（動物園）、campground（露營地）或餐廳。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：農場的性質", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-27", "year": 114, "no": 27, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What do we learn from the first paragraph?", "options": {"A": "What Libby does at Rolling Acres.", "B": "What visitors think of Rolling Acres.", "C": "Why Libby’s grandparents started Rolling Acres.", "D": "What the Larson family’s plans are for Rolling Acres."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "114-P4", "explain": "第一段主要在描述Libby每天幾點起床、做哪些工作（拖地、拿信、招呼遊客、教小孩餵羊等），內容都是「Libby做的事」，所以答案是A。段落並沒有講遊客的想法或祖父母創業的原因。", "keyPoint": "段落主旨判斷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-28", "year": 114, "no": 28, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does making sacrifices mean?", "options": {"A": "Learning to make money and use it wisely.", "B": "Getting to know different sides of your family.", "C": "Making excuses for failing to do something difficult.", "D": "Giving up something important to do something else."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "114-P4", "explain": "文中提到Libby想睡到中午、想跟朋友出去玩卻做不到，這種「為了工作而放棄自己想做的事」正是making sacrifices（做出犧牲）的意思，答案是D，即「放棄重要的事去做別的事」。其他選項都偏離了「犧牲、放棄」這個核心意思。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：make sacrifices", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-29", "year": 114, "no": 29, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What do the comics tell us?", "options": {"A": "Enjoy life while we can.", "B": "Follow the old ways of life.", "C": "Save our planet before it’s too late.", "D": "Treat others the way we want to be treated."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P5", "explain": "漫畫用復活節島因為過度砍樹導致缺水、缺糧、甚至滅亡的故事，最後一句 Let's not make Earth...another Easter Island 直接點出主旨：要趁還來得及好好珍惜、保護地球資源，答案是C。", "keyPoint": "漫畫主旨：珍惜地球資源", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-30", "year": 114, "no": 30, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What can we learn about the people in the comics?", "options": {"A": "They made fire before starting a fight.", "B": "They fought for land and plants all the time.", "C": "They prayed to the statues beside a large fire.", "D": "They used statues to show how strong they were."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "114-P5", "explain": "文中提到人們搬雕像到打鬥的地方是為了 show their power（展現力量），符合選項D「用雕像展示他們有多強」。他們並非先生火才打架，也不是一直為土地植物打架（是缺水缺糧才開始），也沒有向雕像祈禱。", "keyPoint": "漫畫細節推論：雕像象徵力量", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-31", "year": 114, "no": 31, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "What does did it in Picture 7 mean?", "options": {"A": "Fall to the ground.", "B": "Cut down the last trees.", "C": "Move the statues to fighting grounds.", "D": "Understand how important trees were."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "114-P5", "explain": "did it 指的是前一句提到的動作「cut down the last trees（砍下最後的樹）」，也就是文中說「那些砍下最後一棵樹的人，明明知道樹有多重要，卻還是做了（did it）」，答案是B。", "keyPoint": "代名詞指代：did it 指砍樹這件事", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-32", "year": 114, "no": 32, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What did Ariely try to find out in the origami study?", "options": {"A": "If he could stop the IKEA effect.", "B": "Why people love making origami.", "C": "Why IKEA furniture is so famous.", "D": "If anyone shared his IKEA experience."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "114-P6", "explain": "文中說 Ariely wanted to know if anyone shared his feelings，也就是想知道「是不是其他人也有他那種對親手做的東西特別有感情」的經驗，所以做了摺紙實驗，答案是D。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：研究動機", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-33", "year": 114, "no": 33, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Which is true about the origami study?", "options": {"A": "Buyers would spend less on builders’ origami than builders would.", "B": "Builders and buyers needed to decide a price on the origami they made.", "C": "Builders knew others would not pay as much for the origami as they would.", "D": "Buyers would spend more on builders’ origami after knowing how they were made."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "114-P6", "explain": "文中提到 buyers would pay only five cents...builders would spend 25 cents，也就是買家願意付的錢（5分）比做的人自己願意付的錢（25分）少很多，符合選項A「buyers付得比builders少」。B錯在只有builders要定價，buyers是被問願付多少而非定價；C、D也與原文不符。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：實驗結果數字", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-34", "year": 114, "no": 34, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Jerry just can’t get his daughter Mia to eat more vegetables at dinner. Every time he tries to do so, there is always a lot of shouting and crying. If Jerry wants to have Mia eat more vegetables by using the IKEA effect, what should he do?", "options": {"A": "Tell Mia that he cooks the vegetables just for her.", "B": "Ask Mia to help him cook vegetables for her meal.", "C": "Give Mia her favorite candy after she eats vegetables.", "D": "Ask Mia what vegetables she likes and cook them for her."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "114-P6", "explain": "IKEA效應的重點是「親手參與製作，會讓人更珍惜、更喜歡那個成果」，所以若想讓Mia更願意吃蔬菜，就要讓她「親自參與煮」，答案是B（請Mia幫忙一起煮菜）。其他選項像用糖果獎勵、問她喜好、說是特別為她煮的，都不是靠「親手製作」來提升價值感。", "keyPoint": "應用IKEA效應到新情境", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-35", "year": 114, "no": 35, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What is the reading mainly about?", "options": {"A": "The tips on using a picture to tell a story.", "B": "The change that electricity brought to people’s lives.", "C": "The history behind the picture of a UK electricity worker.", "D": "The story of a famous UK electricity worker from the 1970s."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P7", "explain": "整篇文章從一張1970年代英國電力工人的照片講起，說明這張照片背後1972、1973年兩次罷工加薪的歷史故事，所以主旨是「這張照片背後的歷史」，答案是C，而不是單純講電力如何改變生活或某位工人的個人故事。", "keyPoint": "文章主旨題", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R114-36", "year": 114, "no": 36, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "In the UK in the 1970s, what did people most likely think of the UK electricity workers?", "options": {"A": "They were not brave enough to fix their problems.", "B": "They worked like robots and never learned to change.", "C": "They were asking too much and did not know when to stop.", "D": "They did not care whether their job might hurt people’s health."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P7", "explain": "從文中限電規定造成人民生活困擾（沒暖氣、醫院用蠟燭、工廠停工、很多人失業）卻電力工人仍持續施壓要加薪，可以推論當時民眾覺得電力工人「要求太多、不知道適可而止」，答案是C。", "keyPoint": "推論當時民眾觀感", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-37", "year": 114, "no": 37, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "Why does the writer put the “ ” mark around the word dark in the last sentence?", "options": {"A": "To say that the “dark” time was actually not dark.", "B": "To tell people that the word was said by the government.", "C": "To mean both the days without lights and the difficult lives people lived.", "D": "To show that the government and the electricity workers both lost their fights."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P7", "explain": "文末的「dark」加上引號，一語雙關：一方面照字面指「沒有電、沒有燈的黑暗」，一方面也暗指人民那段生活困難、痛苦的「黑暗時期」，所以答案是C，兩種意思都包含。", "keyPoint": "引號的雙關字義猜測", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-38", "year": 114, "no": 38, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "第38題：選出最適合填入文中 ___38___ 處的答案。", "options": {"A": "starts", "B": "started", "C": "has started", "D": "will start"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "114-P8", "explain": "此句描述的是Cameron「從國一那年開始」做這件事，是描述過去已發生並持續至今的習慣起點，用過去式 started 最符合後面 That year...的敘述方式，答案是B。", "keyPoint": "綜合填空：過去式描述習慣起點", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-39", "year": 114, "no": 39, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "第39題：選出最適合填入文中 ___39___ 處的答案。", "options": {"A": "he got quite scared of two things", "B": "he still couldn’t understand two things", "C": "he couldn’t stop thinking about two things", "D": "he did two things that would change his life"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P8", "explain": "空格後面接著他心裡想的兩件事（媽媽生小孩多勇敢、自己絕對不用經歷這種事），這是「下課後他一直想著」這兩件事，用 couldn't stop thinking about（一直想著）最符合，答案是C。", "keyPoint": "綜合填空：情節銜接", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-40", "year": 114, "no": 40, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "第40題：選出最適合填入文中 ___40___ 處的答案。", "options": {"A": "should be spent helping his mom", "B": "should be a time of welcoming a new start", "C": "should not be about him, but about his mom", "D": "should not be celebrated for just one day, but for nine months"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "114-P8", "explain": "後面說明他覺得自己在媽媽肚子裡九個月只是吃睡，媽媽卻辛苦做所有事，所以他認為生日「不該只跟自己有關，而該是關於媽媽」，答案是C should not be about him, but about his mom。", "keyPoint": "綜合填空：呼應段落主旨", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-41", "year": 114, "no": 41, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "第41題：選出最適合填入文中 ___41___ 處的答案。", "options": {"A": "first", "B": "last", "C": "only", "D": "other"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "114-P8", "explain": "這是Cameron開始做這件事後「第一個」準備的生日禮物（一包他自己烤的餅乾），後文接著描述之後每年都會做禮物，所以這裡指的是「最初、第一個」，答案是A first。", "keyPoint": "綜合填空：first 表第一次", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-42", "year": 114, "no": 42, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "第42題：選出最適合填入文中 ___42___ 處的答案。", "options": {"A": "made his head hurt", "B": "made his heart sing", "C": "made him change his mind", "D": "made him give up baking"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "114-P8", "explain": "媽媽說那是她吃過最好吃的東西，聽到這句話讓Cameron覺得很感動、很開心，比收到禮物還好，所以答案是B made his heart sing（讓他心花怒放/很感動開心）。", "keyPoint": "綜合填空：情緒描寫片語", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R114-43", "year": 114, "no": 43, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "第43題：選出最適合填入文中 ___43___ 處的答案。", "options": {"A": "is going to give", "B": "gives", "C": "has given", "D": "gave"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "114-P8", "explain": "文中說「今年」他打算做一件洋裝給媽媽（表示計畫、尚未完成的未來動作），且後文提到「Now the dress is finished」表示現在已完成，所以填入的應該是描述「打算要做」的未來式 is going to give，答案是A。", "keyPoint": "綜合填空：be going to 表計畫", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-1", "year": 113, "no": 1, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Look at the picture. There is 　　　 under the door.", "options": {"A": "an envelope", "B": "a plant", "C": "a sign", "D": "an umbrella"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "這題要看原卷的圖片才能作答，圖中門下有一封信（envelope）。plant（植物）、sign（標誌）、umbrella（雨傘）都不符合圖片內容。", "keyPoint": "看圖選字彙", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R113-2", "year": 113, "no": 2, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "My 　　　 hurts so much that I cannot even turn my head.", "options": {"A": "arm", "B": "knee", "C": "neck", "D": "stomach"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "關鍵線索是後半句 cannot even turn my head（連轉頭都不行），表示痛的地方一定跟頭部相連，所以是脖子（neck）。arm手臂、knee膝蓋、stomach胃都跟轉頭無關。", "keyPoint": "身體部位字彙 neck", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-3", "year": 113, "no": 3, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Our school basketball team won the national game last night. We are so 　　　 them.", "options": {"A": "popular with", "B": "proud of", "C": "sorry for", "D": "worried about"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "球隊贏得全國冠軍是件光榮的事，所以是「以他們為榮」be proud of。popular with(受歡迎)、sorry for(同情)、worried about(擔心)都不合邏輯，因為前面是好消息(won)。", "keyPoint": "be proud of 為某人感到驕傲", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-4", "year": 113, "no": 4, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Tomorrow is Sam's last day in the office. Nobody knows why he decided to 　　　 .", "options": {"A": "hide", "B": "leave", "C": "pack", "D": "walk"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「明天是Sam在辦公室的最後一天」表示他要離職了，所以填 leave（離開）。hide躲藏、pack打包（雖然離職常會打包但不是動詞核心語意）、walk走路都不符合「最後一天」這個線索。", "keyPoint": "情境推斷字義 leave", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-5", "year": 113, "no": 5, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "It's not a good idea to go mountain climbing in this bad 　　　 . We should wait until the typhoon goes away.", "options": {"A": "chance", "B": "dream", "C": "habit", "D": "weather"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面一句提到颱風（typhoon），表示前面說的是天氣不好，所以填 weather。chance機會、dream夢、habit習慣都跟颱風無關。", "keyPoint": "颱風→weather 天氣字彙", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-6", "year": 113, "no": 6, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Chris loves walking with Anna on snowy days, but Anna hates 　　　 very much.", "options": {"A": "them", "B": "so", "C": "one", "D": "it"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "正解 D(it)。這裡的 it 代替前面「walking with Anna on snowy days（在雪天和Anna散步這件事）」整個活動／情境——指代「一整件事情」時用單數 it。them 要指複數的具體東西、one 指同類中的另一個、so 用法不同，都不合。", "keyPoint": "代名詞 it（指代整件事）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-7", "year": 113, "no": 7, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Lora likes to eat bananas that are already a little brown on the outside, and so 　　　 I.", "options": {"A": "am", "B": "do", "C": "have", "D": "will"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前面用一般現在式 likes（第三人稱）表達習慣，所以附和句「so 　 I」要用助動詞 do 代替 like，變成 so do I（我也是）。am/have/will 都跟前面的一般現在式動詞不一致。", "keyPoint": "so + 助動詞 + 主詞（附和句）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-8", "year": 113, "no": 8, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Your refrigerator shouldn't be making loud noises now, but if it 　　　 does, just give me a call and I'll come check it again.", "options": {"A": "already", "B": "even", "C": "finally", "D": "still"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「冰箱現在不該有噪音，但如果它『仍然』有噪音…」，still 表示「（狀況不該持續卻）仍舊」最符合語意。already已經、even甚至、finally終於都不合邏輯。", "keyPoint": "still 表示狀況持續", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-9", "year": 113, "no": 9, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "After winning money in the card game, Jay decided to try again. He felt that he might also be 　　　 a second time.", "options": {"A": "famous", "B": "interested", "C": "lucky", "D": "ready"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "第一次玩牌贏了錢，所以他覺得自己「可能也會走運（lucky）」再贏一次。famous出名、interested感興趣、ready準備好，都跟贏錢的運氣無關。", "keyPoint": "情境語意 lucky", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-10", "year": 113, "no": 10, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "The knife doesn't cut very well. It's not as 　　　 as before.", "options": {"A": "bright", "B": "heavy", "C": "quick", "D": "sharp"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「刀子切不好，不像以前一樣」表示刀刃不夠鋒利，所以填 sharp（鋒利的）。bright明亮、heavy重、quick快都不是形容刀子鋒利度的字。", "keyPoint": "sharp 形容刀具鋒利", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-11", "year": 113, "no": 11, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "John will stay with his sister until he 　　　 an apartment.", "options": {"A": "will find", "B": "would find", "C": "finds", "D": "found"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "until 引導的時間副詞子句，即使講未來的事，也要用現在式代替未來式，所以選 finds（第三人稱單數現在式）。will find/would find是未來式或條件式，found是過去式，都不對。", "keyPoint": "時間副詞子句：未來用現在式代替", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-12", "year": 113, "no": 12, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Students 　　　 to go on the school trip should ask their parents first.", "options": {"A": "who want", "B": "want", "C": "who they want", "D": "what they want"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "空格要修飾 Students（學生），用關係代名詞 who 引導形容詞子句 who want to go on the school trip（想去校外教學的學生）。want少了主詞、who they want/what they want 句構不合文法。", "keyPoint": "關係代名詞 who 引導形容詞子句", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-13", "year": 113, "no": 13, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "The temple sits alone in the mountains at a height of 3,000m 　　　 sea level.", "options": {"A": "above", "B": "at", "C": "below", "D": "in"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「海拔3000公尺」的英文是 3,000m above sea level，above表示「在…之上」，是固定用法。below（在下方）、at/in不符合「海拔」的固定搭配。", "keyPoint": "above sea level 海拔固定用法", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-14", "year": 113, "no": 14, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Patty spent several days planning to invite Charlie to dinner, 　　　 she couldn't say a word when they met.", "options": {"A": "but", "B": "if", "C": "or", "D": "so"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前面「花好幾天計畫要邀請Charlie吃飯」跟後面「見面時卻說不出話」意思相反，要用轉折連接詞 but。if如果、or或者、so所以都不能表達語意上的轉折對比。", "keyPoint": "but 表示語意轉折", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-15", "year": 113, "no": 15, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "I can't tell you what I think of the movie because I 　　　 it. I'll probably watch it this Saturday.", "options": {"A": "am not seeing", "B": "don't see", "C": "haven't seen", "D": "won't see"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面說「這禮拜六大概會去看」，表示到現在為止都還沒看過這部電影，用現在完成式 haven't seen 最能表達「到目前為止的經驗」。am not seeing/don't see是現在式、won't see是未來式，都不符合「還沒看過」的語意。", "keyPoint": "現在完成式：到目前為止「還沒」…（haven't + p.p.）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-16", "year": 113, "no": 16, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "The new guy at the help desk answers calls like a 　　　 . There are no ups and downs in his voice and you can't tell if he is happy or sad.", "options": {"A": "father", "B": "foreigner", "C": "radio", "D": "robot"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「聲音沒有高低起伏，聽不出喜怒哀樂」是在形容像機器人一樣呆板單調地說話，所以選 robot。father父親、foreigner外國人、radio收音機都不符合「沒有情緒起伏」的比喻。", "keyPoint": "比喻語意：像機器人一樣（robot）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-17", "year": 113, "no": 17, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Jasmine planned to spend her summer in the country, but right after she got there, she started to 　　　 the noise in the city.", "options": {"A": "enjoy", "B": "mind", "C": "miss", "D": "notice"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "Jasmine計畫到鄉下過暑假，但一到那裡就開始想念城市的吵鬧聲，表示她其實習慣了城市生活，所以選 miss（想念）。enjoy享受、mind介意、notice注意到都不符合這種「反而想念」的轉折語意。", "keyPoint": "miss 表示想念", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-18", "year": 113, "no": 18, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "\"Bad traffic\" is perhaps the 　　　 excuse for being late when your boss knows it only takes you five minutes to walk to work.", "options": {"A": "easiest", "B": "oldest", "C": "smartest", "D": "worst"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "走路只要五分鐘卻遲到，還用「塞車」當藉口，是最糟糕、最爛的藉口，所以選 worst（最差的）。easiest最簡單、oldest最舊、smartest最聰明都不符合這種諷刺語氣。", "keyPoint": "worst excuse 最爛的藉口", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-19", "year": 113, "no": 19, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "The housework in Mr. and Mrs. Wang's family 　　　 between them and their kids. Everyone's got their own job to do.", "options": {"A": "is shared", "B": "are shared", "C": "shares", "D": "share"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "housework（家事）是單數不可數名詞，且家事「被」分攤，所以用被動語態 is shared。are shared主詞單複數不對，shares/share是主動語態，跟「家事被分擔」的被動語意不符。", "keyPoint": "被動語態 + 單數主詞一致", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-20", "year": 113, "no": 20, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "I want to find another dentist because 　　　 pulled out a good tooth last time I went to him.", "options": {"A": "I", "B": "me", "C": "mine", "D": "myself"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「我的牙醫（mine＝my dentist）上次幫我拔錯了一顆好牙」，mine 是所有格代名詞，代替 my dentist，避免重複。I/me是主格受格、myself是反身代名詞，都不符合這裡「代替所有格名詞」的用法。", "keyPoint": "所有格代名詞 mine", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-21", "year": 113, "no": 21, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Mom: Linda, you've been playing computer games all evening! Have you finished your report?\nLinda: Well, 　　　 most of it this afternoon, and I'll finish it by Friday.", "options": {"A": "I would do", "B": "I did", "C": "I was doing", "D": "I'll do"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "Linda說她「今天下午已經做了大部分」，是描述過去已完成的動作，用過去式 I did。I would do/I'll do是未來或條件語氣、I was doing是過去進行式強調過程，都跟「已經做完大部分」的語意不符。", "keyPoint": "過去式表示已完成的動作", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-22", "year": 113, "no": 22, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why did Philip go out?", "options": {"A": "To meet a woman.", "B": "To look for his father.", "C": "To ask the police for help.", "D": "To buy food for his brother."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "113-P1", "explain": "文章第一段說 Jason 肚子餓一直哭，Philip不會煮飯，所以帶 Jason 出去買食物（take Jason out for some food），對應答案D。他不是要去見女人、找爸爸或找警察幫忙。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：外出原因", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-23", "year": 113, "no": 23, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why was Philip's father angry?", "options": {"A": "He forgot his keys.", "B": "The woman was hiding from him.", "C": "The police didn't believe what he said.", "D": "Philip and his brother went out at night."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "113-P1", "explain": "文中爸爸生氣地喊「我只是要進自己的家！」，但警察一直不相信他（didn't believe him），直到Philip跑來解釋才澄清，所以爸爸生氣是因為警察不相信他的話。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：生氣的原因", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-24", "year": 113, "no": 24, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Kevin is going to buy some fresh bread at Baker's Kitchen. He loves white bread, his mom likes farm bread, his father enjoys bagels, and his sister eats only challah. Which is the earliest possible time for him to get all these breads for his family?", "options": {"A": "11:00am.", "B": "4:00pm.", "C": "5:00pm.", "D": "7:00pm."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "113-P2", "explain": "這題要對照麵包店的圖表時刻表，找出白麵包、農場麵包、貝果、猶太辮子麵包四種麵包全部都已出爐、最早可以同時買齊的時間點，答案是下午5點。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：交集時間", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R113-25", "year": 113, "no": 25, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What do we know about Baker's Kitchen?", "options": {"A": "It is open five days a week.", "B": "Its breads are half price one hour before closing.", "C": "Its croissants and pretzels are sold on weekends.", "D": "Its members can save $100 when they shop on Fridays."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P2", "explain": "要看圖表中的說明文字，圖表標示打烊前一小時麵包會半價出售，符合選項B。其餘關於營業天數、可頌貝果只在週末賣、會員省$100等描述都與圖表資訊不符。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：細節資訊", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R113-26", "year": 113, "no": 26, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What is recommended to people who want to visit the festival?", "options": {"A": "Using the free festival bus service.", "B": "Visiting the festival on the weekend.", "C": "Entering Satyr's Park from Fox Street.", "D": "Parking in Garden Square and walking to the festival."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "113-P3", "explain": "要看地圖上的建議說明文字（recommend），地圖建議遊客搭乘免費的音樂季接駁公車前往會場，其餘選項（週末去、走某條街進公園、停車在某廣場走路過去）都不是地圖上建議的做法。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：地圖建議", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R113-27", "year": 113, "no": 27, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What can we learn about the farmers' market from the map?", "options": {"A": "The farmers' market is next to the flower market.", "B": "The farmers' market and the festival are on the same block.", "C": "You can go to the farmers' market by taking Bus No. 157 to Puppy Street.", "D": "The nearest metro station to the farmers' market is the Koala Street Station."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "113-P3", "explain": "要對照地圖上農夫市集的位置，最靠近的捷運站是 Koala Street Station。地圖顯示農夫市集不是緊鄰花卉市集、不在音樂季同一街廓，也不是搭157號公車到Puppy Street可到。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：地圖位置關係", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R113-28", "year": 113, "no": 28, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What kind of people do Yan's and Chang's friends most likely think Yan and Chang are?", "options": {"A": "They enjoy good food.", "B": "They don't like to share.", "C": "They like to make friends.", "D": "They don't like new things."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P4", "explain": "兩個故事裡，Yan只準備一小盤魚、Chang說食物不夠不留客人吃飯，朋友都用反諷的方式（借燈、要殺馬）暗示主人小氣。所以朋友心裡覺得他們是「不願意分享」的人。", "keyPoint": "推論主旨：反諷手法看出小氣", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-29", "year": 113, "no": 29, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "What is it in the second story?", "options": {"A": "A big knife.", "B": "The horse.", "C": "Lunch.", "D": "One of Chang's ducks or chickens."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P4", "explain": "第二個故事中朋友說「我在想要不要殺了騎來的那匹馬當午餐」，這裡的 it 指的就是前面提到的「馬」（the horse）。不是刀子、午餐本身或雞鴨，因為it是承接horse這個受詞。", "keyPoint": "指代理解：it 指代 the horse", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-30", "year": 113, "no": 30, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Why does the writer talk about doctors and a health center in the reading?", "options": {"A": "To explain Chen's services.", "B": "To talk about Chen's future plans.", "C": "To explain Chen's love for books.", "D": "To show why bookstores are important."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "113-P5", "explain": "作者把大圖書館、博物館比喻成「醫院」，把陳彥宏的書店比喻成「健康中心」，是為了說明陳彥宏提供的修書服務等級（處理小問題而非大問題），對應選項A。", "keyPoint": "推論寫作目的：譬喻說明服務內容", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-31", "year": 113, "no": 31, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why is Chen Bing-Hong's job important in the example he gave?", "options": {"A": "It allows people to get books as gifts.", "B": "It saves people money on new books.", "C": "It gives people hope to follow their dreams.", "D": "It helps people think of special moments in the past."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "113-P5", "explain": "文中說書的主人拿回修好的書後，感覺自己「被帶回和老師相處的那些日子」（brought back to the days with his teacher），這正是選項D「讓人回想起特別的時刻」。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：修書喚起回憶", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-32", "year": 113, "no": 32, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "What is his magic?", "options": {"A": "Fixing books.", "B": "Making book owners smile.", "C": "Finding books that are long lost.", "D": "Changing his bookstore into a library."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "113-P5", "explain": "文末說「看到書主人的微笑讓陳彥宏開心，因為這樣的笑容就是他的魔法所在」，這裡的「魔法」(magic)指的就是他修書的技藝(fixing books)，讓書恢復完整才引出書主人的笑容。", "keyPoint": "指代理解：his magic = 修書技藝", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-33", "year": 113, "no": 33, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "According to the reading, why did Rohla and Kreytenberg open Habibi & Hawara?", "options": {"A": "To help refugees live better in Austria.", "B": "To collect money to help Syria fight the war.", "C": "To help Austrians learn about the war in Syria.", "D": "To help refugees go back to their home countries."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "113-P6", "explain": "文章說兩人開餐廳是為了「幫助難民在奧地利有更好的新生活」（help them start a new life），不是為了幫敘利亞打仗募款、讓奧地利人了解戰爭，或送難民回國。", "keyPoint": "主旨理解：開店目的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-34", "year": 113, "no": 34, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What can we learn about Habibi & Hawara?", "options": {"A": "It was moved from Syria to Austria.", "B": "It may finally be sold to its workers.", "C": "It has cooking classes in Syrian food.", "D": "It is an important meeting place for Syrians."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P6", "explain": "文中提到 Rohla 和 Kreytenberg 希望「最好的員工最終能買下這間餐廳」（buy the restaurant in the end），也就是餐廳可能會賣給員工，對應選項B。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：未來計畫", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-35", "year": 113, "no": 35, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does it mean when people beg to differ?", "options": {"A": "They do not agree.", "B": "They look different.", "C": "They cannot speak for others.", "D": "They do not notice something."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "113-P6", "explain": "beg to differ 是「恕難苟同、不同意」的固定用語，前文說有些奧地利人擔心難民問題，但兩位老闆「beg to differ」，接著解釋難民不必然是問題，可見他們是「不同意」前面的說法。", "keyPoint": "片語字義猜測 beg to differ = 不同意", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-36", "year": 113, "no": 36, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does it mean when someone is an advocate of something?", "options": {"A": "They talk a lot but do little about it.", "B": "They believe it is good and should be done.", "C": "They have had some bad experiences with it.", "D": "They are one of the first people who have done it."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P7", "explain": "advocate 指「支持者、提倡者」，文中說 Smith 是 an advocate of bringing extinct animals back，後面接著說他認為「我們必須盡全力讓牠們復活」，可見 advocate 是相信這件事該做並支持的人。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測 advocate = 支持提倡者", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-37", "year": 113, "no": 37, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What is special about the extinct frog in Smith's book?", "options": {"A": "It can live in a dirty living space.", "B": "It might help fix a health problem.", "C": "It eats its babies when it cannot find food.", "D": "It is the first extinct animal that people studied."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P7", "explain": "文中提到那隻絕種青蛙在胃裡孵蝌蚪，作者認為研究牠可能可以幫助解決「胎兒在出生前死亡」的健康問題，所以特別之處是牠可能有助於解決一個健康問題。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：青蛙研究的意義", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-38", "year": 113, "no": 38, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Why does Ellen Zimmer use the words from Dr. Solomon Wang?", "options": {"A": "To start a new topic.", "B": "To share a big dream.", "C": "To make her idea clearer.", "D": "To invite people to take action."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "113-P7", "explain": "Ellen在文末引用 Dr. Wang 說的話「throwing good money after bad」（花大錢卻沒有回報），是用專家的話來加強、印證自己前面「花大錢卻沒進展」的質疑，讓自己的論點更清楚有力。", "keyPoint": "推論寫作手法：引用專家佐證論點", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-39", "year": 113, "no": 39, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What does Ellen Zimmer most likely think about bringing back extinct animals?", "options": {"A": "It is possible.", "B": "It is dangerous.", "C": "It is not possible.", "D": "It is not dangerous."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "113-P7", "explain": "Ellen全文都在質疑復活絕種動物的可行性，說「沒人知道牠們真的能不能復活」、花十年千萬美金卻只得到幾顆死掉的蛙蛋，可見她認為這件事「不可能做到」。", "keyPoint": "推論作者立場", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-40", "year": 113, "no": 40, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "40. (fill in the blank) Though it has been a very popular topic this year, social distancing 　　　 .", "options": {"A": "is not a new idea", "B": "has not been very useful", "C": "may bring some problems", "D": "is not welcomed by everyone"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "113-P8", "explain": "空格後面馬上接「事實上，這個做法早在1918年流感大流行時就被廣泛使用」，這句話就是在說明社交距離「不是新概念」，呼應選項A is not a new idea。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：由下文推出上文空格", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-41", "year": 113, "no": 41, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "41. (fill in the blank) From the picture, we can see that 　　　 started social distancing earlier than the other three cities.", "options": {"A": "Portland", "B": "New York", "C": "Denver", "D": "Pittsburgh"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P8", "explain": "這題一定要看圖表中各城市死亡率曲線，找出哪一個城市最早開始社交距離（曲線最早出現下降或平緩），圖表顯示是紐約（New York）最早開始。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：最早開始社交距離的城市", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R113-42", "year": 113, "no": 42, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "42. (fill in the blank) However, both cities 　　　 , and the numbers of deaths climbed again.", "options": {"A": "had higher numbers of deaths", "B": "stopped social distancing too soon", "C": "began social distancing a second time", "D": "had the most days of social distancing"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "113-P8", "explain": "前文說 Portland 和 Denver 前幾週做得不錯，但後來死亡人數又攀升，最合理的原因就是「太早停止社交距離措施」（stopped social distancing too soon），才會導致疫情反彈。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：因果推論", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R113-43", "year": 113, "no": 43, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "43. (fill in the blank) 　　　 , sick people were kept away from healthy ones; schools were closed; public activities were not allowed.", "options": {"A": "Also", "B": "At first", "C": "However", "D": "For example"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "113-P8", "explain": "空格後面列舉了具體做法（隔離病患、關閉學校、禁止公共活動），這些都是「舉例說明」Portland同時使用多種社交距離方法，所以要用 For example（舉例來說）連接。", "keyPoint": "轉承語詞 For example 舉例", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-1", "year": 112, "no": 1, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Look at the picture. The man is holding a ___ of grapes in his hands.", "options": {"A": "bag", "B": "basket", "C": "bowl", "D": "box"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "題目要你看圖，圖中的人手裡拿的葡萄裝在「一籃」裡，英文常說 a basket of grapes（一籃水果）。bag（袋子）、box（盒子）、bowl（碗）都不是圖片中裝葡萄的容器，所以要看圖才能選出正確答案。", "keyPoint": "看圖選字：容器類單字 basket", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-2", "year": 112, "no": 2, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Dennis enjoys ___ in public. He is proud of his beautiful voice.", "options": {"A": "dancing", "B": "drawing", "C": "shopping", "D": "singing"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面一句「proud of his beautiful voice（以自己美妙的歌聲為傲）」是關鍵線索，代表 Dennis 喜歡的是唱歌，所以選 singing。dancing、drawing、shopping 都跟「聲音」無關，不合邏輯。", "keyPoint": "上下文語意連貫：voice → singing", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-3", "year": 112, "no": 3, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Mrs. Johnson can't hear very well. If you need to talk to her, you must ___.", "options": {"A": "explain", "B": "hurry", "C": "listen", "D": "shout"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句子說 Mrs. Johnson「聽不太清楚」，所以跟她說話時要「大聲喊」才聽得到，答案是 shout。explain（解釋）、hurry（趕快）、listen（聽）都不能解決「聽不清楚」這個問題。", "keyPoint": "因果推理：聽力不好 → shout", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-4", "year": 112, "no": 4, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "People got very excited when they watched Ms. Smith ___ at the party.", "options": {"A": "danced", "B": "dancing", "C": "has danced", "D": "to dance"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "watch 是感官動詞，後面接受詞再加 V-ing 表示「看到某人正在做某事的過程」，watch sb doing sth，所以要選 dancing。這是感官動詞＋受詞＋現在分詞的句型，不能用 danced（過去式）、has danced（完成式）或 to dance。", "keyPoint": "感官動詞 watch + O + V-ing", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-5", "year": 112, "no": 5, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "I tried on these shoes in several different ___ , and I thought the white pair looked best on me.", "options": {"A": "colors", "B": "prices", "C": "shapes", "D": "sizes"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後半句「白色那雙看起來最好看」提到的是「顏色」，所以空格要選 colors（顏色）。prices（價錢）、shapes（形狀）、sizes（尺寸）跟「白色」這個線索對不上。", "keyPoint": "關鍵字對應：white → colors", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-6", "year": 112, "no": 6, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Rex did not feel the earthquake this morning. He ___ in the park at the time.", "options": {"A": "jogged", "B": "was jogging", "C": "has jogged", "D": "would jog"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「這個時候」正在慢跑，所以沒感覺到地震，這是過去進行式（was/were + V-ing），表示過去某時間點正在做的動作，選 was jogging。jogged 是單純過去式、has jogged 是完成式、would jog 表示過去習慣，都不符合「當下正在做」的語氣。", "keyPoint": "過去進行式：at the time", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-7", "year": 112, "no": 7, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Mr. Lee has worked in the same store for ten years; he's never thought about ___ his job.", "options": {"A": "changing", "B": "finding", "C": "remembering", "D": "starting"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "think about + V-ing 是固定用法，表示「考慮做某事」。做同一份工作十年，從沒想過「換工作」，所以選 changing。finding、remembering、starting 語意上都講不通。", "keyPoint": "think about + V-ing 片語", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-8", "year": 112, "no": 8, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "I didn't take the bus today because it was ___ . All the seats were taken and a lot of students were standing.", "options": {"A": "dirty", "B": "fast", "C": "full", "D": "wrong"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面說「所有座位都坐滿了，很多學生都站著」，就是在解釋公車「客滿」，所以選 full。dirty（髒）、fast（快）、wrong（不對）都跟「座位坐滿」沒有關係。", "keyPoint": "細節線索：seats taken → full", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-9", "year": 112, "no": 9, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Don't go away when you're cooking, ___ the food might burn.", "options": {"A": "but", "B": "if", "C": "or", "D": "so"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「祈使句 + or + 子句」表示「不然的話…」，意思是「煮東西時不要走開，不然食物會燒焦」，選 or。but 表轉折、if 表條件、so 表結果，都不符合「警告後果」的語氣。", "keyPoint": "祈使句 + or（否則）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-10", "year": 112, "no": 10, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Jerry wanted to know ___ he was kicked off the soccer team, but no one gave him a good reason.", "options": {"A": "where", "B": "when", "C": "whether", "D": "why"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "Jerry 想知道「為什麼」被踢出球隊，但沒人給他好理由，所以選 why，這樣才能跟後面「沒有好理由」呼應。where（哪裡）、when（何時）、whether（是否）都答非所問。", "keyPoint": "疑問詞子句：why 對應理由", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-11", "year": 112, "no": 11, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Jenny is already forty, doesn't have a job and often makes trouble for her parents. To them, she is really a(n) ___ .", "options": {"A": "daughter", "B": "example", "C": "gift", "D": "headache"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "40歲沒工作又常給父母惹麻煩，對父母來說她簡直是個「頭痛人物」，headache 在口語中常用來形容「麻煩人物/事」。daughter（女兒）雖然身分符合但不是形容詞義；example（榜樣）、gift（禮物）都是正面詞，跟前面負面描述矛盾。", "keyPoint": "headache 引申義：麻煩人物", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-12", "year": 112, "no": 12, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Ed and Jill ___ camping this weekend, so they have to finish their homework by Friday.", "options": {"A": "went", "B": "were going", "C": "are going", "D": "have gone"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "be going to / be V-ing 可表示「已經安排好的未來計畫」，這裡用現在進行式 are going 表示這週末要去露營的既定計畫，所以要在星期五前把作業寫完。went 是過去式、were going 是過去式的進行式、have gone 是完成式，時態都不對。", "keyPoint": "現在進行式表示未來計畫", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-13", "year": 112, "no": 13, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Doraemon, a blue Japanese robot cat, has hated mice since his ears ___ by a mouse.", "options": {"A": "bit", "B": "bite", "C": "were bitten", "D": "have bitten"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "耳朵是「被老鼠咬」的，主詞 ears 是被動承受動作的一方，要用被動語態 be動詞 + p.p.，選 were bitten。bit、bite 是主動語態，have bitten 雖是完成式但仍是主動，都不符合「耳朵被咬」的邏輯。", "keyPoint": "被動語態：were bitten by", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-14", "year": 112, "no": 14, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "If we play some interesting games in class, there ___ more fun in learning English.", "options": {"A": "are", "B": "has", "C": "will be", "D": "will have"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "If 引導的條件句是現在式（play），表示未來可能發生的假設，主要子句要用未來式 will be，符合「若條件句用現在式，主要子句用未來式」的句型規則。are、has、will have 在文法或語意上都不對。", "keyPoint": "條件句：If + 現在式, 主要子句 + will", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-15", "year": 112, "no": 15, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "The ___ of this shop was so bad; I never got any answer after I emailed them my questions.", "options": {"A": "item", "B": "business", "C": "price", "D": "service"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "寄信問問題卻都沒有回覆，形容的是這家店的「服務」很差，所以選 service。item（商品）、business（生意）、price（價格）都跟「回信、服務態度」沒有直接關係。", "keyPoint": "語意線索：email 沒回覆 → service", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-16", "year": 112, "no": 16, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "It's not easy to see those islands clearly from here on sunny days, and it's even less ___ to see them on cloudy days.", "options": {"A": "difficult", "B": "lucky", "C": "possible", "D": "special"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "晴天都不容易看清楚島嶼了，陰天當然更「不可能」看清楚，選 possible，並用 less possible 表示「更不可能」。difficult（困難）、lucky（幸運）、special（特別）語意都不通順。", "keyPoint": "less + 形容詞：更不可能", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-17", "year": 112, "no": 17, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Do you remember the CD I was looking for for months? I ___ found it in a small shop. Look, here it is!", "options": {"A": "almost", "B": "even", "C": "finally", "D": "still"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "找了好幾個月的CD，「終於」在小店裡找到了，finally 表示「經過一段時間後終於」，符合語境。almost（幾乎）、even（甚至）、still（仍然）都跟「找了很久終於找到」的語氣不符。", "keyPoint": "副詞語意：finally 終於", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-18", "year": 112, "no": 18, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Business at Jane's shop has not been good these days. And the new supermarket across the street only makes things ___ .", "options": {"A": "easier", "B": "worse", "C": "more boring", "D": "more convenient"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前面說 Jane 的店生意不好，對街新開超市只會讓情況「更糟」，所以選 worse（bad 的比較級）。easier（更容易）、more boring（更無聊）、more convenient（更方便）都不符合「生意不好」這個負面語境。", "keyPoint": "比較級語意：worse 更糟", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-19", "year": 112, "no": 19, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Scott wasn't sure if the young woman before him was ___ pulled him out of a car on fire.", "options": {"A": "who", "B": "the one", "C": "the one she", "D": "the one who"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "the one who + 動詞是常見句型，表示「…的那個人」，這裡指「把他從燃燒的車子裡拉出來的那個人」，who 引導形容詞子句修飾 the one，主格關代不可省略，也不能只留 who 或漏掉 the one。", "keyPoint": "the one who + V（先行詞+主格關代）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-20", "year": 112, "no": 20, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "I ___ swimming for several years before I went to this high school. I gave it up because of heavy schoolwork.", "options": {"A": "have practiced", "B": "am practicing", "C": "practiced", "D": "would practice"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「上高中之前」練習游泳好幾年，後面又說「因為課業重才放棄」，代表這件事在過去已經結束，用簡單過去式 practiced 即可。have practiced 表示動作延續到現在、am practicing 是現在進行式、would practice 表過去習慣但語氣不符，都不對。", "keyPoint": "簡單過去式：已結束的過去動作", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-21", "year": 112, "no": 21, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Frank Kane is so good in the movie that many people ___ he will win the best actor prize.", "options": {"A": "expect", "B": "forget", "C": "notice", "D": "plan"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "演得好，大家「預期/期待」他會得獎，expect 表示「預期、期待」最符合語境。forget（忘記）、notice（注意到）、plan（計畫）都跟「認為他會得獎」的語意不同。", "keyPoint": "字彙語意：expect 預期", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-22", "year": 112, "no": 22, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "The new medicine that just came out on the market ___ thousands of lives.", "options": {"A": "and saved", "B": "has saved", "C": "saving", "D": "to save"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "新藥剛上市，到目前為止已經「救了」好幾千條人命，強調從過去到現在累積的結果，用現在完成式 has saved。and saved 文法不通、saving/to save 都不是完整動詞形式，無法單獨當句子的謂語動詞。", "keyPoint": "現在完成式：強調過去到現在的累積結果", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-23", "year": 112, "no": 23, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Now I often think of those days with Pip, my pet dog. When I read in my room, he ___ quietly beside me.", "options": {"A": "will come and sit", "B": "comes and sits", "C": "has come and sat", "D": "used to come and sit"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「現在常常想起」跟愛犬 Pip 在一起的「那些日子」，代表回憶的是過去已經不再發生的習慣，used to + 原形動詞表示「過去習慣性做的事，現在已不做」，正好符合語境。will come and sit 是未來式、comes and sits 是現在式、has come and sat 是完成式，都不符合「懷念過去」的語氣。", "keyPoint": "used to + V：過去的習慣（現在已不做）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-24", "year": 112, "no": 24, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Amy went to Four Seasons' Kitchen with her mother after she collected 15 stars. They ordered two Garden Sandwiches, an Autumn Wind, and a Winter Snow. After using the stars, how much did they pay for their meals?", "options": {"A": "$290.", "B": "$230.", "C": "$220.", "D": "$160."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P1", "explain": "這題要對照原卷的菜單價目表，把兩份 Garden Sandwich、一份 Autumn Wind、一份 Winter Snow 的價錢加總，再扣掉集滿 15 顆星可折抵的優惠金額，算出實際付款金額為 $230。因為原卷是圖表式價目表，必須看圖才能算出正確總額。", "keyPoint": "圖表金額計算＋集點折抵", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-25", "year": 112, "no": 25, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Amy wants to bring her friends to Four Seasons' Kitchen in August. She looks at her calendar to pick a time to go there. Which are the time and date she can choose?", "options": {"A": "8:30 pm, August 1.", "B": "5:00 pm, August 11.", "C": "3:00 pm, August 13.", "D": "2:00 pm, August 28."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P1", "explain": "這題要看原卷八月的營業月曆圖表，找出餐廳有營業、且時段適合帶朋友一起用餐的日期時間，答案是 8月11日下午5點。其餘選項的日期或時間應該對應到公休日或不合適的營業時段，必須實際看月曆圖才能判斷排除。", "keyPoint": "月曆圖表判讀：找出可行日期時間", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-26", "year": 112, "no": 26, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "According to the notes, which is the WRONG way to help a baby bird that is out of its nest?", "options": {"A": "Feed it before you take it to a hospital.", "B": "Leave it alone if it is not hurt and has feathers.", "C": "Call the animal center if you can't find its nest.", "D": "Put it back in its nest if it is not hurt and has few feathers."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "112-P2", "explain": "告示內容通常會依照幼鳥「有沒有受傷」「羽毛多不多」給不同建議：沒受傷且羽毛長齊就別管它、羽毛少就放回巢裡、找不到巢就打電話給動物中心。而「先餵食再送醫」不在正確處理步驟中，擅自餵食反而可能傷害幼鳥，所以是錯誤做法，答案選 A。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：找出錯誤處理方式", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-27", "year": 112, "no": 27, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "According to the notes, what do birds do if their babies have the smell of people on them?", "options": {"A": "They keep taking care of them.", "B": "They push them out of the nest.", "C": "They clean them until the smell goes away.", "D": "They leave them behind and move to a new nest."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "112-P2", "explain": "告示中提到，很多人誤以為幼鳥一旦沾上人類氣味，親鳥就會棄養牠，但其實親鳥仍然會繼續照顧、餵養幼鳥，不會因為人類的氣味而拋棄牠們，所以答案選 A（繼續照顧牠們），破除一般人常有的迷思。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：破除親鳥棄養迷思", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-28", "year": 112, "no": 28, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "According to the reading, which is one of the reasons for food waste?", "options": {"A": "Stores do not know how to pack food well.", "B": "Farmers do not have enough machines to collect food.", "C": "There is no refrigerator on the truck to keep food fresh.", "D": "Factories do not have enough trucks to carry food to stores."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "112-P3", "explain": "這題要對照原卷的統計圖表，圖表把食物從生產到消費分成五個階段(Stage 1-5)，其中某個階段的浪費原因是「運送途中卡車沒有冷藏設備，導致食物在運送過程中壞掉」，對應到選項 C「卡車上沒有冰箱保鮮」，是圖表文字說明中列出的浪費原因之一。", "keyPoint": "圖表細節：找出食物浪費原因", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-29", "year": 112, "no": 29, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Which is true about food waste at each stage in the three parts of the world?", "options": {"A": "For each area, the highest percentage of food waste happens at Stage 5.", "B": "Europe has a lower percentage of food waste at Stage 3 than the other two areas.", "C": "North America & Oceania has a higher percentage of food waste at Stage 1 than Europe.", "D": "South & Southeast Asia has a higher percentage of food waste at Stage 4 than the other two areas."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "112-P3", "explain": "這題要比較統計圖表中三個地區（歐洲、北美＋大洋洲、南亞＋東南亞）在五個階段的浪費百分比。答案顯示「南亞與東南亞地區在 Stage 4 的浪費百分比，比另外兩個地區都高」，這是圖表中三條資料柱狀圖比較後才能得出的結論，必須實際看圖才能確認數值高低。", "keyPoint": "圖表數據比較：跨地區跨階段判讀", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R112-30", "year": 112, "no": 30, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What is the trick that the mosquito uses in rain?", "options": {"A": "It shakes its body fast enough to get water off.", "B": "It drops with the raindrop and then rolls off it.", "C": "It flies behind the raindrop and pushes it away.", "D": "It rides on the raindrop and lands on the ground."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P4", "explain": "文章第三段清楚寫到，蚊子被雨滴打到後會「被雨滴推著一起往下掉（falls together with it）」，掉了大約6公分後才會「滾離雨滴然後飛走（roll off the raindrop and fly away）」，這正是選項 B 描述的內容，其餘選項都不是文中提到的方法。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：蚊子躲雨的技巧", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-31", "year": 112, "no": 31, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What keeps a mosquito safe in the rain?", "options": {"A": "It is very light.", "B": "It has no body hairs.", "C": "It is as big as a raindrop.", "D": "It is strong enough to fight the force of a raindrop."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "112-P4", "explain": "文章第二段明白指出，蚊子雖然跟雨滴一樣大，但重量只有0.002公克，非常輕，所以被雨滴打到時感受到的力道不足以致命，這就是牠能存活的關鍵，對應選項 A「牠非常輕」。牠其實有毛（選項B錯）、跟雨滴一樣大只是體積不是安全的原因（選項C不是主因）、也不是靠自身力量對抗雨滴（選項D錯）。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：mosquito 輕 → 存活關鍵", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-32", "year": 112, "no": 32, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "When would it be dangerous for a mosquito in the rain?", "options": {"A": "When it flies too close to the ground.", "B": "When the rain falls too hard and too fast.", "C": "When it is hit by raindrops too many times.", "D": "When it drops for more than 6 cm in the rain."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "112-P4", "explain": "文章最後一段說，如果蚊子被雨滴打到時「飛得太低（flies too low）」，就沒有時間滾離雨滴飛走，會直接摔到地上而死，所以答案是 A「飛得太靠近地面時」，這是文中明確提到蚊子會有生命危險的情況，屬於根據文意做出的推論題。", "keyPoint": "推論：flies too low → 有生命危險", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-33", "year": 112, "no": 33, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What do the three stories in the reading all talk about?", "options": {"A": "Who Beethoven's true love was.", "B": "Who played \"For Elise\" the best.", "C": "How \"For Elise\" became popular.", "D": "Why Beethoven wrote \"For Elise.\""}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "112-P5", "explain": "文章一開始就問「Elise是誰」，接著講了三個不同的故事，每個故事雖然主角不同，但都是在解釋「貝多芬當初為什麼要寫這首曲子送給某位女性」，所以三個故事共同的主題是 D「貝多芬為什麼寫這首曲子」，而不是討論誰彈得最好或曲子如何走紅。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：三個故事的共同主題", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-34", "year": 112, "no": 34, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What do we know about \"For Elise\" from the reading?", "options": {"A": "It first appeared in the opera Fidelio.", "B": "The true \"Elise\" was Elise Barensfeld.", "C": "The manuscript was found after Beethoven died.", "D": "The manuscript is now kept by the city of Vienna."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "112-P5", "explain": "文章最後一段提到，這份手稿一直到1867年才被人發現，而這時候已經是貝多芬去世後40年了，所以貝多芬在世時根本沒人知道這首曲子，答案選 C「手稿是在貝多芬過世後才被發現的」，符合文中「40 years after Beethoven's death」這句關鍵線索。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：手稿發現的時間點", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-35", "year": 112, "no": 35, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What can we learn about the three women from the stories?", "options": {"A": "They were called \"Elise\" by their friends.", "B": "Elisabeth Röckel was a close friend of Beethoven's.", "C": "Therese Malfatti changed \"For Elise\" to \"For Therese.\"", "D": "Elise Barensfeld was Beethoven's student."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P5", "explain": "文章第一個故事說 Elisabeth Röckel 曾和貝多芬一起演出歌劇 Fidelio，兩人因此成為「很要好的朋友（very good friends）」，符合選項 B。其他選項則與文章內容不符：她們不是都被朋友稱作Elise、Therese Malfatti並沒有自己把曲名改掉（是後人抄寫手稿時寫錯）、Elise Barensfeld是跟Malfatti學琴，不是貝多芬的學生。", "keyPoint": "推論：三位女性各自的關係細節", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-36", "year": 112, "no": 36, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What idea does the reading talk about?", "options": {"A": "Not all kinds of toys are helpful for children's learning.", "B": "Parents should give their children the right toys for their age.", "C": "Children should learn about their gender from playing with toys.", "D": "We should not let gender decide which toys children can play with."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "112-P6", "explain": "文章從頭到尾都在討論「玩具不該分性別」這個觀念，指出男孩女孩其實不是天生就對特定玩具有興趣，而是「有樣學樣」造成的刻板印象，最後也提到這種觀念可能讓孩子錯失更多學習與生涯機會，整體主旨就是選項 D「不該讓性別決定孩子能玩什麼玩具」。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：反對玩具性別刻板印象", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-37", "year": 112, "no": 37, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "In the third paragraph, why does the writer think \"this rule can be bad for children\"?", "options": {"A": "Children may not want to share their toys with others.", "B": "Children may have the wrong idea about following rules.", "C": "Children may not be able to learn from playing with toys.", "D": "Children may miss the chance to find out what they really like."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "112-P6", "explain": "第三段提到，如果孩子只玩固定一種玩具（例如男生只玩積木、女生只玩娃娃），就會失去嘗試不同玩具、發掘自己真正興趣和專長的機會，這正是選項 D 所說「孩子可能錯失發現自己真正喜歡什麼的機會」，是文章給的核心理由。", "keyPoint": "推論：規則對孩子不好的原因", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-38", "year": 112, "no": 38, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "In the reading, after the writer talks about an idea, he often gives an example to make it clear. Below are four of the sentences in the third paragraph. Which is used as an example?", "options": {"A": "\"However, this rule can be bad for children.\"", "B": "\"Dolls help with their early language use, and building toys are good for learning math and science.\"", "C": "\"Some doctors worry that children may use the same kind of thinking when they look for jobs in the future.\"", "D": "\"If they do, they may miss something more important than just getting a chance to play with different toys.\""}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P6", "explain": "作者先說「不同玩具教孩子不同的東西」，接著舉出具體例子：娃娃有助語言發展、積木有助數學科學學習，這句「Dolls help with their early language use, and building toys are good for learning math and science.」就是用來說明前一句抽象概念的具體例子，所以選 B，其他選項都是作者陳述看法或推論的句子，不是舉例。", "keyPoint": "篇章結構：找出舉例句", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-39", "year": 112, "no": 39, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What is the reading mostly about?", "options": {"A": "Marie Colvin's war reports.", "B": "Marie Colvin's working life.", "C": "Marie Colvin's schooldays at Yale.", "D": "Marie Colvin's experiences in Homs."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P7", "explain": "文章雖然提到她在戰地報導的表現，但整篇其實是從她大學立志當記者開始，講到她加入 Sunday Times、到各地戰地採訪、失去一隻眼睛，一路到最後殉職，涵蓋的是她整個「記者生涯」，所以主旨是選項 B，而不是只談某一次報導或某段經歷。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：整篇人物傳記的重點", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-40", "year": 112, "no": 40, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does it mean when someone has empathy?", "options": {"A": "They are good at taking war photos.", "B": "They like to read other people's life stories.", "C": "They are able to understand how other people feel.", "D": "They are good at helping people change their own lives."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "112-P7", "explain": "文章描述 Colvin 寫的故事「讓你強烈感受到這些人的遭遇，就好像是你自己的事一樣」，這正是 empathy（同理心）的意思——能夠感同身受、理解別人的感受，所以選 C。其餘選項講的是攝影技巧、閱讀興趣或改變別人生活的能力，都不是 empathy 的定義。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：empathy = 同理心", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-41", "year": 112, "no": 41, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Which is true about Marie Colvin?", "options": {"A": "The chance to study at Yale made her leave her job in the Middle East.", "B": "The experience in Sri Lanka did not change her way of reporting news.", "C": "She was killed in Homs when she was interviewing soldiers there for her report.", "D": "She was not sure what to do in the future until she worked for the Sunday Times."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "112-P7", "explain": "文章提到她在斯里蘭卡的戰爭報導中失去了左眼，但「那從未阻止過她（that never stopped her）」，她依然繼續前往危險的地方採訪，代表這次經驗並沒有改變她的採訪風格，符合選項 B。其餘選項與文章不符：她並非因求學離開中東工作、她死於被攻擊而非採訪士兵時、她在念大學時就已立志當記者，並非到 Sunday Times 才確定方向。", "keyPoint": "細節理解：受傷後仍堅持報導風格", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-42", "year": 112, "no": 42, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "It's about ___(42)___ in different parts of the US.", "options": {"A": "what things are called", "B": "how sports are played", "C": "why different languages are spoken", "D": "what words are often spelled differently"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "112-P8", "explain": "後面舉的例子是「運動鞋在美國不同地區有不同叫法：tennis shoes、sneakers、gym shoes」，這說明書中討論的是「同一件東西在不同地方被叫做什麼」，也就是選項 A「事物的名稱」，而不是運動怎麼玩、語言為何不同或拼字差異。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：由舉例回推空格語意", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R112-43", "year": 112, "no": 43, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "But in my experience, it also shows ___(43)___.", "options": {"A": "how old they are", "B": "who they speak to", "C": "where they grew up", "D": "whether they are men or women"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "112-P8", "explain": "作者接著舉自己家三代人的例子：她自己說 sneakers、祖父說 plimsolls、女兒說 kicks/vans，三個世代用詞不同，說明用字反映的是「年齡（世代）」的差異，對應選項 A「他們的年紀多大」，而不是說話對象、成長地點或性別。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：用詞差異反映世代／年齡", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-1", "year": 111, "no": 1, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Look at the picture. The woman is putting       on the cake.", "options": {"A": "candles", "B": "forks", "C": "plates", "D": "strawberries"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "題目要看圖片，圖中女生正在蛋糕上放東西，慶祝場合的蛋糕上最常放的就是蠟燭(candles)，所以選A。叉子(forks)、盤子(plates)是用餐工具、草莓(strawberries)是水果配料，都不是圖片中被放上蛋糕的主角。", "keyPoint": "看圖選字彙(蛋糕情境)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-2", "year": 111, "no": 2, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "The movie starts at two o'clock,       let's meet at the theater at one forty-five.", "options": {"A": "so", "B": "or", "C": "if", "D": "because"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前句「電影兩點開演」是原因，後句「我們一點四十五在戲院見」是結果，所以要用表示「因此、所以」的連接詞so。or(否則)、if(如果)、because(因為，用來連接原因不能放在結果句前)語意都不合。", "keyPoint": "連接詞 so(表結果)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-3", "year": 111, "no": 3, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Peter is afraid of the dark. He even leaves the       on when sleeping.", "options": {"A": "computer", "B": "fans", "C": "lights", "D": "music"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "關鍵字是「afraid of the dark(怕黑)」，怕黑的人睡覺會開著燈(lights)壯膽，所以選C。電腦、電扇、音樂都跟怕黑沒有直接關係。", "keyPoint": "情境字彙 be afraid of the dark", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-4", "year": 111, "no": 4, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Pam is a       baseball player; she has more fans than any other player on her team.", "options": {"A": "boring", "B": "heavy", "C": "popular", "D": "rich"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後半句「she has more fans than any other player(她的粉絲比任何人都多)」就是線索，粉絲多代表受歡迎，所以選popular。boring(無聊)、heavy(重)、rich(有錢)都跟粉絲多寡沒有邏輯關聯。", "keyPoint": "語意推斷 popular(受歡迎)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-5", "year": 111, "no": 5, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "I did not do my homework, so my teacher said I       stay after school to finish it.", "options": {"A": "failed to", "B": "had to", "C": "hoped to", "D": "used to"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "因為沒寫作業被老師處罰，「不得不」留下來完成作業，表示被迫、必須做的意思要用had to(不得不)。failed to(失敗)、hoped to(希望)、used to(過去習慣)語意都不合。", "keyPoint": "had to(過去式的不得不)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-6", "year": 111, "no": 6, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Kevin has only enough money for the bag or the shoes. That is a hard       to make because he likes them both.", "options": {"A": "choice", "B": "gift", "C": "rule", "D": "trick"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「錢只夠買包包或鞋子其中一樣，這是很難做的...」，「做決定/選擇」的英文固定用make a choice，所以選choice。gift(禮物)、rule(規則)、trick(把戲)都套不進「難以做的___」。", "keyPoint": "make a choice(做選擇)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-7", "year": 111, "no": 7, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "It was       for us to answer the math question because we've done the same kind of questions many times.", "options": {"A": "common", "B": "easy", "C": "safe", "D": "special"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後半句「因為我們已經做過很多次同樣的題目」是原因，代表這題「很簡單」，所以選easy。common(常見)、safe(安全)、special(特別)在因果邏輯上都說不通。", "keyPoint": "語意因果判斷 easy", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-8", "year": 111, "no": 8, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Although it took me lots of time       a big meal for ten people, I was happy that everyone enjoyed it.", "options": {"A": "prepare", "B": "to prepare", "C": "preparing", "D": "prepared"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句型是「It took me + 時間 + to + 原形動詞」，表示「花了我...時間去做某事」，固定用to V，所以選to prepare。這是常考的it takes/took句型，不能直接用動詞原形、Ving或過去式。", "keyPoint": "It takes/took + 時間 + to V", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-9", "year": 111, "no": 9, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Don't let the children swim in the river. We don't know how       it is. It could be dangerous.", "options": {"A": "deep", "B": "far", "C": "long", "D": "thick"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「不知道河有多___，可能很危險」，講水的危險性通常是講「深度」，所以選deep(深)。far(遠)、long(長)、thick(厚)都不是形容河流危險程度常用的字。", "keyPoint": "how deep(深度)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-10", "year": 111, "no": 10, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Bob is       of the boys in the family. He never does any housework. His brothers at least take out the garbage sometimes.", "options": {"A": "lazier", "B": "the lazy", "C": "the lazier", "D": "the laziest"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句尾有「of the boys in the family(家裡的男孩們之中)」，這是「在一群人之中最...」的用法，要用最高級the laziest，所以選D。比較級lazier/the lazier用於兩者比較，這裡是三人以上比較要用最高級。", "keyPoint": "最高級 the + 形容詞est + of...", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-11", "year": 111, "no": 11, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Aunt Gina has lived in this town for more than sixty years, so she       it very well.", "options": {"A": "will know", "B": "knew", "C": "knows", "D": "was going to know"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「Gina阿姨已經住這裡60年了，所以她很了解這裡」，「很了解」是現在仍然存在的事實/狀態，要用現在簡單式knows，所以選C。will know是未來、knew是過去、was going to know是過去未實現的計畫，都不符合現在仍成立的狀態。", "keyPoint": "現在簡單式表示現況(結果)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-12", "year": 111, "no": 12, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "We won't see the sun even after the typhoon leaves, because the news said that heavier rain will soon      .", "options": {"A": "catch", "B": "follow", "C": "move", "D": "stop"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「颱風走了還看不到太陽，因為新聞說更大的雨快要___」，颱風過後常常伴隨後續的豪雨，「接著來、隨後而來」是follow，所以選B。catch(抓住)、move(移動)、stop(停止)語意都不合。", "keyPoint": "follow(接續而來)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-13", "year": 111, "no": 13, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Yesterday when I got home from work, my brother       for dinner, so he invited me to join him.", "options": {"A": "goes out", "B": "went out", "C": "has gone out", "D": "was going out"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「我到家的那一刻，弟弟正要出門吃晚餐」，表示過去某個時間點正在進行的動作，要用過去進行式was going out，所以選D。goes out是現在式、went out是過去完成的動作(會跟後面「邀我一起去」矛盾，因為他還沒真的出門)、has gone out是現在完成式，都不對。", "keyPoint": "過去進行式(過去某時正在進行的動作)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-14", "year": 111, "no": 14, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "You were       not to lend Amy money. She never gives back what she borrows.", "options": {"A": "crazy", "B": "helpful", "C": "wise", "D": "wrong"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「你當初沒借錢給Amy是明智的，因為她從不還錢」，「明智、聰明的判斷」要用wise，所以選C。crazy(瘋狂)、helpful(有幫助)、wrong(錯誤)都和「不借她錢是對的」這個正面評價相反或不合。", "keyPoint": "It's wise (not) to V(明智的做法)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-15", "year": 111, "no": 15, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Have you found a summer job yet? Mr. Firth       someone to take care of his kids during the vacation. Maybe you can talk to him.", "options": {"A": "has looked for", "B": "is looking for", "C": "looks for", "D": "was looking for"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前一句問「你找到暑期工作了嗎？」，後面說Mr. Firth現在正在找人顧小孩，這是現在正在進行的動作，要用現在進行式is looking for，所以選B。has looked for(現在完成式，已找到/找過)、looks for(現在簡單式，習慣性動作)、was looking for(過去進行式)都不符合「現在正在找、你可以去問他」的情境。", "keyPoint": "現在進行式(此刻正在進行)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-16", "year": 111, "no": 16, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "David looked out of the balcony window and saw a woman get in his car       away.", "options": {"A": "drive", "B": "drove", "C": "and drive", "D": "and drove"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句型是「感官動詞see + 受詞 + 原形動詞」，表示「看到某人做某事」，這裡有兩個動作(上車、開走)用and連接兩個原形動詞get in和drive，所以選and drive(C)。drive單獨用文法不完整；drove、and drove是過去式，不能接在受詞後面當受詞補語。", "keyPoint": "感官動詞 see + O + 原形V(and 原形並列)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-17", "year": 111, "no": 17, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "The police haven't found the little girl who       at a supermarket. They'll keep doing all they can to find her.", "options": {"A": "took away", "B": "taken away", "C": "has taken away", "D": "was taken away"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「警察還沒找到那個在超市被帶走的小女孩」，「被帶走」是被動語態，要用was taken away，所以選D。took away、taken away(缺be動詞文法不完整)、has taken away是主動完成式，都跟「小女孩被帶走」這個被動意思不合。", "keyPoint": "被動語態 was/were + p.p.", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-18", "year": 111, "no": 18, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Buses to the airport only come once every hour, and we just missed      . Why don't we take a taxi?", "options": {"A": "another", "B": "it", "C": "one", "D": "them"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「公車一小時一班，我們剛好錯過了___」，這裡指的是「同一類但不特定的一班公車」，要用one代替，所以選C。it指「特定同一個東西」、another是「另一個」、them是複數，都不符合這裡「錯過一班公車(泛指)」的意思。", "keyPoint": "one 代替同類但不特定的單數名詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-19", "year": 111, "no": 19, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Ariel       every night for a week before her Chinese test and got a very good grade.", "options": {"A": "studied", "B": "studies", "C": "has studied", "D": "was going to study"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意是「Ariel在中文考試前一星期，每晚都___，結果考得很好」，這是過去已經完成的固定動作，要用簡單過去式studied，所以選A。studies是現在式、has studied是現在完成式、was going to study是過去未實現的計畫，都不符合「已經做完並得到好成績」的情境。", "keyPoint": "簡單過去式(過去已完成的動作)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-20", "year": 111, "no": 20, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "While reading this story, Brad saw the word \"trolling\" and didn't know what it meant. Josh turned off the screen and sat back. \"Why are they trolling me like this?\" He didn't understand. They wanted him to share what he thought about the show, and he did. And now look what he got. In the end, all they wanted was nice words. He found several meanings of the word in a dictionary. Which one should Brad choose?", "options": {"A": "To celebrate in song.", "B": "To make someone or something move around.", "C": "To pull a fishing line through the water, often from a boat.", "D": "To write something on the Internet to hurt someone or make them angry."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "從上下文可以看出Josh分享了自己對節目的想法後，反而被別人用難聽的話攻擊，讓他很困惑不解，這符合「在網路上寫東西惹怒/傷害別人」的意思，所以選D。A唱歌慶祝、B讓某物到處移動、C拖釣魚線都跟網路上被人針對的情境無關。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測(上下文選出正確字義)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-21", "year": 111, "no": 21, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What does Tea-Rock celebrate?", "options": {"A": "Their sales in 20 countries.", "B": "The coming out of their 20th kind of tea.", "C": "Their 20th year of business.", "D": "The opening of their 20th store in the USA."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "111-P1", "explain": "文章提到Tea-Rock這個品牌正在慶祝品牌的第20年，也就是「20週年慶」，所以選C(20週年的生意/經營)。文中並沒有提到20個國家的銷售、第20種茶、或第20間美國分店開幕，都是誤導選項。", "keyPoint": "細節理解(慶祝主題)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-22", "year": 111, "no": 22, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Here is the postcard Jason is going to send to Tea-Rock 20. What else does he need to put on the postcard before he sends it?", "options": {"A": "His age.", "B": "His address.", "C": "His birthday.", "D": "Another picture of the tea cup."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "111-P1", "explain": "要看明信片圖片上已經填寫哪些欄位，題目說Jason準備要寄出前還缺什麼。從圖上可看出地址(address)已經有欄位、年齡與圖片也都已具備，唯獨還沒填生日(birthday)，所以選C。", "keyPoint": "看圖細節(明信片缺漏欄位)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-23", "year": 111, "no": 23, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What can we learn about sugar from the infographic?", "options": {"A": "There are 4 g of sugar in 66 g of ice cream.", "B": "A woman can eat as much sugar a day as a man can.", "C": "Taiwan eats more sugar for each person than the US does.", "D": "400 ml of rice milk has less sugar than 400 ml of grape juice."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P2", "explain": "這題要對照資訊圖表上各食物飲料的含糖量數字，圖表顯示400毫升的米漿(rice milk)含糖量比400毫升葡萄汁(grape juice)少，所以選D。其他選項的數字或比較(冰淇淋含糖量、男女攝取量、台美每人攝取量)跟圖表實際數據不符。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀(數據比較)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-24", "year": 111, "no": 24, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What can be a reason why the list of \"Sugar that is hidden in foods and drinks\" is put in the infographic?", "options": {"A": "To help us understand how sugar hurts our body.", "B": "To show what kinds of foods and drinks are popular with children.", "C": "To tell us that we often have more sugar than we can without knowing it.", "D": "To let us know how much sugar is enough to make foods and drinks taste good."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "111-P2", "explain": "圖表列出「隱藏在食物飲料中的糖分」清單，用意是要提醒大家：日常飲食中常常在不知不覺間攝取超量的糖分，所以選C。A只講糖對身體不好但沒點出「隱藏」重點，B、D跟清單的真正用意不符。", "keyPoint": "推論(圖表列表的用意)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-25", "year": 111, "no": 25, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why did Darrell tell Marina to go to Pinterest?", "options": {"A": "To find some examples for her homework.", "B": "To shop for things that are needed for art classes.", "C": "To meet new friends who have the same interests.", "D": "To share her works and tell people how they are made."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "111-P3", "explain": "對話中Marina說要幫美術作業畫一間未來的房子卻沒有靈感，Darrell才建議她去Pinterest找點子，所以選A。Pinterest不是拿來買東西的購物軟體(B錯)，對話裡也沒提到交朋友(C)，Darrell講的是「別人怎麼分享作品」但他叫Marina去的目的是找靈感、不是要她自己分享作品(D錯)。", "keyPoint": "細節理解(建議原因)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-26", "year": 111, "no": 26, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does it mean when you learn something from A to Z?", "options": {"A": "You can learn it at any time.", "B": "You learn it in a baking class.", "C": "You learn everything about it.", "D": "You spend all your life learning it."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "111-P3", "explain": "「from A to Z」字面是「從A到Z」，也就是從頭到尾全部都學到，對話中提到Darrell在Pinterest上學到做巧克力蛋糕「從選巧克力到烤蛋糕到裝飾糖花」，代表整個完整過程都學會了，所以選C(學會關於這件事的一切)。", "keyPoint": "片語 from A to Z(從頭到尾、完整學會)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-27", "year": 111, "no": 27, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "Which idea is talked about in the first paragraph of the reading?", "options": {"A": "How you should do Tabata training.", "B": "What is the best time for Tabata training.", "C": "Who first had the idea of Tabata training.", "D": "How often you should do Tabata training."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "111-P4", "explain": "第一段先講Tabata訓練很簡單、20秒運動休息10秒重複這個做法，還列出幾個常見動作，這些都是在說「你應該怎麼做Tabata訓練」，所以選A。訓練的最佳時間、發明人、頻率次數都沒有在第一段被提到。", "keyPoint": "段落主旨(首段大意)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-28", "year": 111, "no": 28, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Who might find that Tabata training is right for them?", "options": {"A": "People who enjoy team sports.", "B": "People who want to start exercising.", "C": "People who want to fix their heart problems.", "D": "People who already have a habit of exercising."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P4", "explain": "文章第二段說如果很少運動或有心臟問題的人不適合做這個訓練，反而是「喜歡運動但太忙沒空去健身房的人」最適合，這代表本來就有運動習慣的人(D)比較適合，A團體運動、B剛要開始運動、C想治心臟病都不符合文章描述。", "keyPoint": "推論(適合對象)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-29", "year": 111, "no": 29, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Which is true about Tabata training?", "options": {"A": "It is difficult to learn the moves.", "B": "You are free to choose your own moves.", "C": "You need a large space to do the exercises.", "D": "You cannot rest between moves if you want the afterburn."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "111-P4", "explain": "文章明確寫「You can decide yourself what moves to do(你可以自己決定要做哪些動作)」，所以選B(可以自由選擇自己的動作)。動作其實不難學(A錯)、不需要大空間(C錯)、文章說要休息10秒(D錯，並非不能休息)。", "keyPoint": "細節理解(自選動作)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-30", "year": 111, "no": 30, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "There are four important points in the report: a. What \"No Overtime Day\" is  b. Why \"No Overtime Day\" fails  c. Why there is \"No Overtime Day\" in the country  d. How workers deal with \"No Overtime Day\"  How are they ordered in the report?", "options": {"A": "acdb.", "B": "adcb.", "C": "cabd.", "D": "cadb."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P5", "explain": "對照文章段落順序：第一段先講長工時是問題、以及公司為何設立無加班日(c，為何有無加班日)，接著描述無加班日當天的樣子(a，無加班日是什麼)；第二段講員工離開辦公室後其實去別的地方繼續工作(d，員工怎麼應對無加班日)；第三段講研究顯示長工時能加薪升遷，解釋為何政策沒效果(b，為何無加班日失敗)。順序是c→a→d→b，所以選D。", "keyPoint": "段落順序(文章結構分析)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-31", "year": 111, "no": 31, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "What does \"this\" mean in the report?", "options": {"A": "The way workers show they are hard-working.", "B": "Restaurants and coffee shops open until very late at night.", "C": "Workers do not go home when they walk out of the office.", "D": "The number of workers who get paid more and rise higher in the company."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "111-P5", "explain": "「this」通常代替前一句提到的內容，前面一句寫「Working long hours has become a way to show that people are hard-working(長工時已經變成一種展現自己很努力工作的方式)」，「this」就是指這個現象，所以選A。", "keyPoint": "指代題(this/that回頭找前一句)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-32", "year": 111, "no": 32, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What can we learn from Figure 1 and Figure 2?", "options": {"A": "Long working hours killed more women than men in 2014.", "B": "Long working hours kills more and more workers every year.", "C": "Men usually have a bigger chance to get paid more and rise higher when they work the same hours as women.", "D": "Men and women have almost the same chance to get paid more and rise higher when they work 2,200 hours."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P5", "explain": "這題要看Figure 1、Figure 2兩張圖表的數據，圖2顯示當工時達到2,200小時左右時，男性和女性獲得加薪升遷的機會幾乎相同，所以選D。其他選項(哪年死更多女性、工時致死人數逐年增加、男性機會比女性大)都跟圖表實際數據不符。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀(數據對照)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-33", "year": 111, "no": 33, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "Which map is most likely the map of Cameroon in 1962?", "options": {"A": "(地圖圖片A，原始PDF未擷取圖像內容)", "B": "(地圖圖片B，原始PDF未擷取圖像內容)", "C": "(地圖圖片C，原始PDF未擷取圖像內容)", "D": "(地圖圖片D，原始PDF未擷取圖像內容)"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P6", "explain": "這題要看四張地圖選項，配合文章「1960年法屬喀麥隆變成喀麥隆共和國，1961年英屬部分加入，1961年後兩塊合併成一個國家」的歷史，1962年時喀麥隆應該已經是合併後的完整國家版圖，所以要選顯示「已合併成一整塊」的地圖D。", "keyPoint": "推論(對照文章歷史找出正確地圖)", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-34", "year": 111, "no": 34, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does resentful mean in the reading?", "options": {"A": "Sad.", "B": "Angry.", "C": "Careful.", "D": "Worried."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "111-P6", "explain": "從上下文「英語使用者對政府感到resentful，後來決定為自己抗爭(fight for themselves)」，可以推斷這是一種「生氣、不滿」的情緒才會導致抗爭，所以選B(Angry生氣)。難過(A)、小心(C)、擔心(D)都不會直接導致「起身抗爭」這個結果。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測(resentful=生氣不滿)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-35", "year": 111, "no": 35, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What does Cameroon's government most likely think of Ambazonia?", "options": {"A": "It plans to do business with Ambazonia.", "B": "It needs Ambazonia for money and help.", "C": "It does not want to be part of Ambazonia.", "D": "It does not agree that Ambazonia is a country."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P6", "explain": "文章說英語使用者自行宣布獨立成立「Ambazonia」，而政府派警察去阻止這場集會，這代表政府根本不承認Ambazonia是一個國家，所以選D。文中沒有提到政府想跟Ambazonia做生意(A)或需要它的資源(B)，C的說法邏輯也不通(政府本來就不屬於Ambazonia)。", "keyPoint": "推論(政府立場)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-36", "year": 111, "no": 36, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What does Elisa Grant try to tell readers by talking about the history of Cameroon?", "options": {"A": "Why speaking English is a way to get power.", "B": "Why English speakers in Cameroon have less power.", "C": "Why the two parts of Cameroon became one country.", "D": "Why only 20% of the people in Cameroon speak English."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "111-P6", "explain": "文章一開頭就說「通常會英語代表有權力，但喀麥隆卻不是這樣」，接著回顧歷史來解釋原因，所以整篇歷史說明的目的是要解釋「為什麼喀麥隆的英語使用者權力比較小」，選B。A剛好講反了(文章要說的是喀麥隆的特例，不是一般規則)，C、D只是歷史細節，不是作者講述歷史的主要目的。", "keyPoint": "主旨(作者寫作目的)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-37", "year": 111, "no": 37, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What is recommended to people who are visiting the Southend Trail?", "options": {"A": "Camping on the side trails.", "B": "Biking along the side trails.", "C": "Hiking one part of the trail a day.", "D": "Visiting the museum in the morning."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "111-P7", "explain": "文章建議「一天走一段步道(one part of the trail per day)」，因為每段至少要走七小時，所以選C。側邊步道不能露營也不能騎腳踏車(A、B錯)，博物館參觀時間文章並沒有特別建議在早上(D錯，早上是建議「開始健行」的時間)。", "keyPoint": "細節理解(行程建議)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-38", "year": 111, "no": 38, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does lodging mean in the reading?", "options": {"A": "A meal to have.", "B": "A place to stay in.", "C": "A time for visiting.", "D": "A way of moving around."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "111-P7", "explain": "文章接著說lodging有兩種：露營和住旅館，這些都是「過夜住宿的地方」，所以lodging是「住的地方」，選B。它跟餐點(A)、參觀時間(C)、交通方式(D)都無關。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測(lodging=住宿地點)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-39", "year": 111, "no": 39, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Kaylen will start his trip from Cove. He plans to visit one of the old castles. He also wants to go birdwatching near the river. Which parts of the trail should Kaylen go on?", "options": {"A": "Parts 1 and 2.", "B": "Parts 1 and 2a.", "C": "Parts 2 and 3.", "D": "Parts 4 and 4a."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "111-P7", "explain": "這題要對照步道地圖，Kaylen從Cove出發，要去參觀一座古堡並沿著河邊賞鳥，從地圖上可以看出從Cove走的Part 1和Part 2剛好會經過河流賞鳥點以及其中一座城堡，所以選A。", "keyPoint": "圖表(地圖)判讀", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R111-40", "year": 111, "no": 40, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "40. (在文中空格處，選出最適合的用語)", "options": {"A": "in fact", "B": "at first", "C": "of course", "D": "for example"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "111-P8", "explain": "空格前先定義「回文」，空格後緊接著列出「eye」、「Bob」等好幾個回文的實際範例，這種「先講定義、再舉出例子」的銜接語要用for example(舉例來說)，所以選D。in fact(事實上)、at first(起初)、of course(當然)前後語意銜接都不通順。", "keyPoint": "銜接語 for example(舉例)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-41", "year": 111, "no": 41, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "41. (根據上下文，選出符合anagram範例的選項)", "options": {"A": "take sit", "B": "Ms Easy", "C": "it makes", "D": "me steak"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "111-P8", "explain": "變位詞(anagram)是把同一組字母重新排列組成新的字/詞，「it makes」的字母剛好可以重組成「mistake(錯誤)」這個字，符合anagram的定義，所以選C。其他選項的字母組合沒有對應到一個有意義、常考的變位詞例子。", "keyPoint": "變位詞(anagram)辨識", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-42", "year": 111, "no": 42, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "42. (在文中空格處，選出最適合的用語)", "options": {"A": "strange", "B": "difficult", "C": "delicious", "D": "important"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "111-P8", "explain": "文章舉例「restaurant」重組後變成「Eat rats, run!(吃老鼠，快跑！)」，這樣的意思跟原本的字完全不相關又很搞笑，這種「意想不到、很奇怪」的感覺要用strange，所以選A。difficult(困難)、delicious(好吃)、important(重要)都跟這個例子想表達的意外感不合。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測(strange=奇特意外)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R111-43", "year": 111, "no": 43, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "43. (在文中空格處，選出最適合總結全文的用語)", "options": {"A": "more than just games", "B": "often played in public", "C": "not so popular as before", "D": "not first used to learn words"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "111-P8", "explain": "最後一段說回文和變位詞可以拿來學數學、作曲、甚至藏重要資料，這些都超出「只是好玩的文字遊戲」的範圍，所以要選能總結全文的more than just games(不只是遊戲)，選A。其他選項都沒有呼應「還有實際用途」這個總結重點。", "keyPoint": "主旨(段落/全文總結)", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-1", "year": 110, "no": 1, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "In the picture, the boy is ___ the old man.", "options": {"A": "smiling at", "B": "dancing with", "C": "cheering for", "D": "bowing to"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "題目說「男孩對老人 ___」，圖片是關鍵線索，男孩對長輩應該是行禮鞠躬，所以是 bowing to（向...鞠躬）。smiling at（對...微笑）、dancing with（和...跳舞）、cheering for（為...歡呼）都不符合對長輩的禮貌動作情境。", "keyPoint": "看圖選動詞片語", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R110-2", "year": 110, "no": 2, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Listen! The baby ___ in the bedroom. Why don't you go in and take a look?", "options": {"A": "cried", "B": "cries", "C": "is crying", "D": "will cry"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句首 Listen! 表示「現在正在發生」的動作，加上建議對方馬上去看看，所以要用現在進行式 is crying，表示嬰兒此刻正在哭。cried 是過去式、cries 是現在簡單式（習慣性動作）、will cry 是未來式，都不符合當下正在發生的情境。", "keyPoint": "現在進行式：Listen! 提示正在發生的動作", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-3", "year": 110, "no": 3, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Jill is ___ that the city park is closed for the music festival because now she can't jog there.", "options": {"A": "excited", "B": "proud", "C": "scared", "D": "unhappy"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "公園關閉導致她不能去慢跑，這是令人不開心的事，所以選 unhappy（不高興的）。excited（興奮）、proud（驕傲）、scared（害怕）都跟「不能慢跑」這個負面結果不搭配。", "keyPoint": "情緒形容詞語意判斷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-4", "year": 110, "no": 4, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Steven wants to be a ___, because he loves to watch people enjoy the food he prepares.", "options": {"A": "cook", "B": "doctor", "C": "driver", "D": "farmer"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "關鍵線索是 watch people enjoy the food he prepares（看人們享用他準備的食物），這是廚師（cook）的工作內容，doctor、driver、farmer 都跟準備食物給人吃無關。", "keyPoint": "職業字彙依線索判斷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-5", "year": 110, "no": 5, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Paul misses his parents a lot. He ___ them since he came to work in Taiwan a year ago.", "options": {"A": "didn't see", "B": "doesn't see", "C": "hasn't seen", "D": "won't see"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "since he came to work in Taiwan a year ago（自從一年前來台灣工作）是現在完成式的經典提示詞 since，表示「從過去某時間點到現在」一直沒見到爸媽，所以用 has/have + p.p.，選 hasn't seen。didn't see、doesn't see、won't see 時態都不對。", "keyPoint": "現在完成式 since", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-6", "year": 110, "no": 6, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Our teacher Ms. Wu seldom laughs, but when she ___, everyone in the same building can hear her.", "options": {"A": "can", "B": "does", "C": "has", "D": "will"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "這句用助動詞代替前面的動詞 laughs，因為前面是現在簡單式動詞 laughs，所以要用 does 來代替，避免重複，形成 do/does 代動詞。can、has、will 的時態或用法都跟前面 laughs 不一致。", "keyPoint": "助動詞代動詞（do/does）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-7", "year": 110, "no": 7, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "My sister is coming to my home today. She ___ with me for a week.", "options": {"A": "stays", "B": "stayed", "C": "has stayed", "D": "will stay"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "today 加上「接下來要待一週」，是講未來即將發生的事，所以用未來式 will stay。stays 是現在簡單式、stayed 是過去式、has stayed 是完成式，都不符合「今天要來、之後會待一週」的未來情境。", "keyPoint": "未來式表示即將發生的事", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-8", "year": 110, "no": 8, "section": "單題", "type": "字彙", "skill": "字彙", "stem": "Edward had worked as a computer engineer for ten years. This ___ helped him a lot when he started his own computer shop.", "options": {"A": "chance", "B": "experience", "C": "hobby", "D": "knowledge"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "做了十年的電腦工程師，這段「經歷」對他日後開店很有幫助，所以選 experience（經驗、經歷）。chance（機會）、hobby（嗜好）、knowledge（知識）都無法對應「做了十年」這種累積出來的東西。補充：knowledge 偏「知識內容」，常搭配 of…；此處 This 回指「當了十年工程師」這段經歷，用 experience（一段經歷）最貼切。", "keyPoint": "字彙語意：experience（經驗）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-9", "year": 110, "no": 9, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "If you're interested in our business plan, ___ this number and ask for Ms. Lee. She'll answer your questions.", "options": {"A": "calling", "B": "call", "C": "and call", "D": "to call"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "這句是祈使句：If 開頭的條件句後面接主要子句，主要子句要用原形動詞開頭表示命令/建議，所以選 call（打電話）。calling、to call 不是祈使句該用的形式，and call 則多加了不必要的連接詞。", "keyPoint": "祈使句：If子句 + 原形動詞", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-10", "year": 110, "no": 10, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Jimmy would not get up for breakfast, ___ his dad had already tried to pull him from his bed several times.", "options": {"A": "although", "B": "because", "C": "if", "D": "until"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前面「爸爸已經拉了他好幾次」，後面「Jimmy還是不起床」，兩件事是「雖然...但還是」的對比關係，所以用 although（雖然）。because（因為）、if（如果）、until（直到）在邏輯上都接不起來這兩個對比的事實。", "keyPoint": "連接詞 although 表讓步", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-11", "year": 110, "no": 11, "section": "單題", "type": "語意", "skill": "語意", "stem": "Duncan spent all his money trying to ___ the bookstore his mom left him. Sadly, the business never got better, and he had to close it in the end.", "options": {"A": "build", "B": "buy", "C": "save", "D": "start"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "花光所有錢想「保住/挽救」媽媽留給他的書店，結果生意沒好轉最後還是關門，所以選 save（挽救、拯救）。build（建造）、buy（買）、start（開始）都跟「已經是媽媽留下的書店、想努力維持」的情境不合。", "keyPoint": "字彙語意：save（挽救）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-12", "year": 110, "no": 12, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Fiona loves listening to her children sing songs ___ at school.", "options": {"A": "are learned", "B": "that learned", "C": "they learned", "D": "that they are learned"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "songs 後面省略了關係代名詞 that/which，還原句子是 songs (that) they learned at school，形容詞子句中省略受格關代後直接接主詞+動詞，所以選 they learned。其餘選項文法結構錯誤（動詞形式或多餘的關代）。", "keyPoint": "形容詞子句省略受格關代", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-13", "year": 110, "no": 13, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Beverly eats lots of snacks ___ meals. That's why she is often too full to eat anything at mealtimes.", "options": {"A": "after", "B": "between", "C": "during", "D": "from"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "在正餐與正餐「之間」吃零食，導致正餐吃不下，所以選 between meals（三餐之間）。after（之後）、during（期間中）、from（從）都不符合「兩餐中間」這個時間點的意思。", "keyPoint": "介系詞 between 表示中間", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-14", "year": 110, "no": 14, "section": "單題", "type": "語法", "skill": "語法", "stem": "Nora: Can I check your drawer for some tools we can use? Matt: Sure. Take a look. See if you can find ___ in there.", "options": {"A": "any", "B": "it", "C": "others", "D": "those"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "在疑問句/條件句中，「任何」東西要用 any（不特定的任何工具），所以選 any。it 指特定的東西、others 指其他的（複數可數）、those 指那些（特定），都不符合「隨便找找看有沒有工具」這種不確定的語氣。", "keyPoint": "any 用於疑問句表示「任何」", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-15", "year": 110, "no": 15, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What is this ad for?", "options": {"A": "Teaching people how to use their BeautiMed points.", "B": "Telling people they can shop at BeautiMed on the Internet now.", "C": "Inviting people to share their shopping experience at e-BeautiMed.", "D": "Letting people know what is on sale at e-BeautiMed from 7/1 to 8/31."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "110-P1", "explain": "整篇DM是在宣布 e-BeautiMed 這個網路商店開張，並列出各種驚喜活動，重點在「告訴大家現在可以上網購物了」，所以答案是B。A、C、D都只是其中一小部分驚喜的內容，不是整篇廣告的主旨。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：找廣告的整體目的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-16", "year": 110, "no": 16, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What will NOT get you BeautiMed points?", "options": {"A": "Shopping at e-BeautiMed.", "B": "Joining \"BeautiMed Friend\" online.", "C": "Inviting a friend to join \"BeautiMed Friend.\"", "D": "Entering the \"BeautiMed Friend\" card number."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "110-P1", "explain": "文中Surprise 2 說已經是會員的人「輸入卡號」是去領免費禮物（free gift），不是拿點數（points）。而Surprise 1、3、5 都明確寫著會得到points，只有輸入卡號領禮物這件事跟拿點數無關，所以選D。", "keyPoint": "細節題：從各驚喜項目找出不給點數的那項", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-17", "year": 110, "no": 17, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Lynn took some photos at Tom's party. Which is most likely one of them?", "options": {"A": "(picture option A)", "B": "(picture option B)", "C": "(picture option C)", "D": "(picture option D)"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "110-P2", "explain": "此題需依原卷圖片判斷，對話中Lynn描述在Caldron吃火鍋的經驗——大家把不同食材丟進同一鍋滾水裡煮，要對照圖片選出最符合「大家自己煮、共用一鍋」的火鍋聚餐照片。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：對照對話內容選圖片", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R110-18", "year": 110, "no": 18, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "What can we learn about Lynn from the dialogue?", "options": {"A": "She does not cook.", "B": "She likes to try new food.", "C": "She did not enjoy the food at Caldron.", "D": "She changed Joey's idea about Caldron."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P2", "explain": "Lynn整段話都在抱怨：食物全部同一個味道、不知道丟進鍋裡的是什麼、覺得沒有樂趣，最後還說「我們對好經驗的定義不一樣」，可知她並不享受在Caldron吃的食物，所以選C。她並非不會煮飯（A），也沒有喜歡嘗新（B），更沒有改變Joey的想法（D，是Joey想說服她）。", "keyPoint": "推論題：從抱怨語氣判斷態度", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-19", "year": 110, "no": 19, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What do we know about Woollie from Katie's diary?", "options": {"A": "Woollie was older than Katie.", "B": "Woollie was taken to visit sick kids.", "C": "Woollie was sick when he ran away.", "D": "Woollie looked strange without his fleece."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P3", "explain": "日記提到Woollie逃跑時是4歲，花了6年才被找到，也就是說Woollie被找到時至少10歲，而這件事發生在Katie出生那天，代表Woollie的年紀比Katie大很多，所以選A。B、C、D在日記中都找不到對應的敘述（他是健康時被剪毛、被賣是為了幫助生病的孩子，不是他自己生病）。", "keyPoint": "細節題：計算年齡推論", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-20", "year": 110, "no": 20, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "Which picture of Woollie and Ms. Clark did Katie talk about in her diary?", "options": {"A": "(picture option A)", "B": "(picture option B)", "C": "(picture option C)", "D": "(picture option D)"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P3", "explain": "此題需依原卷圖片作答，日記中提到故事書裡Woollie被帶去見市長Ms. Clark，兩人還一起喝茶，要選出符合「一隻羊和一位女士一起喝茶」情境的圖片。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：對照文字描述選圖", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R110-21", "year": 110, "no": 21, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What happened when Woollie was put down?", "options": {"A": "He was sold.", "B": "He couldn't be found.", "C": "He died.", "D": "He became famous."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P3", "explain": "文中說Woollie was put down because he was too sick and there was no way to help him，接著Katie就哭了，並希望Woollie在天堂快樂，可知put down在此是「安樂死、死掉」的意思，所以選C（他死了）。從上下文的悲傷情緒和「天上」可以猜出這個字義，不是被賣掉、找不到或變有名。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：put down（安樂死）從上下文推測", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-22", "year": 110, "no": 22, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What can we learn about The Piano Lesson from the reading?", "options": {"A": "Matisse painted it when his son was away from home.", "B": "The woman who sits on a seat behind the boy is his mother.", "C": "Matisse uses yellow and red to show that his son was happy.", "D": "The candle on the piano shows that the piano lesson has just begun."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P4", "explain": "文章最後說Pierre當時16歲卻被畫得更年輕，因為他已經去當兵離家了，父親不知道他是否能平安回來，可知這幅畫是在兒子離家從軍時畫的，所以選A。B錯，那個女人其實是另一幅畫作中的人物，不確定是母親；C錯，灰色調顯示的是嚴肅/不開心而非快樂；D錯，蠟燭快燒完顯示已經彈了很久，不是剛開始。", "keyPoint": "細節題：從文末推論作畫背景", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-23", "year": 110, "no": 23, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "What does \"do that\" mean in the reading?", "options": {"A": "Put his family in his paintings.", "B": "Paint to remember the good old days.", "C": "Use a lot of fun colors in his art works.", "D": "Put his earlier art work in a new painting."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "110-P4", "explain": "前文提到畫中右上角的女士其實是馬諦斯另一幅畫作《Woman on a High Stool》裡的人物，左下角的雕像也是他的另一件作品，說明馬諦斯喜歡把自己「之前的作品」放進新畫作裡，這就是「do that」指的事，所以選D。其餘選項都偏離了「把舊作品放進新畫」這個具體行為。", "keyPoint": "指代題：do that 指前文提到的重複行為", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-24", "year": 110, "no": 24, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "指代", "stem": "What is NOT used in the reading to refer to Henri Matisse?", "options": {"A": "The artist.", "B": "The painter.", "C": "The poor kid.", "D": "A worried father."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P4", "explain": "文中用painter、artist、a worried father來稱呼馬諦斯本人，而「the poor kid」（可憐的孩子）是用來形容兒子Pierre的，不是指馬諦斯自己，所以選C。", "keyPoint": "指代題：分辨稱呼的對象是誰", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-25", "year": 110, "no": 25, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What idea is talked about in the reading?", "options": {"A": "How Teachers' Day is celebrated now.", "B": "Why Teachers' Day was celebrated at first.", "C": "Why Confucius was seen as a great teacher.", "D": "How teachers today feel about Teachers' Day."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "110-P5", "explain": "整篇文章主要在講教師節「一開始」為什麼被慶祝——是老師們為了爭取被尊重、抗議待遇不好而發起的，而不是為了紀念孔子，所以主旨是B。A、C、D都不是文章討論的重點（文章沒講現在怎麼慶祝、也沒特別解釋孔子為何偉大、更沒講現代老師的感受）。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：抓文章討論的核心焦點", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-26", "year": 110, "no": 26, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Which is true about Teachers' Day from the reading?", "options": {"A": "It used to be celebrated on different dates.", "B": "It was started by students for their teachers.", "C": "It has been celebrated in Nanjing for over 2,500 years.", "D": "Teachers decided to celebrate it on Confucius's birthday."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P5", "explain": "文章提到教師節最初是6月6日（1930年老師們自訂），後來變成8月27日（政府誤以為的孔子生日），最後又改成9月28日（真正的孔子生日），可見日期改變過很多次，所以選A。B錯，是老師自己發起而非學生；C錯，教師節在南京只慶祝一次不是2500年；D錯，是政府決定放在孔子生日，不是老師們自己決定。", "keyPoint": "細節題：整理教師節日期的演變", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-27", "year": 110, "no": 27, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "字義猜測", "stem": "What does \"not everyone hailed this decision\" mean in the reading?", "options": {"A": "Not everyone cared about the decision.", "B": "Not everyone welcomed the decision.", "C": "Not everyone heard about the decision.", "D": "Not everyone remembered the decision."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "110-P5", "explain": "hail在這裡是「歡呼、稱讚、歡迎」的意思，接著文章解釋「教師節本來就跟孔子無關，孔子也不能代表所有老師」，可知有人不贊同/不歡迎把教師節定在孔子生日這個決定，所以選B。從後面反對的理由可以推出hail是正面接受的意思。", "keyPoint": "字義猜測：hail（歡迎、稱讚）從上下文推測", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-28", "year": 110, "no": 28, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "What does the writer try to do with this reading?", "options": {"A": "To talk about a problem that no one notices.", "B": "To share a fun experience that was not common.", "C": "To tell a piece of history that few people know about.", "D": "To give an example of an idea that is hard to understand."}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P5", "explain": "整篇文章在講述教師節由來的歷史過程，包含很多一般人不知道的細節（例如最初不是為了孔子、日期還算錯過），這是在分享一段鮮為人知的歷史，所以選C。文章不是討論沒人注意的問題（A）、也不是分享有趣的親身經驗（B）、更沒有舉一個難懂的例子（D）。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：判斷作者寫作目的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-29", "year": 110, "no": 29, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "Why does National Formosa Railway write this letter?", "options": {"A": "There is a train ticket sale.", "B": "A train line will be closed in July.", "C": "It will open a new train line in August.", "D": "Some of its trains will run on different lines."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "110-P6", "explain": "整封信的重點是告訴旅客因颱風影響，部分列車將改走不同路線、不停靠某些站，所以主旨是D。A錯，信中沒提售票活動；B錯，是8月14-28日關閉而非7月；C錯，是既有路線改道，不是開新路線。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：找公告信的目的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-30", "year": 110, "no": 30, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "What is true about NFR's trains between August 14 and 28 2016?", "options": {"A": "No trains will stop at Spring Town.", "B": "Trains that change lines will all stop at Cloud City.", "C": "People can take the free buses to any station on the Sand Town - Spring Town line.", "D": "People can go to Hill Town on any train that runs between Green City and Cloud City."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "110-P6", "explain": "文中說改走Smoke Town–Spring Town線的列車「每一站都停」（will stop at every station），這些列車行駛於Green City和Cloud City之間，所以搭乘這些車就可以到Hill Town（沙町–春町線上的一站），所以選D。A錯，車還是有停Spring Town；B錯，改線列車有些終點站是Spring Town不是全部都到Cloud City；C錯，免費巴士只停Green City和Spring Town，不是任何一站。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：對照公告細節與路線表", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R110-31", "year": 110, "no": 31, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "圖表判讀", "stem": "James lives in Smoke Town. He wants to go to Black Town on August 19. How can he get there?", "options": {"A": "Take Train RL202 to Green City, get off there, and take the free bus.", "B": "Take Train RL103 to Green City, get off there, and take the free bus.", "C": "Take Train RL102 to Spring Town, get off there, and take Train RL201.", "D": "Take Train RL101 to Cloud City, get off there, and take the free bus."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P6", "explain": "James住Smoke Town要去Black Town（沙町線上的站），公告說改線列車在Green City（南下）等免費巴士，且RL202是Cloud City到Green City方向（往北经過/停靠Smoke Town方向可搭乘再到Green City換車），到Green City下車後轉免費巴士就能到Black Town，所以選A。其他選項的路線或轉乘方式與公告資訊不符（例如RL103是南下往Cloud City、免費巴士不到全部站、RL101沒有在Green City停靠转乘）。", "keyPoint": "圖表判讀：對照路線圖規劃轉乘方式", "needsImage": true}, {"id": "R110-32", "year": 110, "no": 32, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "主旨", "stem": "Below are the ideas that are talked about in the reading. a. The problems Darayya has. b. How Darayya's library was started. c. What makes Darayya's library special. d. How Darayya's library helps people there. In what order does the writer put his ideas in the reading?", "options": {"A": "c, b, a, d.", "B": "b, a, d, c.", "C": "a, c, b, d.", "D": "c, a, b, d."}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "110-P7", "explain": "文章第一段先介紹圖書館的特別之處（地下秘密圖書館，對應c），接著講戰爭帶來的問題（房屋被炸、學校關閉，對應a），然後說Anas Ahmad如何建立圖書館（對應b），最後講圖書館如何幫助當地人（對應d），所以順序是c, a, b, d，選D。", "keyPoint": "主旨題：分析文章段落順序", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-33", "year": 110, "no": 33, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "Why do people in Darayya go to the library even during the war?", "options": {"A": "They can get free food.", "B": "They find joy and hope in reading.", "C": "They want to learn how to win the war.", "D": "Their school teachers give lessons there."}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "110-P7", "explain": "文末引用圖書館使用者的話「心靈也需要書就像身體需要食物」，並說閱讀讓人忘記外面可怕的世界、能夠夢想戰後更好的生活，可知人們去圖書館是為了在閱讀中找到快樂與希望，所以選B。文中沒提到免費食物、學打仗或老師授課。", "keyPoint": "細節題：找出人們去圖書館的原因", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-34", "year": 110, "no": 34, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "細節", "stem": "What do we know about Darayya's library?", "options": {"A": "It was built during the war.", "B": "It has been bombed many times.", "C": "It was built to remember people who died in the war.", "D": "Most of its books are collected from outside of Darayya."}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P7", "explain": "文中明確說是為了在戰爭期間幫助孩子們學習，Anas Ahmad和朋友們才決定建這座圖書館，也就是在戰爭「期間」建造的，所以選A。B文中沒說圖書館本身被炸過（是去收書的房子被炸）；C錯，建圖書館是為了幫助孩子學習不是紀念戰死者；D錯，書大多是從被炸毀的Darayya當地房子裡收集來的，不是從外地。", "keyPoint": "細節題：確認圖書館的建造背景", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-35", "year": 110, "no": 35, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "We know we told you that the party would be in  35 .", "options": {"A": "Victor Zoo", "B": "Carlton City", "C": "Mosman Garden", "D": "Northbank Park"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": "110-P8", "explain": "後文說「我們搬到Carlton City了，所以派對不會在Pattersons Town，會辦在Mosman Garden，請不要去我們舊家旁的Northbank Park」，可知原本說過派對要辦在舊家附近，也就是Northbank Park，所以選D。", "keyPoint": "推論題：由後文找出被取代的舊地點", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-36", "year": 110, "no": 36, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "The weather report said that it may be rainy this weekend, but  36 .", "options": {"A": "we have a plan if this happens", "B": "we could just wait for the rain to stop", "C": "we should be fine if the rain isn't too heavy", "D": "we will let you know if we'll still have the party"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P8", "explain": "後一句說「如果下雨，我們會把派對移到家裡」，代表這就是「即使氣象預報說可能下雨，但」他們已經有備案了，所以選A（我們有計畫因應這種狀況）。B、C、D都沒有明確提到「已經想好對策」這件事。", "keyPoint": "推論題：連接下文的備案內容", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-37", "year": 110, "no": 37, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "However, if we're  37  and it is fine, we'll still have the party at the garden.", "options": {"A": "crazy", "B": "good", "C": "lucky", "D": "strong"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P8", "explain": "前面說氣象預報可能下雨，這句是說「如果我們很___而且天氣晴朗，還是會在花園辦派對」，意思是「如果運氣好」天氣沒下雨，所以選 lucky（幸運的）。crazy（瘋狂）、good（好的）、strong（強壯）都不符合「靠運氣賭天氣」的語意。", "keyPoint": "推論題：lucky 表示靠運氣", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-38", "year": 110, "no": 38, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "The stories I'd heard about the park  38  into my head at this moment.", "options": {"A": "are all coming", "B": "have all come", "C": "were all coming", "D": "would all come"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": "110-P9", "explain": "此句描述過去某一刻（看到樹下的男人那瞬間）心裡湧現各種故事，是描述「過去進行中」的心理狀態，故事「當時正一直湧入腦海」，所以用過去進行式 were all coming。故事發生在整段回憶的過去時空裡，其他時態（現在式、現在完成式、條件語氣would）都不符合此刻回憶過去當下的情境。", "keyPoint": "過去進行式描述當下心理狀態", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-39", "year": 110, "no": 39, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "I did  39  stupid thing: I decided to hurry past him.", "options": {"A": "another", "B": "one", "C": "the last", "D": "the other"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P9", "explain": "前一句說任何有清醒頭腦的人都會轉頭走，但「我」卻做了「另一件」蠢事（決定加速從男人身邊經過），暗示這不是唯一一件蠢事、還有其他蠢事，所以選another（再一件、另一件）。one指單純的一件、the last指最後一件、the other指兩者中的另一個，都不符合「還有其他蠢事」的語意。", "keyPoint": "another 表示再一件（暗示不只一件）", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-40", "year": 110, "no": 40, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "I had hoped the trees would keep some rain off. And they  40 .", "options": {"A": "have", "B": "did", "C": "had", "D": "would"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": "110-P9", "explain": "這句用助動詞代替前面提過的動詞片語 keep some rain off，前面是過去式的假設（would keep），實際結果用did來代替「確實有擋到雨」這件事（過去簡單式的代動詞），所以選did。其餘選項時態或用法都對不上。", "keyPoint": "代動詞 did 表示過去確實發生", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "R110-41", "year": 110, "no": 41, "section": "題組", "type": "閱讀理解", "skill": "推論", "stem": "\"What? I  41  to give back your bag! You dropped it,\" the man gave me my bag.", "options": {"A": "was trying", "B": "try", "C": "would try", "D": "will try"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": "110-P9", "explain": "男人解釋自己剛才的動作：他「正試著」把包包還給對方（過去某個時間點正在進行的動作），所以用過去進行式 was trying，呼應前面「他一直追著我跑」的情境。try、would try、will try都不符合「過去正在做的動作」的敘述時態。", "keyPoint": "過去進行式描述當時正在做的動作", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H1", "year": null, "no": 1, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The two countries fought a terrible ___ that lasted for ten years.", "options": {"A": "peace", "B": "meeting", "C": "war", "D": "festival"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：兩國打了一場持續十年的可怕「戰爭」。fought（打）+ terrible（可怕的）都指向war；peace(和平)語意相反不合、meeting(會議)/festival(節慶)不會用「打」且不會「可怕」。", "keyPoint": "war 戰爭", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H2", "year": null, "no": 2, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The ___ built new roads and schools for the people in the city.", "options": {"A": "government", "B": "family", "C": "animal", "D": "weather"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「政府」為市民興建新道路和學校，這是政府的職責。family(家庭)/animal(動物)/weather(天氣)都不會做「建造道路學校」這件事。", "keyPoint": "government 政府", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H3", "year": null, "no": 3, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "Please fill in the ___ space with your name and phone number.", "options": {"A": "busy", "B": "noisy", "C": "full", "D": "blank"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：請在「空白」處填上姓名和電話。fill in（填寫）暗示那裡是空的，故選blank；busy(忙碌的)/noisy(吵鬧的)/full(滿的)都不合理，尤其full和「空白」意思相反。", "keyPoint": "blank 空白的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H4", "year": null, "no": 4, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "She wrote down every ___ that came into her mind before the test.", "options": {"A": "thought", "B": "chair", "C": "river", "D": "shoe"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：考試前她把腦中出現的每個「想法」都寫下來。came into her mind（浮現腦海）明確指向thought；chair(椅子)/river(河流)/shoe(鞋子)都是具體物品，不會「浮現腦海」。", "keyPoint": "thought 想法", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H5", "year": null, "no": 5, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The teacher praised him for his quick ___ when the fire started.", "options": {"A": "color", "B": "price", "C": "action", "D": "shape"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：火災發生時他反應迅速，老師稱讚他的快速「行動」。quick action(迅速的行動)是常見搭配；color(顏色)/price(價格)/shape(形狀)在此語境下都說不通。", "keyPoint": "action 活動；行動", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H6", "year": null, "no": 6, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The singer walked onto the ___ and began to sing for the excited crowd.", "options": {"A": "kitchen", "B": "bathroom", "C": "garage", "D": "stage"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：歌手走上「舞臺」，開始為興奮的觀眾唱歌。walked onto + sing for crowd都指向表演場地stage；kitchen(廚房)/bathroom(浴室)/garage(車庫)都不是表演的地方。", "keyPoint": "stage 舞臺", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H7", "year": null, "no": 7, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "After thinking for a long time, he finally made a ___ to study abroad.", "options": {"A": "decision", "B": "sandwich", "C": "mirror", "D": "umbrella"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：想了很久之後，他終於做出出國唸書的「決定」。make a decision（做決定）是固定搭配；sandwich(三明治)/mirror(鏡子)/umbrella(雨傘)都無法被「做出」來表達選擇。", "keyPoint": "decision 決定", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H8", "year": null, "no": 8, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The students had to write a ___ about their science experiment.", "options": {"A": "balloon", "B": "blanket", "C": "report", "D": "pillow"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：學生們必須為科學實驗寫一份「報告」。write a report(寫報告)是常見用法；balloon(氣球)/blanket(毯子)/pillow(枕頭)都不是可以「撰寫」的東西。", "keyPoint": "report 報告", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H9", "year": null, "no": 9, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The little birds stayed warm inside their ___ high in the tree.", "options": {"A": "nest", "B": "desk", "C": "sofa", "D": "ladder"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：小鳥們待在樹上高處的「鳥巢」裡保暖。high in the tree(在樹上高處)明確指向nest；desk(書桌)/sofa(沙發)/ladder(梯子)都不會出現在樹上。", "keyPoint": "nest 鳥巢", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H10", "year": null, "no": 10, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The restaurant is famous for its friendly ___ and delicious food.", "options": {"A": "mountain", "B": "pencil", "C": "bicycle", "D": "service"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：這家餐廳以親切的「服務」和美味的食物聞名。friendly service(親切的服務)是常見搭配，且和food並列；mountain(山)/pencil(鉛筆)/bicycle(腳踏車)都與餐廳無關。", "keyPoint": "service 服務", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H11", "year": null, "no": 11, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Can you tell me the ___ why you were late for class today?", "options": {"A": "window", "B": "potato", "C": "reason", "D": "ladder"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：你能告訴我今天上課遲到的「理由」嗎？the reason why(…的理由)是固定用法；window(窗戶)/potato(馬鈴薯)/ladder(梯子)都不能解釋遲到的原因。", "keyPoint": "reason 理由", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H12", "year": null, "no": 12, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Elephants have great ___ in their strong legs and trunks.", "options": {"A": "power", "B": "flavor", "C": "shadow", "D": "button"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：大象強壯的腿和鼻子擁有強大的「力量」。strong legs(強壯的腿)呼應power(力量)；flavor(味道)/shadow(影子)/button(鈕扣)都與身體力量無關。", "keyPoint": "power 力量", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H13", "year": null, "no": 13, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "You can find more ___ about the trip on the school website.", "options": {"A": "vegetable", "B": "umbrella", "C": "bicycle", "D": "information"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：你可以在學校網站上找到關於這次旅行更多的「資訊」。find information on a website(在網站上找到資訊)是常見用法；vegetable(蔬菜)/umbrella(雨傘)/bicycle(腳踏車)都不合語意。", "keyPoint": "information 資訊", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H14", "year": null, "no": 14, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Too much sugar can have a bad ___ on your health.", "options": {"A": "chair", "B": "effect", "C": "holiday", "D": "pocket"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：吃太多糖對健康會有不好的「影響」。have an effect on(對…有影響)是固定用法；chair(椅子)/holiday(假期)/pocket(口袋)都無法被「產生」出對健康的影響。", "keyPoint": "effect 影響", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H15", "year": null, "no": 15, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Our English teacher chose \"travel\" as the ___ for this week's discussion.", "options": {"A": "spoon", "B": "ladder", "C": "topic", "D": "jacket"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：英文老師選擇「旅行」作為這週討論的「主題」。chose ... as the topic(選作主題)是常見搭配；spoon(湯匙)/ladder(梯子)/jacket(外套)都不能作為討論主題。", "keyPoint": "topic 主題", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H16", "year": null, "no": 16, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "There were so many desserts that I couldn't make a ___.", "options": {"A": "choice", "B": "window", "C": "hammer", "D": "pillow"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：甜點太多了，我無法做出「選擇」。make a choice(做選擇)是固定搭配；window(窗戶)/hammer(鎚子)/pillow(枕頭)都無法用「做」來表達挑選。", "keyPoint": "choice 選擇", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H17", "year": null, "no": 17, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "If you become a ___ of the club, you can enter for free.", "options": {"A": "kitchen", "B": "umbrella", "C": "banana", "D": "member"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：如果你成為社團的「會員」，就可以免費入場。become a member of(成為…的會員)是常見用法；kitchen(廚房)/umbrella(雨傘)/banana(香蕉)都不能「成為」社團的一份子。", "keyPoint": "member 會員", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H18", "year": null, "no": 18, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Many people around the world believe in a ___ who created everything.", "options": {"A": "chair", "B": "river", "C": "god", "D": "pencil"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：世界上許多人相信有一位創造萬物的「上帝」。believe in a god who created everything(相信創造萬物的上帝)符合語意；chair(椅子)/river(河流)/pencil(鉛筆)都不會「創造萬物」被人信仰。", "keyPoint": "god 上帝", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H19", "year": null, "no": 19, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "My grandfather reads the ___ every morning to learn the day's news.", "options": {"A": "newspaper", "B": "banana", "C": "ladder", "D": "blanket"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：我爺爺每天早上讀「報紙」來了解當天的新聞。reads ... to learn the news(閱讀…以了解新聞)明確指向newspaper；banana(香蕉)/ladder(梯子)/blanket(毯子)都無法被閱讀或提供新聞。", "keyPoint": "newspaper 報紙", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H20", "year": null, "no": 20, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "During the war, a ___ destroyed several buildings in the city.", "options": {"A": "flower", "B": "cookie", "C": "sofa", "D": "bomb"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：戰爭期間，一顆「炸彈」摧毀了城裡好幾棟建築物。destroyed several buildings(摧毀好幾棟建築)明確指向bomb的破壞力；flower(花)/cookie(餅乾)/sofa(沙發)都不可能摧毀建築物。", "keyPoint": "bomb 炸彈", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H21", "year": null, "no": 21, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The ___ of the story gave us a hint about what would happen.", "options": {"A": "window", "B": "title", "C": "spoon", "D": "ladder"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：這篇故事的「標題」給了我們關於接下來會發生什麼事的暗示。the title of the story(故事的標題)是常見用法；window(窗戶)/spoon(湯匙)/ladder(梯子)都不能「暗示」故事情節。", "keyPoint": "title 標題", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H22", "year": null, "no": 22, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "After a year of practice, her piano skills reached a very high ___.", "options": {"A": "banana", "B": "umbrella", "C": "level", "D": "chair"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：練習一年後，她的鋼琴技巧達到很高的「水準」。reached a high level(達到高水準)是固定搭配；banana(香蕉)/umbrella(雨傘)/chair(椅子)都不能被「達到」表示技能程度。", "keyPoint": "level 水準", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H23", "year": null, "no": 23, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Please check each ___ on the shopping list before you pay.", "options": {"A": "item", "B": "cloud", "C": "mountain", "D": "river"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：付款前請確認購物清單上的每一「項目」。on the shopping list(在購物清單上)明確指向item；cloud(雲)/mountain(山)/river(河流)都不會出現在購物清單上。", "keyPoint": "item 項目", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H24", "year": null, "no": 24, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The children loved building castles with the wet ___ on the beach.", "options": {"A": "snow", "B": "glass", "C": "paper", "D": "sand"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：孩子們喜歡用海灘上濕的「沙」堆城堡。on the beach(在海灘上)+ building castles(堆城堡)明確指向sand；snow(雪)/glass(玻璃)/paper(紙)都不是海灘上用來堆城堡的材料。", "keyPoint": "sand 沙", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H25", "year": null, "no": 25, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "The number of car accidents is becoming a serious ___ problem in our city.", "options": {"A": "tasty", "B": "social", "C": "sleepy", "D": "salty"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：車禍數量正成為我們城市裡一個嚴重的「社會」問題。social problem(社會問題)是固定搭配；tasty(美味的)/sleepy(想睡的)/salty(鹹的)都與「問題」的性質不符。", "keyPoint": "social 社會的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H26", "year": null, "no": 26, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "Since it's cloudy and windy, it will ___ rain this afternoon.", "options": {"A": "quickly", "B": "loudly", "C": "likely", "D": "softly"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：因為天氣多雲又有風，今天下午「可能」會下雨。will likely rain(可能會下雨)表推測；quickly(快速地)/loudly(大聲地)/softly(輕柔地)都無法表達「可能性」的推測語氣。", "keyPoint": "likely 可能", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H27", "year": null, "no": 27, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "The ___ reason she moved to Taipei was to find a better job.", "options": {"A": "main", "B": "sweet", "C": "noisy", "D": "heavy"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：她搬到台北的「主要」原因是為了找到更好的工作。main reason(主要原因)是常見搭配；sweet(甜的)/noisy(吵鬧的)/heavy(重的)都無法形容「原因」的重要性。", "keyPoint": "main 主要的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H28", "year": null, "no": 28, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "After his friends left, he sat ___ in the empty classroom.", "options": {"A": "early", "B": "loudly", "C": "quickly", "D": "alone"}, "answer": "D", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：朋友離開後，他「獨自」坐在空蕩蕩的教室裡。friends left(朋友離開了)+ empty classroom(空教室)呼應alone(獨自地)；early(早地)/loudly(大聲地)/quickly(快速地)都與句中孤單情境不符。", "keyPoint": "alone 獨自地", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H29", "year": null, "no": 29, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "Be careful! The knife is very ___, so don't touch its edge.", "options": {"A": "heavy", "B": "sharp", "C": "soft", "D": "empty"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「小心！這把刀很___，別碰到刀刃。」刀刃鋒利用 sharp（銳利的）最合理；heavy（重的）、soft（軟的）、empty（空的）都無法形容刀刃的鋒利程度，放入句中不合理。", "keyPoint": "sharp 銳利的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H30", "year": null, "no": 30, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "It was very ___ of the firefighter to run into the burning building to save the cat.", "options": {"A": "brave", "B": "shy", "C": "lazy", "D": "tired"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「消防員衝進燃燒的大樓救貓，真的很___。」做出這種冒險救援的行為應用 brave（勇敢的）；shy（害羞的）、lazy（懶惰的）、tired（疲累的）都不符合英勇救援的情境。", "keyPoint": "brave 勇敢的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H31", "year": null, "no": 31, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "I was so hungry that I ate the ___ pizza by myself.", "options": {"A": "careful", "B": "whole", "C": "narrow", "D": "empty"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「我太餓了，一個人吃掉了___的披薩。」表示「整個」披薩都被吃光要用 whole（整個的）；careful（小心的）、narrow（狹窄的）、empty（空的）皆與吃披薩的份量無關。", "keyPoint": "whole 整個的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H32", "year": null, "no": 32, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "To be ___, I don't think your plan will work.", "options": {"A": "quiet", "B": "careful", "C": "frank", "D": "lucky"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「To be frank」是固定用法，意思是「坦白說」，符合接下來說出真心話（覺得計畫行不通）的語氣；quiet（安靜的）、careful（小心的）、lucky（幸運的）都無法表達「坦白說」的語意。", "keyPoint": "frank 坦白的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H33", "year": null, "no": 33, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "A ___ bit my arm last night, and now it's really itchy.", "options": {"A": "elephant", "B": "mosquito", "C": "dolphin", "D": "rabbit"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「一隻___昨晚咬了我的手臂，現在很癢。」會叮咬人並造成搔癢的是 mosquito（蚊子）；elephant（大象）、dolphin（海豚）、rabbit（兔子）都不會叮咬人使人發癢。", "keyPoint": "mosquito 蚊子", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H34", "year": null, "no": 34, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "My sister just got a cute ___ that likes to chase its own tail.", "options": {"A": "chicken", "B": "goldfish", "C": "puppy", "D": "turtle"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「我妹妹剛養了一隻愛追自己尾巴的可愛___。」會追自己尾巴玩耍的動物是 puppy（小狗）；chicken（雞）、goldfish（金魚）、turtle（烏龜）都不會有這種行為。", "keyPoint": "puppy 小狗", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H35", "year": null, "no": 35, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "Please don't ___ so much food; finish what's on your plate.", "options": {"A": "save", "B": "waste", "C": "cook", "D": "share"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「請不要___那麼多食物，把盤子裡的吃完。」勸人不要浪費食物要用 waste（浪費）；save（節省）、cook（煮）、share（分享）放入句中語意不合理。", "keyPoint": "waste 浪費", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H36", "year": null, "no": 36, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "Vegetable prices usually ___ during typhoon season.", "options": {"A": "fall", "B": "break", "C": "rise", "D": "stop"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「颱風季節時，蔬菜的價格通常會___。」颱風常使菜價上漲，故用 rise（上升）；fall（下降）方向相反，break（打破）、stop（停止）都不符合價格變化的說法。", "keyPoint": "rise 上升", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H37", "year": null, "no": 37, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "We ___ that it will rain tomorrow, so remember to bring an umbrella.", "options": {"A": "forget", "B": "expect", "C": "refuse", "D": "ignore"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「我們___明天會下雨，所以記得帶傘。」對未來的預測要用 expect（預期）；forget（忘記）、refuse（拒絕）、ignore（忽視）都與「預測天氣」的語意不合。", "keyPoint": "expect 期望", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H38", "year": null, "no": 38, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The store is offering a great ___ this weekend: buy one, get one free.", "options": {"A": "mistake", "B": "deal", "C": "secret", "D": "promise"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「這家店這週末推出很棒的___：買一送一。」買一送一是划算的交易，用 deal（交易）；mistake（錯誤）、secret（秘密）、promise（承諾）都不符合商店促銷的情境。", "keyPoint": "deal 交易", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H39", "year": null, "no": 39, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "You don't say much, but you ___ happy today.", "options": {"A": "seem", "B": "hope", "C": "wish", "D": "worry"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「你話不多，但你今天看起來___很開心。」表達從外表判斷的感覺要用 seem（似乎、看起來）；hope（希望）、wish（希望）、worry（擔心）都是說話者自身的心理動作，不能用來形容別人看起來如何。", "keyPoint": "seem 似乎", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H40", "year": null, "no": 40, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "After walking for hours, we finally ___ the top of the mountain.", "options": {"A": "miss", "B": "lose", "C": "reach", "D": "catch"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「走了好幾個小時後，我們終於___山頂。」抵達目的地要用 reach（到達）；miss（錯過）、lose（失去）、catch（抓住）都無法表達「走到、抵達」的意思。", "keyPoint": "reach 到達", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H41", "year": null, "no": 41, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "Can you ___ what the thief looked like to the police officer?", "options": {"A": "describe", "B": "forget", "C": "hide", "D": "copy"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「你能向警察___小偷長什麼樣子嗎？」向他人說明外貌特徵要用 describe（描述）；forget（忘記）、hide（隱藏）、copy（複製）都與「說明外貌」的語意不合。", "keyPoint": "describe 描述", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H42", "year": null, "no": 42, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "The school rules do not ___ students to use their phones during the exam.", "options": {"A": "expect", "B": "allow", "C": "want", "D": "tell"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：校規「不准」學生在考試時使用手機。allow 指「允許、准許」，最符合「規定」語氣（校規只會 allow/禁止，不會 want）。其他選項放進「規則不___學生用手機」都不合理。", "keyPoint": "allow 允許", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H43", "year": null, "no": 43, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "Her parents ___ her to practice the piano every day, even though she really hates it.", "options": {"A": "force", "B": "allow", "C": "invite", "D": "thank"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「即使她很討厭，父母仍___她每天練鋼琴。」表示「強迫」某人做不情願的事要用 force sb. to V；allow（允許）、invite（邀請）、thank（感謝）都與「她很討厭」的語氣矛盾。", "keyPoint": "force 強迫", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H44", "year": null, "no": 44, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "You can buy the concert tickets ___ instead of standing in a long line.", "options": {"A": "outside", "B": "online", "C": "upstairs", "D": "nearby"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「你可以___購買演唱會門票，而不用排長長的隊伍。」不用出門排隊即可購票，指的是「線上」購買，用 online；outside（在外面）、upstairs（在樓上）、nearby（在附近）都與「不用排隊」的意思矛盾。", "keyPoint": "online 在線上", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H45", "year": null, "no": 45, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "You can find more information about the museum on its ___.", "options": {"A": "notebook", "B": "calendar", "C": "website", "D": "newspaper"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「你可以在博物館的___上找到更多資訊。」提供線上資訊的地方是 website（網站）；notebook（筆記本）、calendar（日曆）、newspaper（報紙）都不是博物館提供資訊的常見管道。", "keyPoint": "website 網站", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H46", "year": null, "no": 46, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "She was so interested in the letter that she read it ___ without stopping.", "options": {"A": "through", "B": "along", "C": "down", "D": "away"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「她對這封信很感興趣，所以___不停地讀完。」read something through 表示「從頭讀到尾」；along（沿著）、over（結束／越過）、away（離開）都不能表達「讀完全部」的意思。", "keyPoint": "through 自始至終", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H47", "year": null, "no": 47, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "conj", "stem": "___ I was doing my homework, my little brother was watching TV in the living room.", "options": {"A": "Because", "B": "While", "C": "Unless", "D": "Although"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「___我在做作業的時候，我弟弟在客廳看電視。」表示兩件事同時發生要用 while（當…的時候）；Because（因為）、Unless（除非）、Although（雖然）在邏輯上都不符合「同時發生」的語意。", "keyPoint": "while 當…時候", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H48", "year": null, "no": 48, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "I don't really want to go to the party tonight. ___, I still have a lot of homework to finish.", "options": {"A": "However", "B": "Besides", "C": "Therefore", "D": "Instead"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「我今晚其實不太想去派對。___，我還有很多作業要寫。」用來補充另一個理由要用 Besides（此外）；However（然而，表轉折）、Therefore（因此，表結果）、Instead（取而代之）在邏輯關係上都不吻合。", "keyPoint": "besides 此外", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H49", "year": null, "no": 49, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "pron", "stem": "That red bike is not John's. It's ___ — I got it for my birthday last year.", "options": {"A": "yours", "B": "hers", "C": "mine", "D": "theirs"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「那台紅色腳踏車不是約翰的，它是___的——去年生日我拿到的。」由「我拿到」可知車主是說話者自己，要用所有格代名詞 mine（我的）；yours（你的）、hers（她的）、theirs（他們的）人稱都不符合句意。", "keyPoint": "mine 我的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H50", "year": null, "no": 50, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Look at that big gray ___ in the sky — it might rain soon.", "options": {"A": "star", "B": "cloud", "C": "moon", "D": "rainbow"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「看天上那朵灰色的大___——快下雨了。」會帶來降雨徵兆的是 cloud（雲）；star（星星）、moon（月亮）、rainbow（彩虹）都不會讓人聯想到「快下雨」。", "keyPoint": "cloud 雲", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H51", "year": null, "no": 51, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Hiking in the mountains lets us enjoy the beauty of ___.", "options": {"A": "weather", "B": "nature", "C": "season", "D": "distance"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「爬山讓我們享受___之美。」山林景色所展現的美屬於 nature（大自然）；weather（天氣）、season（季節）、distance（距離）都無法表達「山林景色的美」。", "keyPoint": "nature 大自然", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H52", "year": null, "no": 52, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The loud sound of ___ scared the little dog during the storm.", "options": {"A": "wind", "B": "thunder", "C": "rain", "D": "snow"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「暴風雨中，巨大的___聲嚇壞了那隻小狗。」發出巨大聲響、令動物害怕的自然現象是 thunder（雷）；wind（風）、rain（雨）、snow（雪）通常不會被形容成「loud sound」使動物受驚。", "keyPoint": "thunder 雷", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H53", "year": null, "no": 53, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "This ___ of the city is famous for its old temples and small shops.", "options": {"A": "height", "B": "area", "C": "level", "D": "distance"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「這座城市的這個___以古老的廟宇和小商店聞名。」指城市中的某個「區域」要用 area（地區）；height（高度）、level（水準）、distance（距離）都不能表示「城市中的一塊區域」。", "keyPoint": "area 地區", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H54", "year": null, "no": 54, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The ___ spent three months painting this beautiful picture.", "options": {"A": "driver", "B": "artist", "C": "farmer", "D": "waiter"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「這位___花了三個月畫出這幅美麗的畫。」畫畫的人是 artist（藝術家）；driver（司機）、farmer（農夫）、waiter（服務生）的職業內容都與繪畫無關。", "keyPoint": "artist 藝術家", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H55", "year": null, "no": 55, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The ___ of the small shop knows all his customers by name.", "options": {"A": "owner", "B": "guest", "C": "visitor", "D": "stranger"}, "answer": "A", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「這家小店的___認識所有顧客的名字。」擁有並經營這家店的人是 owner（老闆／物主）；guest（客人）、visitor（訪客）、stranger（陌生人）都不是「經營店家、認識顧客」的角色。", "keyPoint": "owner 物主／老闆", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H56", "year": null, "no": 56, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "He became a famous ___ after starring in that popular movie.", "options": {"A": "painter", "B": "actor", "C": "dancer", "D": "doctor"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「在那部熱門電影中主演之後，他成了知名的___。」在電影中主演的人是 actor（男演員）；painter（畫家）、dancer（舞者）、doctor（醫生）的職業內容都與「電影主演」無關。", "keyPoint": "actor 男演員", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H57", "year": null, "no": 57, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "My father works for a big ___ that makes cars for people all over the world.", "options": {"A": "oven", "B": "company", "C": "height", "D": "diary"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「我爸爸在一間製造汽車的大公司上班。」works for a big ___ that makes cars 表示「在...上班」，只有 company（公司）合理；oven(烤箱)、height(高度)、diary(日記) 都是名詞但放進句子完全不通。", "keyPoint": "company 公司", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H58", "year": null, "no": 58, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "My uncle is a famous ___. He paints beautiful pictures of the sea.", "options": {"A": "actor", "B": "owner", "C": "painter", "D": "visitor"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "第二句「他畫美麗的海景畫」提示職業是畫家 painter；actor(演員)、owner(物主)、visitor(訪客) 雖同為表示人的名詞，但都不會「畫畫」，故不合。", "keyPoint": "painter 畫家", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H59", "year": null, "no": 59, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "v", "stem": "Can you ___ this math problem to me? I don't understand it at all.", "options": {"A": "waste", "B": "explain", "C": "rise", "D": "expect"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "句意：「你可以跟我說明這道數學題嗎？我完全不懂。」explain 表示「說明、解釋」最符合；waste(浪費)、rise(上升)、expect(期望) 放進句子語意都不通。", "keyPoint": "explain 說明", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H60", "year": null, "no": 60, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Every night before bed, Mia writes about her day in her ___.", "options": {"A": "calendar", "B": "diary", "C": "address", "D": "oven"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「每晚睡前把當天的事寫下來」正是寫日記 diary 的行為；calendar(日曆)不能「寫」、address(地址)、oven(烤箱)都不合句意。", "keyPoint": "diary 日記", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H61", "year": null, "no": 61, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "After high school, Tom wants to study medicine at a famous ___.", "options": {"A": "village", "B": "university", "C": "supermarket", "D": "building"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「高中畢業後想讀醫學」暗示是要去 university(大學) 就讀；village(村莊)、supermarket(超市)、building(建築物，泛稱)都不是能「study medicine」的學校機構。", "keyPoint": "university 大學", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H62", "year": null, "no": 62, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "That tall ___ next to the park has more than fifty floors.", "options": {"A": "furniture", "B": "building", "C": "oven", "D": "housework"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「那棟高的___有超過五十層樓」，只有 building(建築物)符合有「樓層」的概念；furniture(傢俱)、oven(烤箱)、housework(家事)都不會有樓層。", "keyPoint": "building 建築物", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H63", "year": null, "no": 63, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "On weekends, I help my mom with the ___, like cleaning and washing dishes.", "options": {"A": "diary", "B": "calendar", "C": "housework", "D": "address"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面舉例「打掃、洗碗」正是家事 housework 的內容；diary(日記)、calendar(日曆)、address(地址)都與打掃洗碗無關。", "keyPoint": "housework 家事", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H64", "year": null, "no": 64, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "We bought new ___ for our living room, like a sofa and a table.", "options": {"A": "oven", "B": "furniture", "C": "diary", "D": "housework"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面舉例「沙發和桌子」正是傢俱 furniture 的例子；oven(烤箱)是家電非傢俱，diary(日記)、housework(家事)也不符合。", "keyPoint": "furniture 傢俱", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H65", "year": null, "no": 65, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Mom put the cake into the ___ to bake it for thirty minutes.", "options": {"A": "address", "B": "oven", "C": "university", "D": "village"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「把蛋糕放進___烤三十分鐘」，只有 oven(烤箱) 能用來烤東西；address(地址)、university(大學)、village(村莊)都不能拿來烤蛋糕。", "keyPoint": "oven 烤箱", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H66", "year": null, "no": 66, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Please write your home ___ on this form so we can send the package to you.", "options": {"A": "height", "B": "calendar", "C": "address", "D": "diary"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「填寫地址以便寄送包裹」提示答案是 address(地址)；height(高度)、calendar(日曆)、diary(日記) 都無法用來寄送包裹。", "keyPoint": "address 地址", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H67", "year": null, "no": 67, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "conj", "stem": "___ it was raining heavily, the players kept playing the game.", "options": {"A": "because", "B": "although", "C": "if", "D": "unless"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前後句意相反（下大雨/球員仍繼續比賽），需用表示「雖然」的連接詞 although 表示讓步；because(因為)是因果、if(如果)是條件、unless(除非)語意都不合。", "keyPoint": "although 雖然", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H68", "year": null, "no": 68, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "I don't want to play video games ___; I'd rather read books now.", "options": {"A": "always", "B": "anymore", "C": "sometimes", "D": "still"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "與否定句連用、句尾放置，表示「不再」某行為，anymore 最合適；always(總是)、sometimes(有時候)、still(仍然)放在此處語意矛盾或不自然。", "keyPoint": "anymore 不再", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H69", "year": null, "no": 69, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "This medicine is ___ used in hospitals all over the world.", "options": {"A": "loudly", "B": "widely", "C": "probably", "D": "actually"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「這種藥在全世界的醫院都被使用」強調使用範圍廣泛，故用 widely(廣泛地)；mostly(主要地)、probably(或許)、actually(確實) 語意不合此處強調「範圍廣」的意思。", "keyPoint": "widely 廣泛地", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H70", "year": null, "no": 70, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "The food at this restaurant is ___ made from local vegetables and fish.", "options": {"A": "widely", "B": "probably", "C": "mostly", "D": "actually"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "強調「主要由當地蔬菜和魚做成」，用 mostly(主要地)最恰當；widely(廣泛地)強調範圍不是比例、probably(或許)表不確定、actually(確實)語意不合。", "keyPoint": "mostly 主要地", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H71", "year": null, "no": 71, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Every summer, thousands of ___ come to see the famous waterfall.", "options": {"A": "owners", "B": "visitors", "C": "ladys", "D": "fools"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「每年夏天有數千名___來看瀑布」，指的是前來參觀的訪客 visitor；owner(物主)、lady(女士)、fool(傻子) 都不符合「來參觀」的語意。", "keyPoint": "visitor 訪客", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H72", "year": null, "no": 72, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The kind old ___ next door often gives us cookies.", "options": {"A": "fool", "B": "owner", "C": "lady", "D": "visitor"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「隔壁善良的老___常給我們餅乾」，用來稱呼一位女性長輩，用 lady(女士)最自然；fool(傻子)、owner(物主)、visitor(訪客) 都不符合語意。", "keyPoint": "lady 女士", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H73", "year": null, "no": 73, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "Don't be a ___ and believe everything strangers tell you online.", "options": {"A": "visitor", "B": "fool", "C": "lady", "D": "owner"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「別當傻子，別輕信網路陌生人說的話」，fool(傻子)符合被勸誡不要犯傻的語境；visitor(訪客)、lady(女士)、owner(物主)都不合。", "keyPoint": "fool 傻子", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H74", "year": null, "no": 74, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "Look at those dark clouds — it will ___ rain later today.", "options": {"A": "actually", "B": "probably", "C": "widely", "D": "mostly"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "看到烏雲推測「等一下大概會下雨」，是不確定的推測語氣，用 probably(或許/大概)最合適；actually(確實)、widely(廣泛地)、mostly(主要地)語意不合此推測情境。", "keyPoint": "probably 或許", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H75", "year": null, "no": 75, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adv", "stem": "I thought the movie would be boring, but it was ___ very exciting.", "options": {"A": "probably", "B": "actually", "C": "widely", "D": "mostly"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "前後語意轉折（原以為無聊，但事實上卻很刺激），用 actually(事實上、確實)表達與預期相反的事實；probably(或許)、widely(廣泛地)、mostly(主要地)都不符合這種轉折語氣。", "keyPoint": "actually 確實", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H76", "year": null, "no": 76, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "She checked the ___ on the wall to find out what day her birthday falls on this year.", "options": {"A": "address", "B": "diary", "C": "calendar", "D": "height"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「查看牆上的___確認生日是星期幾」，只有 calendar(日曆) 能用來查日期；address(地址)、diary(日記)、height(高度)皆不符合查日期的用途。", "keyPoint": "calendar 日曆", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H77", "year": null, "no": 77, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "Our classroom is in the ___ room on the second floor, between two other classrooms.", "options": {"A": "whole", "B": "main", "C": "middle", "D": "social"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "後面說「在另外兩間教室之間」，正是位於中間，故用 middle(中間的)；whole(全體的)、main(主要的)、social(社會的)都不符合「位於兩者之間」的描述。", "keyPoint": "middle 中間的", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H78", "year": null, "no": 78, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "We need eggs and milk, so let's go to the ___ before it closes.", "options": {"A": "university", "B": "supermarket", "C": "village", "D": "building"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「需要買雞蛋和牛奶，去___購買」，只有 supermarket(超市) 能買到這些食品雜貨；university(大學)、village(村莊)、building(建築物，泛稱)都不合適。", "keyPoint": "supermarket 超市", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H79", "year": null, "no": 79, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "My grandparents live in a small ___ in the mountains with only a few hundred people.", "options": {"A": "building", "B": "village", "C": "supermarket", "D": "university"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「住在山裡只有幾百人的小___」正是村莊 village 的描述；building(建築物)、supermarket(超市)、university(大學)都不符合「有幾百位居民」的地方概念。", "keyPoint": "village 村莊", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H80", "year": null, "no": 80, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The old king's ___ made the whole country very sad.", "options": {"A": "flu", "B": "death", "C": "height", "D": "garden"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「老國王的___讓全國都很悲傷」暗示國王過世，即 death(死亡)；flu(流感)、height(高度)、war(戰爭)雖同為名詞，但語意不符合「讓全國悲傷」的直接原因。", "keyPoint": "death 死亡", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H81", "year": null, "no": 81, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "I stayed home from school because I had the ___ and a high fever.", "options": {"A": "war", "B": "death", "C": "flu", "D": "height"}, "answer": "C", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「因為得了___又發高燒而請假在家」，符合症狀描述的是 flu(流感)；war(戰爭)、death(死亡)、height(高度)都與發燒生病無關。", "keyPoint": "flu 流行性感冒", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H82", "year": null, "no": 82, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "n", "stem": "The doctor measured his ___ and weight during the check-up.", "options": {"A": "death", "B": "height", "C": "flu", "D": "war"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "健康檢查時常量的是「身高和體重」，height(高度/身高)最合適；death(死亡)、flu(流感)、war(戰爭)都不是檢查時測量的項目。", "keyPoint": "height 高度", "needsImage": false}, {"id": "H83", "year": null, "no": 83, "section": "難字", "type": "難字", "skill": "adj", "stem": "Be careful swimming here — the water is very ___ near the rocks.", "options": {"A": "sharp", "B": "deep", "C": "brave", "D": "whole"}, "answer": "B", "passageRef": null, "explain": "「這裡游泳要小心，岩石附近的水很___」提示水的深度，用 deep(深的)最合理；sharp(銳利的)、brave(勇敢的)、whole(全體的)都不能形容水。", "keyPoint": "deep 深的", "needsImage": false}], "passages": [{"pid": "115-P1", "year": 115, "genre": "說明文/食譜", "topic": "自製水果茶做法", "text": "The Best Fruit Tea You Can Make at Home\n(A recipe brochure showing how to make fruit tea at home using fruit such as apples, bananas, oranges, papayas, pears, and strawberries; boil water, add teabags, add fruit and lemon juice, stir, and let steep before removing the fruit.)\n※ stir 攪拌"}, {"pid": "115-P2", "year": 115, "genre": "對話/漫畫", "topic": "Hawkins 屢次失敗卻總是過度自信", "text": "In 6th grade, I tried to get the students to pick me as student leader.\n\"I'll make class hours shorter. And we'll have only three days of school a week…\"\nI totally bombed it.\n\"What? That's not what a student leader can decide. He doesn't know anything.\"\nI was the best choice, but why didn't people know that?\n\nI became a salesperson when I was 23, and I believed I could be Number 1.\n\"You said you would sell 50 cars a month. But you sold only 1 car in two months.\"\n\"Don't worry. I'll sell 149 cars next month.\"\n\"You said that a year ago.\"\nI bombed it again.\n\"Hawkins, we don't need your service anymore. Go pack your things…\"\n\"Why?\""}, {"pid": "115-P3", "year": 115, "genre": "廣告DM/公告通知", "topic": "The Marigolds' Home 參觀宣傳手冊", "text": "The Marigolds' Home\nOpening times: March to October 10:00-17:00, November to February 10:00-16:00. Closed on Mondays.\nTo make sure you enjoy your visit to The Marigolds' Home, we'd like to ask you to follow the rules below:\n1. Pets are not allowed in any areas of the Marigolds' Home.\n2. Eating and drinking are not allowed inside the buildings, except in the café.\n3. Picture-taking is not allowed inside Sir Archie's House.\n4. Please take off your shoes before entering the Rabbit's Temple.\nBecome a member and save 10% on tickets and 30% on all items in the gift shops. To join, visit www.themarigoldshome.com.\n※ brochure 宣傳手冊"}, {"pid": "115-P4", "year": 115, "genre": "記敘文/新聞報導", "topic": "大提琴家 Beatrice Harrison 與夜鶯共演的故事", "text": "One summer evening when English cello player Beatrice Harrison was practicing in her garden, she was joined by a visitor she did not expect.\nThe visitor was a nightingale. The small brown bird sang together with Harrison's cello music, and the birdsong sounded like the piece she was playing. For the next few evenings, her visitor kept coming back, sometimes with several of its friends. Harrison decided that more people should hear the little singers.\nSo, on May 19, 1924, Harrison worked with the BBC, the UK's national TV and radio station, and played in her garden. At first, the artist was playing alone. Fifteen minutes before the end of her playing, the nightingales began to sing with the cello.\nThe nightingale show was popular with radio listeners. It was repeated the next week, and for the next twelve years Harrison played on the radio with her garden friends. During this time, she got 50,000 fan letters. People called her \"the Nightingale Lady.\""}, {"pid": "115-P5", "year": 115, "genre": "記敘文/悼詞", "topic": "悼念電影文章作家 Rose Lacey", "text": "With heavy hearts, we are here to say goodbye to Rose Lacey, a wonderful writer who will be sadly missed.\nRose and I first met in 2010. I was at a party to pick up my wife when I heard Rose explaining to her and her friends why Get Across was a great movie. Her ideas were so interesting that I invited her to write some articles about movies for Action! US. Rose was very excited and agreed right away.\nOver the next ten years, Rose wrote more than 150 articles. Rose could always bring out something new from movies that we thought we knew so well. People often told me that Rose never failed to surprise them. Her articles often made them think whether they actually saw the same movie, but if they went to see it again, they experienced the movie in a whole new way.\nIn her short life of 40 years, Rose has made her mark on the world of movies with her articles for Action! US. We are lucky to have had her in our lives. She was a very special person.\nAlex Jackson\nHead of Action! US\n※ article 文章"}, {"pid": "115-P6", "year": 115, "genre": "說明文/圖表(流程圖)", "topic": "海玻璃的形成過程", "text": "SEA GLASS: GLASS BOTTLES' SECOND LIFE\nSea glass is made from the magic of the sea. It usually comes from glass bottles that are thrown into the water. Each piece of sea glass looks different, and sea glass is often seen on art pieces. The pictures below explain how sea glass is born.\n1. Glass bottles are thrown as garbage into the sea.\n2. When these bottles ride the waves of the sea, they hit each other or other garbage in the sea and break into small pieces of glass.\n3. Pieces of glass are pushed by sea water and move along the sea floor. The sharp pieces slowly become rounder and rounder.\n4. After tens or hundreds of years in the sea, the pieces of glass grow an ice-like white color on the outside and become sea glass.\n5. Sea glass is finally pushed up to the beach.\n6. Artists collect pieces of sea glass and put them into their works.\nHowever, people now seldom use glass to make bottles and bowls—paper bowls and cups have become more popular these days. This means there are fewer glass items in the sea, so less and less sea glass will be found in the future.\n※ title 標題"}, {"pid": "115-P7", "year": 115, "genre": "說明文/新聞評論(對照兩篇)", "topic": "冰島語的未來（兩篇對立觀點文章）", "text": "The Future of Icelandic — Scandinavian News, by Anna Adams\nIcelandic is a language that is spoken only in Iceland. It has a long history. But many Icelanders are worried that they're losing Icelandic.\nThe reason for their worry is the prevalence of English in Iceland. \"I use English when I talk to my housework robot, use my phone, and watch movies,\" said Helgi Atlason, an engineer. There is a reason for that. Most of these products use English, and few companies care to change the language into Icelandic because there are only a small number of Icelandic speakers (314,000 people). Actually, you see English everywhere in Iceland.\nIcelanders also speak and hear more English than Icelandic these days because many foreigners who come to live and work in Iceland speak only English. \"We can't use Icelandic abroad, and we're not using it much in Iceland, either. How do you expect our kids will want to learn it?\" said Eirikur Wilson, a teacher.\nWill Iceland one day give up Icelandic for English? It may happen soon.\n\nOur Future with Icelandic — Scandinavian News, by Gunnar Eggertsson\nMany people think Icelandic is a language in its sickbed and that it needs to be saved. I understand their worries, but does the future of our language really look that bad?\nAccording to Dr. David Clingingsmith, a language needs at least 35,000 speakers to be \"safe\" from becoming a dying language. There are now 314,000 Icelandic speakers. Also, every year Iceland spends 51.3 million Icelandic crowns (3.7 million US dollars) teaching Icelandic to machines: phones, computers, and robots. Icelandic is appearing more often in products. Most importantly, schools still teach Icelandic to children. Clearly, we are not giving up our first language.\nHowever, I'm not saying that Iceland has done enough for Icelandic. Our country can do a better job at getting more people to speak this beautiful language. One way to do so is to give more language courses to foreigners. With much more work, I'm sure Icelandic can grow and even reach farther into the world.\n※ Icelander 冰島人　product 商品"}, {"pid": "115-P8", "year": 115, "genre": "記敘文/故事", "topic": "老國王以種子考驗孩子選出誠實繼承人", "text": "A long time ago, there was an old king who had no child of his own. The king was worried that his land would fall into the wrong hands after his death, so he decided to pick a child in his land to take the high seat. One day, he called all the children to his castle and gave each of them a seed. \"Come back on New Year's Day and show me what you have grown,\" he said to them, \"and I will 40 .\" Every child brought their seeds home carefully. One of the children, Wong, planted his seed in a pot. He gave it water every day and made sure there was sun to help it grow. 41 . Then, Sung, the child of the richest family in the land, told people that a small plant was growing from his seed. He was 42 . Everyone excitedly said that he would be king. Soon, one after another, more and more children were also saying that they had something in their pots. But Wong still didn't find anything in his. On the big day, when Wong brought his pot to the castle, he saw all the other children carrying interesting plants. Some had flowers in the shape of a bird, and some had grasses of different colors. Everyone proudly showed their plants to the king, but the king looked unhappy until he saw Wong's pot. \"I boiled the seeds before I gave them out, so no plants could grow from them.\" The king looked seriously at the children. \"There is only one child who is 43 enough to be king.\" Ten years later, the king died. On his deathbed, he was not worried because he knew Wong would be a good king."}, {"pid": "114-P1", "year": 114, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "學校旁麵包店的狗 Rex 被車撞傷後，大家陪伴牠復原的故事", "text": "Rex is a dog that lives at the bakery next to our school. He is cute and friendly. Every morning, he stands in front of the school to welcome everybody. We all see Rex as one of us. But one Monday morning, I was surprised that Rex was not there to say hello to us. “Rex is in the hospital. He was hit by a car last night,” my classmate told me. We went to see Rex in the hospital that day after school. Two weeks later, Rex was much better, and we decided to take him for a walk every evening. Because of the exercise, Rex became healthier and stronger. Soon he could happily run and jump again. He is now as handsome and strong as before!"}, {"pid": "114-P2", "year": 114, "genre": "對話", "topic": "關於 Mark、Linda 與 Jenny 之間狀況的對話（原文為對話框圖像，PDF文字擷取時對話內容遺失，僅保留題目）", "text": "[說明：此篇為對話框（圖像）形式的題組，pdftotext 轉檔時僅擷取到題號與題目，未能擷取對話框內的實際對白文字，原始對話內容缺失。]"}, {"pid": "114-P3", "year": 114, "genre": "廣告DM/圖表(票券/地圖)", "topic": "White Lake City 交通票卡（White Lake City Card）的種類、票價與使用規則", "text": "Buy a White Lake City Card When You’re in the City\nWith any of the Cards, you can\n- visit the city by metro, bus, or train as many times as you want. *\n- take one child under 12 with you for free.\n- save 20% on tickets to public museums.\nThe 1-day, 3-day, and 5-day Cards are for trips from Monday to Friday, and the Weekend Card is for trips on weekends and holidays.\nCheck the map and buy the right Card for the zones you’ll be entering.\n\nCard / Zone 1 / Zones 1-2 / Zones 1-3\n1-day: $20 / $40 / $60\n3-day: $40 / $60 / $80\n5-day: $50 / $80 / $110\nWeekend: $30 / $50 / $80\n\n* The Cards are only for trips inside the three zones.\n\nⓐ White Lake Main Station ⓑ Museum of White Lake City History ⓒ Museum of Modern Art ⓓ White Lake ⓔ White Lake Castle ⓕ White Lake Airport"}, {"pid": "114-P4", "year": 114, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "16歲少女 Libby Larson 在家族經營的 Rolling Acres 度假農場工作的故事", "text": "At 5 o’clock every morning, while most people are sleeping, 16-year-old Libby Larson is already up. She mops the floor, gets the mail and the newspapers, and gets ready for visitors to Rolling Acres. Libby’s grandparents started Rolling Acres in 1970, and since then all of the Larson family have been working there. Rolling Acres used to be just a sheep farm, but now, with its fruit trees, vegetable gardens, and many other kinds of animals, it has become a popular place for families to go on vacation. Visitors can pick fruits, collect eggs, and feed the animals. It is one of Libby’s jobs to show kids how to feed the baby sheep.\nFor her work, Libby is paid $10 an hour. This summer, she expects to make about $1,200 and plans to buy a cell phone. Her friends think it’s great to make that much money in a summer. However, for Libby, working at a family business also means making sacrifices. “I’d love to sleep until noon or go to summer camp like other kids. My friends stopped inviting me on trips because I’m always busy in the summer.” However, Libby also said, “But it’s better to see both sides. Working with your family is great. You feel closer to each other.”"}, {"pid": "114-P5", "year": 114, "genre": "漫畫", "topic": "以復活節島（Easter Island）為喻，說明過度砍伐樹木導致文明衰亡，藉此呼籲珍惜地球資源", "text": "Around the year 400, people came to Easter Island. So many trees here!\nThey used trees to make fire and build houses. Because of the trees, people had a great life on the island.\nIn their free time, they loved making statues with big rocks. With the trees they cut down, they could move the statues around easily.\nTrees were needed and used in every part of their life. Years passed, and there were fewer and fewer trees on Easter Island.\nWithout enough trees to keep water under the ground, the land became dry, and plants didn’t grow.\nAnd I’m hungry. I’m thirsty.\nPeople began to fight for water and food. The statues were moved to fighting grounds to show their power. The last trees were probably cut down at this time.\nThose who cut down the last trees surely understood how important trees were to them—but still, they did it. When the last trees fell to the ground, people on the island fell, too.\nLet’s not make Earth, our only home, another Easter Island."}, {"pid": "114-P6", "year": 114, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "行為經濟學家 Dan Ariely 以 IKEA 家具和摺紙實驗，說明人們對親手製作之物會產生更高評價的「IKEA效應」", "text": "Many years ago, Dan Ariely bought a cabinet from IKEA. IKEA is a famous furniture store that sells boxes of furniture parts. People who buy them have to put all the parts together themselves. It took Ariely hours to build his cabinet. Ariely didn’t really enjoy himself when he was trying to put all the parts together. However, after he finished, he felt quite good about himself and his cabinet. Later, he found that he loved his cabinet more than any of his other furniture.\nAriely wanted to know if anyone shared his feelings, so he did a fun origami study. He invited two groups of people to join his study. He called one group “builders” and the other group “buyers.” Builders were told to make origami, like paper frogs or paper birds. When they finished, they were asked how much they would spend on their works. Ariely then showed the origami to buyers and asked them how much they would pay for them. The two groups gave very different answers. Though buyers would pay only five cents for builders’ origami, builders would spend 25 cents! Interestingly, builders believed others would think their works were good enough to cost that much money! Ariely’s study showed that he was not alone in his IKEA experience — we just love things more, sometimes blindly, when we make them ourselves. Ariely called it “the IKEA effect.”"}, {"pid": "114-P7", "year": 114, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "1970年代英國電力工人兩度罷工要求加薪、政府因應限電，以及當時社會大眾對此事件觀感的歷史故事", "text": "In the picture is a UK electricity worker in the 1970s. Pictures like this appeared in many newspapers at the time. In 1972, electricity workers in the UK asked to be paid more, and they decided to stop working until their wish was answered. The government worried that there wouldn’t be enough electricity for the country if these workers didn’t go to work, so it agreed to give them the pay rise. However, the story didn’t end there.\nA year later, the electricity workers asked for another pay rise. To get what they wanted, they worked shorter hours and acted like they would walk away from their job anytime. But this time, the government decided to fight. To save electricity, it made new rules for people to follow. For example, each family could turn on the heat in only one room; TV stations had to stop their shows at 10:30 p.m.; businesses could open only three days a week.\nPeople’s lives were greatly changed. Without enough heat to keep the house warm, people covered themselves in blankets all the time. Hospitals had to use candles because they couldn’t keep all the lights on. Factories couldn’t keep their machines working. Many people lost their jobs. For months, people were paying the price while the electricity workers were fighting for their wish. In the end, the government agreed to the second pay rise. This picture shows what many people thought of the electricity workers during the “dark” time."}, {"pid": "114-P8", "year": 114, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "少年 Cameron 每年生日反而親手做禮物感謝媽媽生養之恩的故事（綜合填空）", "text": "Most kids want gifts from their parents on their birthdays, but Cameron doesn’t. On his birthday, he gives his mom a gift. He ___38___ doing this in his first year of junior high school. That year, during one class, he watched a video about how a baby is pushed from its mother’s body. After class, ___39___ . How brave a woman is to have a baby! Thank God I’ll never have to do that!\nWhen Cameron came home that day, he held his mom in his arms for a long time. He decided that his birthday ___40___ . During those nine months inside his mom, he just ate and slept while his mom was doing all the hard work. So why should he get a birthday gift for doing nothing? If anyone should get a gift on his birthday, it should be his mom.\nThe ___41___ “birthday gift” Cameron prepared was a bag of cookies he baked. The cookies tasted so bad, but his mom said they were the best thing she ever got. Hearing that ___42___ . It was so much better than getting a gift. Now, on his birthday every year, Cameron makes a gift for his mother to thank her for giving him life.\nThis year, Cameron ___43___ his mom a nice dress. A few months ago, he learned to make dresses at school and decided to make one for his mom. Now the dress is finished and hanging behind Cameron’s bedroom door. He believes the gift will tell his mother how much he loves her."}, {"pid": "113-P1", "year": 113, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "男孩帶弟弟外出買食物，返家時父親被誤認為闖空門", "text": "It was around eight o'clock on Saturday night. Philip was at home with his little brother, Jason. Jason was hungry and kept crying. But Philip couldn't cook and their father was not home yet because he was working late in the office. So Philip decided to take Jason out for some food.\nHalf an hour later, when they came back home, Philip was surprised to find that their father was talking to the police and a woman outside their house. He didn't know who the woman was. She looked scared and stood behind the police. Philip's father was very angry and kept shouting, \"I didn't do anything wrong! I forgot my keys and was just trying to get into MY OWN HOUSE!\" But the police didn't believe him until Philip ran to them and explained everything.\nThe police told Philip that the woman called 110 when she saw Philip's father trying to get into a house through a window. That was how it all happened."}, {"pid": "113-P2", "year": 113, "genre": "圖表(時刻表/菜單)", "topic": "Baker's Kitchen 麵包店的販售時間表", "text": "[圖表題：Baker's Kitchen 麵包店的營業與各式麵包（白麵包、農場麵包、貝果、猶太辮子麵包）供應時刻表，原文為圖片，PDF文字擷取僅保留註解 oven 烤爐]"}, {"pid": "113-P3", "year": 113, "genre": "圖表(地圖)", "topic": "音樂季/市集會場地圖與交通資訊", "text": "[圖表題：音樂季會場地圖，標示 Satyr's Park、Fox Street、Garden Square、農夫市集、花卉市集、公車路線 No.157、Puppy Street、Koala Street 捷運站等地點與交通建議，原文為地圖圖片，PDF文字擷取僅保留註解 recommend 推薦]"}, {"pid": "113-P4", "year": 113, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "兩則關於待客小氣的幽默故事（Yan與Chang）", "text": "Yan lived a good life in a big house. One day he invited a friend to dinner at his house. However, on the dinner table there was only one small dish of one small fish.\nThe friend looked quietly at the fish. It was no bigger than a finger. Then he asked Yan if he could borrow a lamp.\n\"What for?\" Yan asked. \"Well, it's so dark in here,\" the friend said with a dry smile, \"I can't see the other delicious dishes you've prepared for me.\"\n\nChang kept a lot of ducks and chickens on his farm. One day, his best friend came to visit him. At noon, Chang told his friend that he couldn't let him stay for lunch because there wasn't much food to eat. The friend looked out at Chang's farm animals for a moment. Then he asked Chang if he had a big knife.\n\"Yes, but what for?\" Chang asked. \"I'm thinking about killing the horse I rode here so we'll have something for lunch,\" the friend said. \"But how are you going to go home without it?\" \"Well, you wouldn't mind lending me one of your many ducks or chickens so I can ride it home, would you?\""}, {"pid": "113-P5", "year": 113, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "修書師傅陳彥宏(Chen Bing-Hong)與書店Cotoha的故事", "text": "Usually, people visit bookstores to buy books. But those who walk into Cotoha come to see its owner, Chen Bing-Hong. They bring him books with different problems. Some have lost their covers, some are missing a few pages, and some have pages that are falling out. Chen can always fix the books and make them whole again.\nChen sees himself as a doctor. He says that books, like people, get sick and need help. In Taiwan, there are not many \"doctors\" like him, and most of them work for big libraries and museums. If big libraries and museums are hospitals, Chen's bookstore is a health center. Big libraries and museums fix important old books with serious problems, and Chen helps people with books that have smaller problems. However, the smaller size of the problems doesn't mean Chen's job is less important.\nChen gave an example of a science book he once worked on. It was very old and half of its cover was lost. Its owner still wanted to keep it because it was a gift from a teacher who helped him follow his dream of studying science. When he got his book back, he was very surprised at the new-old book. He felt he was brought back to the days with his teacher. Seeing the owner's smile made Chen happy, because smiles like that are what his magic is for."}, {"pid": "113-P6", "year": 113, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "奧地利敘利亞難民合開的餐廳 Habibi & Hawara", "text": "A Delicious Surprise and Welcome Change\nBy Karl Falk, June 1, 2016\nIn Austria, there are not many restaurants like Habibi & Hawara. Here you can enjoy Austrian and Syrian food together. Two Austrians, Martin Rohla and David Kreytenberg, started this yummy plan from their experience of working with refugees. Every year, thousands of people have to leave their homes and families because of war in their countries. So many of them go to Austria that some people in the country think they have become a problem. They are afraid refugees may take away their jobs and they don't feel safe around them, either. But Rohla and Kreytenberg would beg to differ: The refugees don't have to be a problem. They want to help them start a new life. They invited refugees to meetings and found that some of them were cooks back in Syria. So the idea of Habibi & Hawara was born—a restaurant that brings together Austrian and Syrian food. \"The two worlds far away from each other meet together,\" Kreytenberg said. But Rohla and Kreytenberg want to do more than just give the refugees work. They want their best workers to buy the restaurant in the end. They hope that Habibi & Hawara is not just a one-time plan and that other Austrians will join them and help more refugees."}, {"pid": "113-P7", "year": 113, "genre": "書信/網頁貼文", "topic": "讀者對 John Smith 復活絕種動物一書的評論", "text": "VOICES OF PEOPLE\nEllen Zimmer\nIf you want to learn about bringing back extinct animals, reading John Smith's Back from the Dead is a good start. But I have to say I can't agree with everything he says.\nFrom his book, I can see Smith is an advocate of bringing extinct animals back. He says we have lost many animals because we made their living spaces too dirty. He also thinks we must do everything we can to bring them back. However, I don't know how much time and money we would need to make the world a better place for them, and honestly no one knows if they could actually come back.\nSmith also says that bringing back extinct animals may be good for us. He talks about an extinct frog that grew tadpoles in its stomach. Some women's babies die before they are born, and Smith believes bringing back the frog may be an answer to the problem. According to him, by studying how the tadpoles grow inside the frog's stomach, we might be able to find new ways to help these women successfully keep their babies. But I don't think things are as easy as Smith thinks. We have spent ten years and millions of dollars on this kind of frog, but all we have got are only a few dead frog eggs. If we can't see a real frog, how can we be sure women will get the help they need?\nDr. Solomon Wang from the Animal Saving Office says the study of bringing back extinct animals is \"throwing good money after bad.\" And he's right. A lot of hard work has been put into this expensive dream, but we haven't seen anything come out of it. So should we still keep going down this road?"}, {"pid": "113-P8", "year": 113, "genre": "說明文/圖表", "topic": "1918流感大流行中社交距離措施的成效(附城市死亡率圖表)", "text": "A HISTORY LESSON ON THE PANDEMIC 2020.10.29\nSince the Covid-19 pandemic started, people have begun \"social distancing\"— keeping a safe space between you and anyone you don't live with. Though it has been a very popular topic this year, social distancing 40 . In fact, it was widely used in the U.S. in the flu pandemic in 1918. But how well did it work? The Americans' experience can tell us whether it really saved lives.\nFrom the picture, we can see that 41 started social distancing earlier than the other three cities. This helped the city keep the number of deaths down. Besides taking early action, keeping the action long enough was also important in fighting the pandemic. The picture shows that Portland and Denver did well in the first few weeks. However, both cities 42 , and the numbers of deaths climbed again.\nBut there was one thing Portland did right. The city used several ways of social distancing at the same time to deal with the pandemic. 43 , sick people were kept away from healthy ones; schools were closed; public activities were not allowed. All these were useful in keeping people safe.\nThe lessons of the 1918 pandemic bring us hope. While we are still learning to fight Covid-19, social distancing may be the best way to get us through the dark days, at least for now.\n[附有各城市死亡率隨時間變化的統計圖表，原文為圖片]"}, {"pid": "112-P1", "year": 112, "genre": "圖表(菜單/優惠訊息)", "topic": "Four Seasons' Kitchen 餐廳菜單、集點兌換與營業月曆", "text": "[原始題本為菜單價目表與八月營業月曆之圖表，pdftotext僅擷取到詞彙註解「calendar 月曆」，價目與月曆表格內容因圖片排版未能完整擷取為文字。] 題目敘述：Amy went to Four Seasons' Kitchen with her mother after she collected 15 stars. They ordered two Garden Sandwiches, an Autumn Wind, and a Winter Snow. Amy wants to bring her friends to Four Seasons' Kitchen in August. She looks at her calendar to pick a time to go there."}, {"pid": "112-P2", "year": 112, "genre": "公告notice/說明文", "topic": "如何協助落巢的幼鳥", "text": "[原始題本為一則提醒民眾如何處理離巢幼鳥的圖文告示，pdftotext僅擷取到詞彙註解「nest 鳥巢」「feather 羽毛」，告示本文因圖片排版未能完整擷取為文字。] 題目線索：告示內容涉及幼鳥受傷與否、羽毛多寡時應如何處理（送醫、放回巢中、聯絡動物中心等），以及親鳥對沾有人類氣味幼鳥的反應。"}, {"pid": "112-P3", "year": 112, "genre": "圖表(統計圖表)", "topic": "全球食物生產各階段的浪費比例", "text": "[原始題本為比較歐洲、北美與大洋洲、南亞與東南亞三地區在食物生產五個階段(Stage 1-5)食物浪費百分比的統計圖表，pdftotext僅擷取到詞彙註解「stage 階段」「waste 浪費」「percentage 百分比」，圖表數據因圖片排版未能完整擷取為文字。]"}, {"pid": "112-P4", "year": 112, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "蚊子如何在下雨時存活", "text": "Sometimes when the rain falls hard and fast on you, it might hurt a little. But what happens when it hits a mosquito? A 2012 study says when a raindrop falls on a mosquito, it's like when a bus hits a person. Besides, the little insect is hit by a raindrop about once every 20 seconds. So why don't we see many dead mosquitoes after it rains?\nA mosquito is as big as a raindrop, but it is much lighter — 0.002 g only. This saves its life in raindrop attacks. Because the mosquito is so light, when it is hit by a raindrop, it won't experience a force that is strong enough to kill it.\nThe study also found that when a mosquito is hit by a raindrop, the insect is pushed by the raindrop and falls together with it. But the mosquito doesn't get wet easily because it is covered with hairs which keep off water. After dropping about 6 cm, it will roll off the raindrop and fly away.\nHowever, this trick isn't always successful. If the mosquito flies too low when it is hit by the raindrop, it won't have time to fly off. Then it will hit the ground and meet its death.\n(force 力量)"}, {"pid": "112-P5", "year": 112, "genre": "說明文/人物介紹", "topic": "貝多芬鋼琴曲《給愛麗絲》中「愛麗絲」身分之謎", "text": "You probably have heard Beethoven's famous piano piece \"For Elise,\" but do you know who \"Elise\" was?\nOne story is that Elise was Elisabeth Röckel. She once sang in Beethoven's opera Fidelio, and the two became very good friends. Beethoven called her \"Elise.\" When Röckel was leaving the city of Vienna, Beethoven wrote \"For Elise\" to say goodbye to her. Another story is that Elise was Therese Malfatti. Beethoven was in love with her. He wrote a piece for her and put \"For Therese\" on the manuscript. Malfatti kept the manuscript and left it to her family when she died. Later, a man copied the manuscript and wrote \"For Elise\" by mistake. There is another possible Elise: Elise Barensfeld. She learned the piano from Malfatti, the same Malfatti in the second story. To help Malfatti, Beethoven wrote the piece for her to use to teach Barensfeld.\nThese are just some guesses about who Elise was. We may never know the right answer.\nNo one knew about the piece until 1867, when the manuscript was found. This was 40 years after Beethoven's death, so he wasn't around to tell us who Elise was. Only one thing is for sure: \"For Elise\" will always be enjoyed.\n(opera 歌劇 manuscript 手稿)"}, {"pid": "112-P6", "year": 112, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "玩具選擇與性別刻板印象", "text": "Which would you give a boy for his birthday, a toy truck or a doll? If you choose the truck, well, you're not alone. Most people think that some toys are for boys and some are for girls. We might pick building toys for boys and kitchen toys for girls. But why do we do this? Are boys and girls really born with different interests in toys?\nNo, they are not. Children start to show different interests in toys at age three, but only because at this time, they begin to learn about gender and to follow what others of their gender do. If you give a girl kitchen toys, she will think they are girls' toys because she sees other girls playing with them. But if you give a girl a toy car and show her a group of girls who are playing with cars, she'll play with the toy car and think it is a girls' toy. This \"watch and follow\" habit often becomes a rule for both boys and girls in choosing the \"right\" toys.\nHowever, this rule can be bad for children. Different toys teach children different things. Dolls help with their early language use, and building toys are good for learning math and science. By playing with different toys, children can find out what they are interested in or what they are good at. If they only play one kind of toy, they may lose this important chance. They may also get a wrong idea about what boys or girls are able to do. Some doctors worry that children may use the same kind of thinking when they look for jobs in the future. If they do, they may miss something more important than just getting a chance to play with different toys. They may miss many, perhaps better, chances in life.\n(gender 性別)"}, {"pid": "112-P7", "year": 112, "genre": "記敘文/人物傳記", "topic": "戰地記者Marie Colvin的生平", "text": "Marie Colvin was a world-famous war reporter. She was born in New York, USA, in 1956 and died in Homs, Syria, in 2012. When she was a student at Yale University, Colvin decided that she wanted to be a reporter in the future. She joined the Sunday Times, a UK newspaper, in 1985 and soon became its Middle East reporter. Besides the Middle East, she also reported from other parts of the world: Chechnya, Kosovo and Sri Lanka, for example. When she was reporting on the war in Sri Lanka, she lost her left eye. But that never stopped her. She still went to dangerous places that few reporters wanted to visit and stayed when others left.\nColvin showed great empathy in her stories. For her, war reporting was not just some quick interviews and a few photos. She wrote about real people and their real lives. Her writing made you feel so strongly about these people's stories, just like they were your own. She hoped that through her work the world would understand what really happened in war, and would take action to stop the fighting.\nOn February 22, 2012, the day after she gave her report on the war in Homs, Colvin was killed when the house she was staying in was attacked. She always knew what price a war reporter might have to pay. She already lost an eye before. This time, she gave her life to the work she could not give up — telling the true stories to the world.\n(war 戰爭)"}, {"pid": "112-P8", "year": 112, "genre": "網頁貼文/書評", "topic": "《Speaking American》一書談美式英語各地用詞差異", "text": "Speaking American is a great book! Lucia Leisure ★★★★★\nI just love Josh Katz's new book! It's about ___(42)___ in different parts of the US. The information in the book was collected from the quiz that Katz built on the website in 2013. The quiz asked what words people use for something, and their answers showed interesting facts. For example, there are different names for sports shoes. In most parts of the US, people say \"tennis shoes.\" In the northeast of the country, people wear \"sneakers.\" In some towns, \"tennis shoes\" and \"sneakers\" become \"gym shoes.\"\nThe use of words tells us where people are from, like Katz's book says. But in my experience, it also shows ___(43)___. My family has lived in New York since my grandparents. It's not surprising that I say \"sneakers.\" But my grandfather says \"plimsolls,\" and my daughter says \"kicks\" or \"vans.\" Maybe Katz can study this difference for his next book.\n(website 網站)"}, {"pid": "111-P1", "year": 111, "genre": "廣告DM", "topic": "Tea-Rock 20週年紀念明信片", "text": "(此篇為圖像式明信片廣告，原始PDF文字抽取僅保留註解 \"address 地址\"，明信片圖片內容未能以純文字擷取。內容大意：Tea-Rock茶飲品牌慶祝其20週年，並附上一張要寄給Tea-Rock 20的明信片圖樣，圖上有杯子圖案及待填寫的個人資料欄位。)"}, {"pid": "111-P2", "year": 111, "genre": "圖表(統計圖)", "topic": "糖分攝取資訊圖表 (infographic)", "text": "Below is an infographic. (此篇為資訊圖表(infographic)，內容以圖像呈現各種食物/飲料中隱藏的糖分含量比較，原始PDF文字抽取僅保留說明文字 \"Below is an infographic.\" 及註解 \"infographic 資訊圖表\"，圖表數據本身未能以純文字擷取。)"}, {"pid": "111-P3", "year": 111, "genre": "對話", "topic": "Darrell建議Marina使用Pinterest尋找靈感", "text": "Darrell: Marina…Marina…MARINA!\nMarina: Oh, sorry. I didn't hear you. I was thinking about my homework.\nDarrell: What's it about?\nMarina: Well, I need to draw a future house for my art class, but I haven't got any ideas. Maybe I should go to the library and look for something useful.\nDarrell: Or you can try Pinterest.\nMarina: Isn't it a shopping app?\nDarrell: Not really. Many people share their works on Pinterest and tell you how they made them. I'm sure you can get some ideas there.\nMarina: Sounds like you use it often.\nDarrell: Yeah. Just last week I went there and found the A to Z of making chocolate cake—from choosing good chocolate to baking the cake to making sugar flowers on top.\nMarina: Really? I'll check it out later. Thanks a lot."}, {"pid": "111-P4", "year": 111, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "Tabata訓練法介紹", "text": "Tabata training is a very popular way of exercising these days. It doesn't take much time or space, and it burns calories faster than other ways of exercising. The idea of Tabata training is simple: exercise for 20 seconds, rest for 10 seconds, and then repeat (at least eight times). The moves for the 20-second exercise are not difficult to learn. Jumping jacks, high knees, squats, and planks are some of the most common moves. You can decide yourself what moves to do in your Tabata training. For example, you can do more leg exercises if you want strong legs.\n\nOne great thing about Tabata training is that your body will keep burning calories for at least an hour after 4 minutes of Tabata training. But to have this wonderful \"afterburn,\" you need to exercise really hard during each 20 seconds. If you seldom exercise or have heart problems, this exercise may not be good for you. But for people who enjoy exercising but are too busy to go to the gym, Tabata training might just be the answer.\n\n(calorie 卡路里(熱量單位); paragraph 段落)"}, {"pid": "111-P5", "year": 111, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "無加班日(No Overtime Day)與長工時問題報導", "text": "The problem of long working hours is a real headache in our country. It kills many people every year (see Figure 1), and many companies are trying to change that. They have at least one \"No Overtime Day\" in a week, and it is often Wednesday. On \"No Overtime Day,\" workers are asked to leave their offices before 8 p.m. At 8 p.m., companies play the song \"There's Always Tomorrow\" and turn off all the lights.\n\nHowever, after the workers walk out of their offices, they don't go home. Some go back later, turn on their table lamps, and keep working, and others find somewhere else to work until very late at night. Restaurants and coffee shops are busier on Wednesday evenings, and they have started selling drinks and meals for these workers.\n\nBut why do these people keep working? A study shows that workers who work more hours often have a bigger chance to get paid more and rise higher in their companies. This is true for both men and women (see Figure 2). Working long hours has become a way to show that people are hard-working. Clearly, this must be changed before the problem gets any worse.\n\n(Figure 1, Figure 2 為圖表，原始資料未能以純文字擷取; average 平均)"}, {"pid": "111-P6", "year": 111, "genre": "說明文(網頁新聞報導)", "topic": "喀麥隆(Cameroon)的語言與權力問題", "text": "http://www.aab.com/news/language-and-power-756315\nLanguage and Power: Cameroon's Story\nBy Elisa Grant, 2 Oct 2017\n\nIn the modern world, being able to speak English is often a way to get power. However, this is not true for English speakers in Cameroon. To know why things are different in this African country, we need to go back one hundred years.\n\nIn 1919, Kamerun (the name of Cameroon at the time) was cut into two parts: one belonged to France, and the other belonged to the UK. In 1960, the French Cameroon became the Republic of Cameroun, and the UK's part joined it in 1961. The new country changed its name to the Federal Republic of Cameroon. Although both French and English are Cameroon's official languages, only around 20% of its people speak English. Also, the government has been in French speakers' hands since the two parts became one country.\n\nFor a long time, Cameroon's English speakers have felt they are not welcome in their own country. For example, it is very difficult for them to find jobs in the government, and they are often asked to speak French in business and at official events. They have become more resentful at the government and decided to fight for themselves. Since last year, the English speakers have tried to build their own country. Yesterday, they said in a public meeting that they were not part of Cameroon anymore. They are now a new country, \"Ambazonia.\" When the police tried to stop the meeting, at least eight people were killed.\n\nRead more\n\n(official 官方的; government 政府)"}, {"pid": "111-P7", "year": 111, "genre": "說明文(旅遊步道介紹)", "topic": "Southend步道健行旅遊介紹", "text": "THE SOUTHEND TRAIL has been popular with nature lovers for years. The 120-km trail passes beautiful lakes, crosses rivers, and goes through mountains and hills. This gives bird lovers some of the best places for birdwatching. The trail also takes you to the Southend Museum and to two famous castles, Edward Castle and Sloan Castle.\n\nIt's best to plan one day for one part of the trail and start your hike early in the morning, because each part takes at least seven hours. If you don't want to walk, you can bike, but make sure you stay on the main trail, because the side trails are not wide enough for biking.\n\nThere are two types of lodging for visitors. Camping is popular in summer, but it is only allowed on a few campgrounds (see the map). A more comfortable one is to stay at a hotel in one of the towns. You can find some very nice ones that also have breakfast.\n\n(trail 步道; recommend 推薦)\n(附有步道地圖，標示Parts 1, 2, 2a, 3, 4, 4a及Cove等地點，原始地圖圖像未能以純文字擷取。)"}, {"pid": "111-P8", "year": 111, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "回文(palindromes)與變位詞(anagrams)", "text": "English words are made of 26 letters, and palindromes and anagrams are two kinds of word games about spelling. A palindrome is a word or a sentence that reads the same from left to right or from right to left, 40 , \"eye,\" \"Bob,\" \"my gym,\" and \"Was it a car or a cat I saw?\" An anagram of a word or words is made by putting the letters of the word or words in a different way. Look at the words and their anagrams below. Can you think of other possible anagrams of these words?\n\nAnagrams are often longer words that don't really mean anything but are fun to say. Sometimes they can even mean something 42 , like when a common word, \"restaurant,\" becomes \"Eat rats, run!\"\n\nActually, palindromes and anagrams are 43 . Palindromes can be used to learn mathematics and make music. Anagrams are also a good way to hide something. In history, people often hid their important studies in anagrams. Can you think of any other way to use them?"}, {"pid": "110-P1", "year": 110, "genre": "廣告DM", "topic": "e-BeautiMed 線上商店集點優惠活動", "text": "We've prepared many wonderful surprises for you at e-BeautiMed, BeautiMed's online store!\n\nSurprise 1\nJoin \"BeautiMed Friend\" online for free and get 2000 BeautiMed points!\n\nSurprise 2\nAlready a \"BeautiMed Friend\"? Come collect your free gift by entering your \"BeautiMed Friend\" card number at e-BeautiMed before 8/31.\n\nSurprise 3\nGet 500 BeautiMed points by shopping at e-BeautiMed and you'll get 500 more points if you spend more than $1,000.\n\nSurprise 4\nShop at e-BeautiMed during 7/1-8/31 and you may win $5,000 or free movie tickets!\n\nSurprise 5\nInvite a friend to join \"BeautiMed Friend\" and you both can get 1000 points each!"}, {"pid": "110-P2", "year": 110, "genre": "對話", "topic": "Joey 與 Lynn 討論 Caldron 餐廳的火鍋用餐經驗", "text": "Joey: Lynn, have you tried Caldron? I've heard that restaurant is good.\nLynn: I have. I went there once for Tom's party.\nJoey: And?\nLynn: Well, I never thought I would have to cook for myself when eating out.\nJoey: But it's fun to cook your own food.\nLynn: I don't see any fun in that. Besides, I want nice food.\nJoey: So you didn't like the food there?\nLynn: Everything tasted the same. I mean, they were all cooked in the same boiling pot. How could they taste different? I just kept throwing strange things into the pot. I didn't even know what half the things were made of.\nJoey: Don't worry. Everything should be safe to eat after a hot bath in the pot. And you didn't get sick after that, right? Besides, you tried something different there. Still a good experience, I think?\nLynn: I don't think we share the same idea of good experiences."}, {"pid": "110-P3", "year": 110, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "Katie 的日記：關於綿羊 Woollie 的故事", "text": "Dear Diary, June 7, 2011\nI was very sad to hear what happened to Woollie yesterday. Woollie was my favorite sheep. I have a storybook about Woollie. It says when Woollie was four, he ran away from Mr. Armstrong's farm, and it took Mr. Armstrong six years to find Woollie. But Woollie had grown so much fleece that he didn't even look like a sheep. Mr. Armstrong decided to cut his fleece on TV so everyone could see. Daddy said this happened on the day I was born. Woollie's fleece weighed 27 kg, and could make clothes for 20 large men. I asked Daddy if his favorite vest was made from Woollie's fleece. Daddy said no, because Woollie's fleece was sold to collect money for sick kids. In the storybook, Woollie was taken to see Ms. Stella Clark, the leader of our city then. They even had tea together. Daddy said Woollie did meet Ms. Clark, but he wasn't sure if they had tea. Daddy said Woollie was put down because he was too sick and there was no way to help him. I cried. I hope Woollie will be happy up there in the sky.\n(fleece 羊毛 weigh 重達)"}, {"pid": "110-P4", "year": 110, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "介紹馬諦斯的名畫《鋼琴課》", "text": "Here's The Piano Lesson, one of Henri Matisse's most famous paintings. The boy in the picture is the painter's son, Pierre. In the picture, Pierre looks quite serious. Why? Well, look at the yellow candle on the red piano. It's almost burned down. So maybe Pierre has already practiced for hours. And Matisse uses a lot of gray, not a very fun color, right? It shows how the poor kid feels, don't you think?\nOn the top right corner, you can see a woman sitting straight on a seat. Is she Pierre's piano teacher? Or his mother? Well, if you're a Matisse fan, you'll know this is in fact another painting by him, Woman on a High Stool. Interesting, right? Matisse likes to do that a lot. In fact, there's another work by Matisse in the picture. Did you find it? Right! The sculpture on the bottom left corner!\nMatisse painted this picture in 1916. Pierre was already 16 then, but the artist painted his son much younger than he really was. Pierre had gone away to be a soldier, and Matisse didn't know whether he would come back. Maybe this is a worried father's way to remember the good old days.\n(sculpture 雕像)"}, {"pid": "110-P5", "year": 110, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "教師節的由來與歷史演變", "text": "On Teachers' Day, we thank our teachers for their hard work. We also celebrate this day to remember Confucius, the great Chinese teacher from 2,500 years ago. Well, that's everything we're taught about Teachers' Day. But, the first Teachers' Day was not on Confucius's birthday, and it was not about thanking our teachers.\nIn 1930, Mr. Tai Shuang-qiu and other teachers celebrated the first Teachers' Day in Nanjing. But there was nothing to celebrate. Teachers were paid very little and not respected. These teachers took this chance to shout out their problems. They had Teachers' Day on June 6 because the date was easy to remember and near the end of the school year. This action by Mr. Tai and the other teachers was welcomed and followed by teachers from other cities. In 1939, the government made Teachers' Day a national holiday. However, it was on August 27, the day when Confucius's birthday was celebrated. Not everyone hailed this decision: Teachers' Day was never about Confucius, and Confucius couldn't speak for all the teachers either.\nOne funny thing was that the government was wrong about the date of Confucius's birthday. In 1952, people found out he was in fact born on September 28. That was when we started to celebrate Teachers' Day on Confucius's real birthday.\n(respect 尊敬 government 政府)"}, {"pid": "110-P6", "year": 110, "genre": "公告通知", "topic": "國家寶島鐵路因颱風改道公告信件", "text": "Dear Traveler,\nYou have bought an NFR ticket online for a train that runs between White Water City and Cloud City. We are sorry to tell you that, because of the typhoon last month, the Sand Town – Spring Town line will be closed between August 14 and 28 2016. During this time, some trains will change lines and will not stop at a few stations. There will be free buses to take travelers to these stations. Please check below for the changes. Visit http://www.nfr.gov/ for more information.\nWe wish you a nice summer.\nLena Muller\nNational Formosa Railway\n\n1. Trains that run between Green City and Cloud City will take the Smoke Town – Spring Town line, and will stop at every station. Below are the trains that will change lines:\nGoing South: RL101 White Water City -> Cloud City; RL102 White Water City -> Spring Town; RL103 Green City -> Cloud City\nGoing North: RL201 Spring Town -> Green City; RL202 Cloud City -> Green City\n2. The free buses for the Sand Town – Spring Town line will wait at Green City (going south) and Spring Town (going north) stations. No stop at Gray Village.\n(Stations on the Sand Town - Spring Town line, north to south: Spring Town, Hill Town, Black Town, Gray Village, Sand Town; other stations: White Water City, Green City, Smoke Town, Cloud City)\n(line 路線)"}, {"pid": "110-P7", "year": 110, "genre": "說明文", "topic": "敘利亞 Darayya 地下祕密圖書館", "text": "SYRIA - Darayya\nIn Darayya, a city in Syria, there's a library, and it has 15,000 books on almost every subject you can think of. However, it is different from any libraries you know: It is a secret underground library, and only people in Darayya know where it is.\nOver the years, war has shaken Darayya badly. Every day, houses are bombed and people are killed. Stores are closed one after another, and so are schools. To help the kids in Darayya with their learning, Anas Ahmad, a 19-year-old student, and his friends decided to build a library. They built the library under the ground to keep it safe from bombing. But it is dangerous to collect books for the library. Often, Ahmad and his friends look for books in houses that were bombed. They need to be careful because they may be killed in another bombing.\nYou may ask, \"In a place like Darayya, would people be interested in books?\" \"Just like the body needs food, the mind needs books,\" says one library user. In the library, people enjoy their time of reading and forget about the terrible world above, so their life doesn't seem so hard. Through reading, they are able to dream of a better life after war.\n(war 戰爭 bomb 轟炸 seem 彷彿)"}, {"pid": "110-P8", "year": 110, "genre": "書信email", "topic": "Mia Loren 寄給 Dave Doddo 關於兒子生日派對的邀請信", "text": "From: Mia Loren <mloren@qmail.com>\nTo: Dave Doddo <dd1225@qmail.com>\nDate: Tue, Oct 24, 2017 at 10:01 AM\nSubject: Daniel's 5th Birthday Party – This Saturday!\n\nHello Dave,\nWe're happy to invite you and your family to Daniel's fifth birthday party this Saturday.\nWe know we told you that the party would be in  35 . However, we just moved to Carlton City last month, so the party won't be in Pattersons Town. It'll be at Mosman Garden right next to Victor Zoo, just across from our new apartment. Please don't go to Northbank Park next to our old house.\nThe weather report said that it may be rainy this weekend, but  36 . If it rains, we'll move the party inside our home. However, if we're  37  and it is fine, we'll still have the party at the garden.\nAgain, we're all very happy and excited to welcome you to join us for some fun this weekend!\nBest, Mia, Sam & Daniel"}, {"pid": "110-P9", "year": 110, "genre": "記敘文", "topic": "夜晚穿越公園時因誤會而受到驚嚇的故事", "text": "Usually I wouldn't cross the park at this time of night. But walking around the park would take more time, and it was raining so hard that I couldn't even see clearly what was right before me. So I entered the park. And that was the first stupid thing I did tonight. Soon after I walked into the park, I saw a man under a tree up ahead. My heart fell. The stories I'd heard about the park  38  into my head at this moment. Anyone with a clear mind would just turn back. But me? No. I did  39  stupid thing: I decided to hurry past him. Just when I was passing the man, he raised his head and gave me the strangest smile ever. I got scared and started running. \"Hey!\" the man shouted from behind. \"Wait!\" He was running after me! I ran like crazy. I had hoped the trees would keep some rain off. And they  40 . But they also made the park look even darker. I couldn't see what was ahead of me. Then, I ran into something. It was the man! \"Don't kill me!\" I cried. \"What? I  41  to give back your bag! You dropped it,\" the man gave me my bag. Now, I felt saying that to the man was the stupidest thing I did tonight.\n(ahead 在前面)"}], "translation": [{"id": "T1", "pattern": "感官動詞 watch/see + O + Ving/原形", "keyPoint": "感官動詞 + O + Ving", "zh": "我看到他正在打籃球。", "options": ["I saw him plays basketball.", "I saw him played basketball.", "I saw him to play basketball.", "I saw him playing basketball."], "answer": "D", "explain": "感官動詞 see + 受詞 + Ving（表示看到動作正在進行）為正解。A動詞形式錯(plays不可用)；C不可加to；B用過去式動詞形式錯誤，感官動詞後不接過去式。"}, {"id": "T2", "pattern": "感官動詞 watch/see + O + Ving/原形", "keyPoint": "感官動詞 + O + 原形V", "zh": "她每天都聽到小鳥在窗外唱歌。", "options": ["She hear birds singing outside the window every day.", "She hears birds sang outside the window every day.", "She hears birds sing outside the window every day.", "She hears birds to sing outside the window every day."], "answer": "C", "explain": "感官動詞 hear + O + 原形動詞(sing)表示聽到整個動作，正解為C。D多加to錯誤；A主詞she為第三人稱單數，動詞需用hears而非hear；B用過去式sang錯誤。"}, {"id": "T3", "pattern": "感官動詞 watch/see + O + Ving/原形", "keyPoint": "感官動詞 + O + Ving", "zh": "他們看到那隻狗在追一隻貓。", "options": ["They watch the dog chasing a cat yesterday.", "They watched the dog to chase a cat.", "They watched the dog chases a cat.", "They watched the dog chasing a cat."], "answer": "D", "explain": "watch + O + Ving表示看到動作進行中，正解為D。C動詞形式錯誤(chases不可用)；B不可加to；A句中已有yesterday卻用現在式watch，時態錯誤。"}, {"id": "T4", "pattern": "使役動詞 make/let/help + 人 + 原形V", "keyPoint": "使役動詞 let + 人 + 原形V", "zh": "媽媽讓我晚上十點以後不能出門。", "options": ["Mom didn't let me going out after ten at night.", "Mom doesn't let me to go out after ten at night.", "Mom doesn't let me go out after ten at night.", "Mom doesn't lets me go out after ten at night."], "answer": "C", "explain": "let + 人 + 原形V為使役動詞句型，正解為C。B多加to錯誤；D否定句doesn't後動詞應用原形let，不可加s；A用let後接Ving錯誤，且時態與句意不符。"}, {"id": "T5", "pattern": "使役動詞 make/let/help + 人 + 原形V", "keyPoint": "使役動詞 make + 人 + 原形V", "zh": "這部電影讓我哭了。", "options": ["This movie made me crying.", "This movie made me to cry.", "This movie made me cry.", "This movie makes me cried."], "answer": "C", "explain": "make + 人 + 原形V為使役動詞句型，表示「使某人做...」，正解為C。B多加to錯誤；A用Ving錯誤；D時態前後不一致，makes(現在式)配cried(過去式)矛盾。"}, {"id": "T6", "pattern": "使役動詞 make/let/help + 人 + 原形V", "keyPoint": "使役動詞 help + 人 + 原形V", "zh": "老師幫助學生們了解這個難題。", "options": ["The teacher helps the students understanding the difficult problem.", "The teacher helps the students understand the difficult problem.", "The teacher help the students understand the difficult problem.", "The teacher helps the students to understanding the difficult problem."], "answer": "B", "explain": "help + 人 + 原形V(或to V)，此處用原形understand，正解為B。D同時用to又加Ving錯誤混用；C主詞teacher為第三人稱單數，動詞應用helps；A help後接Ving不符合此句型用法。"}, {"id": "T7", "pattern": "want/ask/tell + 人 + to V", "keyPoint": "want + 人 + to V", "zh": "媽媽要我早點回家。", "options": ["Mom want me to go home early.", "Mom wants me go home early.", "Mom wants that I go home early.", "Mom wants me to go home early."], "answer": "D", "explain": "want + 人 + to V為正確句型，正解為D。B漏掉to；C錯用that子句，此句型不用that；A主詞Mom為第三人稱單數，動詞須用wants。"}, {"id": "T8", "pattern": "want/ask/tell + 人 + to V", "keyPoint": "ask + 人 + to V", "zh": "她請我幫她拿一杯水。", "options": ["She asked me get her a glass of water.", "She asked to me to get her a glass of water.", "She asked me to get her a glass of water.", "She asked me getting her a glass of water."], "answer": "C", "explain": "ask + 人 + to V為正確句型，正解為C。D應用to V而非Ving；A漏掉to；B asked後直接加受詞，不需加to me。"}, {"id": "T9", "pattern": "want/ask/tell + 人 + to V", "keyPoint": "tell + 人 + to V", "zh": "老師告訴我們要準時交作業。", "options": ["The teacher tells us handing in our homework on time.", "The teacher tells us hand in our homework on time.", "The teacher tell us to hand in our homework on time.", "The teacher tells us to hand in our homework on time."], "answer": "D", "explain": "tell + 人 + to V為正確句型，正解為D。A應用to V而非Ving；C主詞teacher為第三人稱單數，動詞須用tells；B漏掉to。"}, {"id": "T10", "pattern": "enjoy/keep + Ving", "keyPoint": "enjoy + Ving", "zh": "我弟弟喜歡玩電動遊戲。", "options": ["My brother enjoys to play video games.", "My brother enjoys playing video games.", "My brother enjoys play video games.", "My brother enjoy playing video games."], "answer": "B", "explain": "enjoy + Ving為固定句型，正解為B。A enjoy不可接to V；D主詞brother為第三人稱單數，動詞須用enjoys；C enjoy後須加Ving而非原形動詞。"}, {"id": "T11", "pattern": "enjoy/keep + Ving", "keyPoint": "keep + Ving", "zh": "那個嬰兒一直哭個不停。", "options": ["The baby keeps crying.", "The baby keeps cried.", "The baby keeps to cry.", "The baby keep crying."], "answer": "A", "explain": "keep + Ving表示持續做某事，正解為A。C keep不可接to V；D主詞baby為第三人稱單數，動詞須用keeps；B keeps後應接Ving而非過去式動詞。"}, {"id": "T12", "pattern": "enjoy/keep + Ving", "keyPoint": "enjoy + Ving", "zh": "她很享受和朋友們聊天。", "options": ["She enjoys to chatting with her friends.", "She enjoy chatting with her friends.", "She enjoys chatting with her friends.", "She enjoys chat with her friends."], "answer": "C", "explain": "enjoy + Ving為正確句型，正解為C。D應用Ving而非原形動詞；B主詞she為第三人稱單數，動詞須用enjoys；A同時用to又加Ving為混用錯誤。"}, {"id": "T13", "pattern": "want/decide + to V", "keyPoint": "want + to V", "zh": "我想要學習彈吉他。", "options": ["I want to learn how to play the guitar.", "I want learn how to play the guitar.", "I wants to learn how to play the guitar.", "I want learning how to play the guitar."], "answer": "A", "explain": "want + to V為正確句型，正解為A。D應接to V而非Ving；B漏掉to；C主詞I不可加s於動詞want。"}, {"id": "T14", "pattern": "want/decide + to V", "keyPoint": "decide + to V", "zh": "他決定放棄吃甜食。", "options": ["He decided giving up eating sweets.", "He decided to give up eating sweets.", "He decided give up eating sweets.", "He decide to give up eating sweets."], "answer": "B", "explain": "decide + to V為正確句型(此句中give up後才接Ving)，正解為B。A decide應接to V而非Ving；D過去式應為decided；C漏掉to。"}, {"id": "T15", "pattern": "want/decide + to V", "keyPoint": "had better + 原形V（動詞句型延伸辨析）", "zh": "你最好去看醫生。", "options": ["You had better to see a doctor.", "You had better sees a doctor.", "You had better see a doctor.", "You had better seeing a doctor."], "answer": "C", "explain": "had better + 原形V為固定句型（雖非want/decide，但同屬動詞句型常見易混淆考點：had better後不加to），正解為C。A多加to錯誤；D應用原形而非Ving；B不可加s。"}, {"id": "T16", "pattern": "there be", "keyPoint": "there be 句型", "zh": "教室裡有二十張桌子。", "options": ["Twenty desks are there in the classroom.", "There are twenty desks in the classroom.", "There have twenty desks in the classroom.", "There is twenty desks in the classroom."], "answer": "B", "explain": "there be 句型：There + be動詞 + 主詞(+地點)，be動詞要依「主詞」單複數決定，這裡 twenty desks 是複數，要用 are。D 用 is 與複數主詞不合；A 語序錯，there be 句型固定用 There 開頭；C 誤用 have，there be 只能搭配 be 動詞，不能用 have。"}, {"id": "T17", "pattern": "there be", "keyPoint": "there be 句型（過去式否定）", "zh": "去年這裡沒有公園。", "options": ["There isn't a park here last year.", "There wasn't a park here last year.", "There didn't a park here last year.", "There weren't a park here last year."], "answer": "B", "explain": "過去式否定：There wasn't/weren't + 主詞。a park 是單數，要用 wasn't。A 用現在式 isn't 與 last year 時態不合；C be動詞句型不可加 didn't（didn't 後要接原形動詞，be動詞本身沒有 do-support）；D weren't 用於複數主詞，這裡 a park 是單數應用 wasn't。"}, {"id": "T18", "pattern": "it 虛主詞 + to V", "keyPoint": "it 虛主詞 + to V", "zh": "學英文很有趣。", "options": ["It is interesting to learn English.", "English is interesting to learn it.", "It is interesting to learning English.", "Learn English is interesting."], "answer": "A", "explain": "虛主詞句型：It is + 形容詞 + to V，用 It 代替真正主詞（不定詞片語），避免句子開頭太長。D 動詞 Learn 不能直接當主詞使用（需改成 Learning 或用 It...to V）；C to 後面應接原形動詞，不可加 to learning；B 句尾多餘的 it 重複，且主詞用法錯誤。"}, {"id": "T19", "pattern": "it 虛主詞 + to V", "keyPoint": "it 虛主詞 + to V", "zh": "在這裡游泳是危險的。", "options": ["It is dangerous to swim here.", "Swim here is dangerous.", "It is dangerous swimming here.", "It is dangerous to swimming here."], "answer": "A", "explain": "It is + 形容詞 + to V 的固定句型，此處為 It is dangerous to swim here。B 動詞原形不能直接當句子主詞；D to 後方要接原形動詞 swim，不可用 swimming；C 雖然文法上可用動名詞當主詞，但此題考的是 it...to V 句型，直接省略 to 是常見誤用。"}, {"id": "T20", "pattern": "so...that", "keyPoint": "so...that", "zh": "這題目太難了，所以沒有人能解出來。", "options": ["The question is so difficult that no one can solve it.", "The question is so difficult to that no one can solve it.", "The question is such difficult that no one can solve it.", "The question is too difficult that no one can solve it."], "answer": "A", "explain": "so + 形容詞 + that + 子句，表示「太...以致於...」。D 誤把 so 換成 too，too 不能接 that 子句（too 要接 to V）；C such 後面應接「名詞」或「形容詞+名詞」，不能直接接形容詞 difficult；B so...that 中間不可再加 to，語意重複多餘。"}, {"id": "T21", "pattern": "so...that", "keyPoint": "so...that", "zh": "他跑得太快了，以至於沒人能追上他。", "options": ["He ran too fast that nobody could catch up with him.", "He ran so fast so nobody could catch up with him.", "He ran such fast that nobody could catch up with him.", "He ran so fast that nobody could catch up with him."], "answer": "D", "explain": "so + 副詞/形容詞 + that 子句是正確固定用法。A too 不能接 that 子句；B 兩個 so 重複，第二個連接詞應為 that，不能用 so 再接一次；C such 不可直接修飾形容詞/副詞 fast，such 後要接名詞。"}, {"id": "T22", "pattern": "too...to", "keyPoint": "too...to", "zh": "這杯茶太燙了，不能喝。", "options": ["This cup of tea is too hot to drink it.", "This cup of tea is too hot to drink.", "This cup of tea is too hot that drink.", "This cup of tea is so hot to drink."], "answer": "B", "explain": "too + 形容詞 + to V，表示「太...而不能...」，to V 後不可再加受詞 it（因為邏輯受詞就是主詞 tea 本身）。A 多餘的 it 是常見錯誤；D so 不能接 to V，只能接 that 子句；C too...to 句型中間不能插入 that，這是混淆了 so...that 的用法。"}, {"id": "T23", "pattern": "too...to", "keyPoint": "too...to", "zh": "她太累了，無法讀書。", "options": ["She is too tired to study.", "She is too tired for study.", "She is too tired studying.", "She is so tired to study."], "answer": "A", "explain": "too + 形容詞 + to V 表示「太...以致於不能...」。C to 後面要接原形動詞 study，不可用動名詞 studying；D so 不能直接接 to V，only too 能這樣用；B for 後面接名詞的用法在此語意生硬且不符合 too...to 固定句型。"}, {"id": "T24", "pattern": "not...until", "keyPoint": "not...until", "zh": "他直到昨晚才回家。", "options": ["He went home until last night.", "He didn't go home until last night.", "He isn't go home until last night.", "He didn't went home until last night."], "answer": "B", "explain": "not...until 表示「直到...才...」，過去式否定為 didn't + 原形動詞。A 缺少否定詞，語意變成「他到昨晚才回家」但少了「直到才」的否定強調；D didn't 後面應接原形動詞 go，不可用過去式 went（雙重過去式錯誤）；C 用現在式 isn't 搭配過去時間 last night 時態不一致，且 be動詞不能這樣用來否定一般動詞。"}, {"id": "T25", "pattern": "not...until", "keyPoint": "not...until", "zh": "我直到看完那部電影才知道結局。", "options": ["I didn't know the ending until I finished watching the movie.", "I didn't know the ending after I finished watching the movie.", "I not knew the ending until I finished watching the movie.", "I don't know the ending until I finished watching the movie."], "answer": "A", "explain": "not...until 句型要用 until 表示「直到...才」，而不是 after。B 誤用 after，語意變成「電影看完後才知道」而非強調「直到才」的句型；D 用現在式 don't 與過去事件不合，應用過去式 didn't；C not 不能直接放在一般動詞前否定，需用助動詞 didn't + 原形動詞。"}, {"id": "T26", "pattern": "would like to", "keyPoint": "would like to", "zh": "我想要喝一杯柳橙汁。", "options": ["I would like to drinking a glass of orange juice.", "I like to drink a glass of orange juice.", "I would like drink a glass of orange juice.", "I would like to drink a glass of orange juice."], "answer": "D", "explain": "would like to + 原形動詞，表示禮貌地表達「想要」。C 漏掉 to；A to 後面應接原形動詞 drink，不可加 Ving；B 少了 would，變成一般的「喜歡」語氣，與「想要」的委婉語氣不同。"}, {"id": "T27", "pattern": "would like to", "keyPoint": "would like to", "zh": "你想要去看電影嗎？", "options": ["Would you like to go to the movies?", "Would you like going to the movies?", "Do you like to go to the movies?", "Would you like to going to the movies?"], "answer": "A", "explain": "Would you like to + 原形動詞? 用來禮貌地詢問對方的意願。C 用 Do you like 表示「你是否喜歡（習慣性）」，與「你想不想去（當下的意願）」語意不同；B to 被省略且動詞用了 going，錯誤；D to 後面應接原形動詞 go，不可用 to going。"}, {"id": "T28", "pattern": "had better", "keyPoint": "had better", "zh": "你最好現在就出發。", "options": ["You had better leave now.", "You had better leaving now.", "You had better to leave now.", "You have better leave now."], "answer": "A", "explain": "had better + 原形動詞，表示「最好...」的建議語氣，had 是固定用法不隨主詞改變。C 動詞前不可加 to；D 誤把 had 寫成 have，此句型固定用 had（不論現在或過去語境）；B 動詞應為原形 leave，不可用 leaving。"}, {"id": "T29", "pattern": "be going to", "keyPoint": "be going to", "zh": "他們明天要去海邊。", "options": ["They are going to went to the beach tomorrow.", "They are going go to the beach tomorrow.", "They going to go to the beach tomorrow.", "They are going to go to the beach tomorrow."], "answer": "D", "explain": "be going to + 原形動詞，表示已計畫好的未來動作。A to 後面要接原形動詞 go，不可用過去式 went；C 缺少 be動詞 are，going to 前必須有 be 動詞；B 漏掉了 go 前面的 to，應為 going to go。"}, {"id": "T30", "pattern": "祈使句", "keyPoint": "祈使句", "zh": "請把窗戶打開。", "options": ["Please opens the window.", "Please to open the window.", "Please open the window.", "Please opening the window."], "answer": "C", "explain": "祈使句直接以「原形動詞」開頭（可加 please 更禮貌），不需要主詞也不需要 to。B 動詞前不可加 to；A 祈使句動詞用原形，不可加第三人稱單數的 -s；D 不可用動名詞 opening 開頭，須用原形動詞 open。"}, {"id": "T31", "pattern": "as...as", "keyPoint": "as...as 同等比較", "zh": "他和他哥哥一樣高。", "options": ["He is as tall as his brother.", "He is as tall than his brother.", "He is as taller as his brother.", "He is so tall as his brother."], "answer": "A", "explain": "正解結構為 as + 原級形容詞 + as，tall 不可加 er 也不可搭配 than；B 誤用 than（as...as 才對，than 要搭配比較級）；D 誤用 so...as（so...as 只用在否定句 not so...as）；C 誤把原級 tall 改成比較級 taller，與 as...as 不搭。"}, {"id": "T32", "pattern": "not as...as", "keyPoint": "not as...as 否定同等比較", "zh": "這本書沒有那本書那麼有趣。", "options": ["This book is not as interesting than that one.", "This book isn't so interesting than that one.", "This book doesn't as interesting as that one.", "This book is not as interesting as that one."], "answer": "D", "explain": "否定同等比較為 be動詞 + not as + 原級 + as；A、B 都誤用 than（as/so 應搭配 as，不能搭配 than）；C 用一般動詞 doesn't 卻少了 be 動詞，且 interesting 前不能直接接 not as 前少了 is。"}, {"id": "T33", "pattern": "one of the + 最高級", "keyPoint": "one of the + 最高級 + 複數名詞", "zh": "台北101是世界上最高的建築物之一。", "options": ["Taipei 101 is one of the tallest buildings in the world.", "Taipei 101 is one of the taller buildings in the world.", "Taipei 101 is one of the tallest building in the world.", "Taipei 101 is one of tallest buildings in the world."], "answer": "A", "explain": "句型為 one of the + 最高級形容詞 + 複數名詞；C 誤用單數 building（one of the + 複數名詞才對）；D 漏掉 the（最高級前一定要有 the）；B 誤用比較級 taller，應該用最高級 tallest。"}, {"id": "T34", "pattern": "one of the + 最高級", "keyPoint": "one of the + 最高級 + 複數名詞", "zh": "她是我班上最聰明的學生之一。", "options": ["She is one of the smartest students in my class.", "She is one of smartest students in my class.", "She is one of the smartest student in my class.", "She is one the smartest students in my class."], "answer": "A", "explain": "one of the smartest students 為固定結構：one of + the + 最高級 + 複數名詞；C 名詞誤用單數；B 漏掉 the；D 漏掉 of（應為 one of the，不是 one the）。"}, {"id": "T35", "pattern": "both...and", "keyPoint": "both...and 對等連接（複數動詞）", "zh": "湯姆和瑪莉都喜歡游泳。", "options": ["Both Tom and Mary is like swimming.", "Both Tom and Mary like swimming.", "Both Tom or Mary like swimming.", "Both Tom and Mary likes swimming."], "answer": "B", "explain": "both B and D 視為複數主詞，動詞用原形 like；D 誤用單數動詞 likes；C 誤把 and 改成 or（both 只能搭配 and，不能搭配 or）；A 誤加 be動詞 is 又接一般動詞 like，動詞重複錯誤。"}, {"id": "T36", "pattern": "both...and", "keyPoint": "both...and 對等連接（詞性一致）", "zh": "這件襯衫既便宜又漂亮。", "options": ["This shirt both is cheap and beautiful.", "This shirt is both cheap or beautiful.", "This shirt is both cheap and beautiful.", "This shirt is both cheap and beautifully."], "answer": "C", "explain": "both + 形容詞 + and + 形容詞，兩邊詞性要一致（都是形容詞）；D 誤把 beautiful 改成副詞 beautifully，詞性不一致；A 語序錯誤，both 應放在 be 動詞之後、兩形容詞之前；B 誤把 and 換成 or。"}, {"id": "T37", "pattern": "either...or", "keyPoint": "either...or 二選一", "zh": "你可以選咖啡或茶。", "options": ["You can choose either coffee and tea.", "You can choose either coffee or tea.", "You can choose either coffee nor tea.", "You can choose neither coffee or tea."], "answer": "B", "explain": "either B or A 表示兩者選一；A 誤把 or 換成 and，語意錯誤（either 只能搭配 or）；D 誤把 either 換成 neither，neither 該搭配 nor 而不是 or；C either 卻搭配 nor，兩者不成對搭配。"}, {"id": "T38", "pattern": "either...or", "keyPoint": "either...or 二選一（主詞位置）", "zh": "不是你去，就是我去。", "options": ["Either you or I go will.", "Both you or I will go.", "Either you and I will go.", "Either you or I will go."], "answer": "D", "explain": "either D or A 放在主詞位置，動詞依 or 後面較近的主詞決定，will go 語序正確；A will go 語序顛倒錯誤；B 誤把 either 換成 both，但 both 該搭配 and 而非 or；C either 卻搭配 and，兩者不成對。"}, {"id": "T39", "pattern": "附加問句", "keyPoint": "附加問句（肯定句+否定問句）", "zh": "你喜歡打籃球，對不對？", "options": ["You like playing basketball, do you?", "You like playing basketball, doesn't you?", "You like playing basketball, don't you?", "You like playing basketball, aren't you?"], "answer": "C", "explain": "附加問句：前面肯定句，後面用否定簡答，且動詞須依主要動詞 like（一般動詞）用 don't；A 少了否定 not；D 誤用 be 動詞 aren't，但主要句是一般動詞 like，該用 don't；B doesn't 主詞不合（You 該搭配 don't 而非 doesn't）。"}, {"id": "T40", "pattern": "附加問句", "keyPoint": "附加問句（否定句+肯定問句）", "zh": "她不是老師，對吧？", "options": ["She isn't a teacher, is not she?", "She isn't a teacher, does she?", "She isn't a teacher, is she?", "She isn't a teacher, isn't she?"], "answer": "C", "explain": "前面否定句，後面附加問句要用肯定簡答 is she；D 仍用否定 isn't，錯誤（前否定、後應肯定）；B 誤用一般動詞 does，但主要句用 be 動詞 isn't，附加問句也該用 be 動詞；A 附加問句的否定形式該縮寫成 isn't，不能寫成 is not she。"}, {"id": "T41", "pattern": "so do I", "keyPoint": "so + 助動詞 + 主詞（附和肯定句）", "zh": "我哥哥喜歡打棒球，我也是。", "options": ["My brother likes playing baseball, and so I do.", "My brother likes playing baseball, and so am I.", "My brother likes playing baseball, and I do so.", "My brother likes playing baseball, and so do I."], "answer": "D", "explain": "so + 助動詞 + 主詞 表示「也是」，前句為一般動詞 likes，故用 so do I；A 語序錯誤，so 之後應該是助動詞在前、主詞在後；B 誤用 be 動詞 am，前句是一般動詞應搭配 do；C 語序與用法都不符合 so 倒裝句型。"}, {"id": "T42", "pattern": "so do I", "keyPoint": "so + 助動詞 + 主詞（時態一致）", "zh": "我媽媽昨天很累，我也是。", "options": ["My mom was tired yesterday, and so I was.", "My mom was tired yesterday, and so was I.", "My mom was tired yesterday, and so did I.", "My mom was tired yesterday, and so am I."], "answer": "B", "explain": "前句用 be 動詞過去式 was，附和句也要用 so + was + 主詞；C 誤用助動詞 did，但前句是 be 動詞不是一般動詞；A 語序錯誤，so 之後應為 was I 而非 I was；D 時態錯誤，前句過去式 was，附和句卻用現在式 am。"}, {"id": "T43", "pattern": "連接詞 although", "keyPoint": "although 讓步連接詞（不可與but並用）", "zh": "雖然下雨了，但是我們還是出去了。", "options": ["Although it rained, but we still went out.", "Because it rained, we still went out.", "Although it rained, we still went out.", "Although it rained, so we still went out."], "answer": "C", "explain": "although 表示「雖然」，中文雖然常搭配「但是」，但英文 although 與 but 不能同時出現在一個句子；A 犯了 although...but 重複連接詞的常見錯誤；B 誤用 because（因為），語意不符（下雨不是出去的原因）；D 誤用 so，也是重複連接詞錯誤。"}, {"id": "T44", "pattern": "連接詞 because", "keyPoint": "because 因果連接詞（不可與so並用）", "zh": "因為天氣很冷，所以他穿了外套。", "options": ["The weather was cold, because he wore a coat.", "Although the weather was cold, he wore a coat.", "Because the weather was cold, he wore a coat.", "Because the weather was cold, so he wore a coat."], "answer": "C", "explain": "because 表原因，中文「因為...所以」在英文 because 和 so 不能同時出現在一句；D 犯了 because...so 重複連接詞的常見錯誤；A 語序顛倒導致因果關係錯誤（變成因為他穿外套所以天氣冷）；B 誤用 although（雖然），語意變成讓步而非因果。"}, {"id": "T45", "pattern": "連接詞 or", "keyPoint": "祈使句 + or（否則）", "zh": "快點，不然你會遲到。", "options": ["Hurry up, but you will be late.", "Hurry up, so you will be late.", "Hurry up, and you will late.", "Hurry up, or you will be late."], "answer": "D", "explain": "祈使句 + or 表示「否則、不然」；A 誤用 but（但是），語意不合；B 誤用 so（所以），語意變成「快點所以你會遲到」，邏輯錯誤；C 誤用 and 且動詞 will late 少了 be 動詞，應為 will be late。"}], "meta": {"src": "教育部心測中心110-115", "reading": 256, "trans": 45, "img": 30, "hard": 83, "fixed": "qa-round1"}};